title: broccoli casserole
directions: Undercook broccoli.
Combine and mix well.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Pour over broccoli.
Cover with Cheese Nips.
Bake in 2-quart casserole dish at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: crab and spinach dip
directions: Saute onion in margarine.
Add crabmeat and spinach; add Parmesan cheese to taste.
Yield:
15 servings.

title: cottage cheese salad
directions: Sprinkle cottage cheese with wild strawberry Jell-O.
Add drained fruit cocktail and Cool Whip.
Chill and serve on lettuce leaf.

title: easy bread
directions: Mix together; pour in baking dish, sprayed with Pam, or drop onto a cookie sheet in single serving sizes.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Mix together shortening, brown sugar and dark molasses.
Then stir in cold water.
Sift together and add flour and all other ingredients.
Chill dough.
Roll out very thick (1/2-inch).
Cut with 2 1/2-inch round cutter.
Place far apart on lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for about 15 minutes.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Combine water, sugar, cornstarch and mashed strawberries. Cook.
Place in pie shell.
Cool a bit and add 3 cups strawberries on top of pie.
Add Cool Whip.

title: beef biscuit casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Mix beans and meat together; add remaining ingredients, except cheese and biscuits.
Pour into a casserole dish.
Cut biscuits in halves; place cut sides down on meat and bean mixture.
Sprinkle cheese over biscuits.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: marinated tomato salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Refrigerate at least 4 hours.
Serve cold.

title: easy fruit salad
directions: Mix the partially drained pineapple with the instant lemon pudding mix.
Add the drained fruit cocktail and drained mandarin oranges.
Add bananas last, before serving.

title: shrimp mousse a'la ruth adelle
directions: Heat tomato soup to boiling. May season to taste with salt, red pepper, Worcestershire sauce, etc. Add Tabasco sauce. Soften gelatine in 1/2 cup cold water, then add to hot soup until dissolved. Remove from heat and pour in blender, adding cream cheese, shrimp, lemon juice, celery, onion and bell pepper. Blend until all ingredients are well blended. Add parsley flakes or celery flakes to season if desired. Stir in mayonnaise. Pour in well greased mold and chill.

title: best macaroni bake
directions: Cook macaroni in boiling salted water for 7 to 10 minutes; drain.
Add remaining ingredients; mix lightly.
Season to taste. Pour into a greased 2-quart casserole.
Bake in a 325° oven for 45 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Sift dry ingredients; add nuts and raisins.
Dissolve soda in 1 cup hot water.
Mix.
Add vanilla, butter and flour.
Bake in tube pan in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: microwave pickles
directions: Mix and put in 2 qt. casserole covered.
Microwave on high 7 - 8 minutes stirring twice until cucumbers are crisp and tender and onion is translucent.
Ladle into glass jar (rinsed with hot water).

title: traditional irish soda bread
directions: *To make buttermilk, to 1 cup of milk, add 2 to 3 teaspoons of cider vinegar and let stand for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: crusty bread stuffed with sausage
directions: Cook sausage; drain and set aside.
Saute onions in margarine. Add bell pepper, zucchini and mushrooms.
Cook until veggies are crisply-tender (10 minutes).
Stir in remaining ingredients except bread.
Cook 5 to 7 minutes.
Add sausage.
Cut thin lengthwise slice off top of bread.
Hollow out center of bread, leaving 1-inch shell.
Place bread on cookie sheet; bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes or until crusty.
Fill hot bread with sausage mixture.
Cut bread into wedges.

title: danny's beef tips
directions: Put meat, sauce, oil and water into skillet.
Bring to a boil for 15 to 20 minutes and pour out all of sauce and water.
Brown for 1 to 2 minutes and serve.
Serves 7 to 8.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: *Mushrooms, broccoli, cauliflower, carrots, black olives, finely chopped, can be used.

title: angel food cake
directions: Allow egg whites to set at room temperature for 1 hour before mixing.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Sift four times into a sheet of waxed paper, the cake flour and 3/4 cup sugar.
In a large mixing bowl, combine egg whites, cream of tartar, salt, vanilla extract and almond extract.
Beat on speed 12 until egg whites form soft peaks.
Do not overbeat.
Turn to speed 8 and rapidly sprinkle in remaining 1 cup of sugar.
Scrape sides of bowl as necessary.

title: pecan tassies(yields about 15)
directions: Mix together until smooth and chill.
Shape dough into balls. Pat each ball into an ungreased muffin tin, shaping into a shell.

title: apple pie
directions: Prepare favorite pastry for double crust 9-inch pie.
Mix together dry ingredients.
Toss with fruit and lemon juice.
Turn into pastry lined pie plate.
Dot with margarine.
Make several slits in top crust.
Cover pie with top crust.
Seal and flute edges.
Bake in 425° oven for 50 minutes or until crust is brown.

title: old fashioned cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour in a sheet cake pan.
Bake until done.

title: baked chicken and rice
directions: Line up bottom of a 9 x 11-inch baking dish with enough heavy duty baking foil to make a tent.
Spread rice evenly in bottom. Spread over the cream of mushroom soup and the chicken soup. Place chicken pieces on top of soups.
Pour over the water. Sprinkle with dry onion mushroom soup.
Dot with dabs of butter. Bake in 350° oven for about 2 hours.
Uncover and serve.

title: dump cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spread pie filling evenly in bottom of greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Arrange the pineapple chunks over cherries and sprinkle with cake mix.
Cover with melted butter and top with coconut and nuts.
Bake for 1 hour or until done.
Good served hot or cold.

title: pan' pan' do
directions: Beat eggs together and then add cinnamon, sugar and milk. In pan, melt butter or margarine. Dip bread in egg mixture, then fry in butter on both sides until brown. Serve with cold milk.

title: marinated pasta salad
directions: Cook shells; drain and rinse.
Transfer shells to a bowl and toss with olive oil.
Cover and chill 30 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Serve very cold.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Combine and chill.
Served with carrot sticks, celery sticks etc.
Also good with chips.

title: brownies
directions: This amount makes 1 (8 x 8-inch) square brownie pan. I always double the recipe and make 1 (13 x 9-inch) pan.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cream margarine and both sugars thoroughly.
Beat in egg and vanilla.
Sift together the flour, baking soda and salt.
Mix the dry ingredients with batter.
Stir in the chocolate chips.
Drop by teaspoon on a baking sheet 2 inches apart.
Bake 10 minutes.
Makes about 2 dozen cookies.

title: knickerbocker salad
directions: Thaw peas in strainer.	Remove	moisture
by placing on paper towel on cookie sheet.
Mix
all
ingredients.
Make the day before, if possible.

title: broccoli corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients, adding corn bread or corn muffin mix last. Mix well and pour into 9 x 13 casserole.
Bake 30 minutes at 425°. Serve hot.
Enjoy!

title: pound cake
directions: Preheat oven
Combine all ingredients, mixing well. Pour into greased
and floured tube pan.
Bake 45 to 60 minutes.

title: miniature pizzas
directions: Brown sausage in skillet until meat begins to color.
Add onion and green pepper.
Saute until tender (do not brown).
Add garlic and cook for 1 minute.
Stir in tomato sauce, mushrooms, chili powder, oregano and basil.
Bring to a boil, then reduce heat and simmer for 20 minutes.
Stir mixture well.
(If mixture is too thick, add a little bit of water.)
Let cool.
Place English muffin halves on baking sheet.
Spoon on mixture. Sprinkle with cheese and freeze.

title: roasted vegetable salad
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Make vinaigrette dressing.
Dice squash and peppers into 1/4-inch pieces.
In large bowl, toss squash, peppers, onion, garlic, olive oil, salt and pepper until vegetables are well coated.
Spread vegetables on two large cookie sheets and toast 10 minutes, stirring once.
Allow vegetables to cool.
Transfer vegetables to a large bowl.
Add corn and tomatoes.
Toss this mixture and the greens separately with just enough vinaigrette to coat lightly.
Arrange greens on salad plate and top with vegetable mixture.
Makes 8 servings.

title: blueberry cobbler
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch in pan.
Stir in water.
Bring to boil and boil 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Add fruit and pour into baking dish or pie pan (I use 10-inch pie pan).
Dot with butter and cinnamon for topping.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Pour milk and oil into measuring cup.
Add all at once to flour.
Mix until ball forms.
Drop by spoonfuls onto fruit.
Bake at 425° for 25 to 30 minutes until dough is lightly browned.

title: hoagie salad
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Chill and serve.

title: spiced pecans
directions: Whip egg whites until frothy. Add water, sugar and cinnamon. In a 9 x 12-inch cake pan, melt the butter or margarine. Pour pecans in egg white mixture; stir well and then pour into pan. Bake at 250° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: plum cake
directions: Mix all ingredients, except nuts.
Fold in nuts.
Bake in Bundt pan at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: strawberry tarts
directions: Mix all ingredients except jam.
Grease jelly roll pan.
Pat 3/4 of dough on bottom.
Spread with jam.
Sprinkle rest on top (as crumbs).
Bake about 30 minutes in 350° oven.
Bake until golden, not too dark.
Cut into squares when cool.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Saute butter and onion.
Add flour, then add milk and cheese. Cook over low to medium temperature.
In another kettle, bring water to boil (chicken cubes in water).
Then add broccoli.
When broccoli is tender, put water and broccoli in blender; don't make too fine.
Add this to milk on stove; stir.
It's now ready to eat (this is a really quick way to make this soup).

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour in greased baking dish. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: morning glorious muffins
directions: Combine flour, sugar, soda, cinnamon and salt.
In another bowl, combine carrot, apple, coconut, dates and pecans.
Stir in beaten eggs, oil and vanilla.
Add to dry ingredients, stirring until moistened.
Grease or line muffin pans.
Spoon batter into muffin pans.
Fill batter almost level with top of bake-cups; bakes into nicely rounded muffins.
Bake in 375° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.
Watch carefully to prevent over-browning.
Remove from pans; cool on wire racks.
Makes about 24 muffins.
Contain 207 calories each.

title: cranberry-glazed pork roast
directions: In small saucepan, stir together all ingredients, except pork. Cook, stirring, over medium heat until thickened; set aside. Place roast in shallow baking dish.
Roast at 325° for 45 minutes. Spoon 1/2 cup glaze over roast; continue roasting for 45 minutes more, until internal temperature is 160°.
Let stand 10 minutes before slicing.
Serve with remaining sauce.
Makes 14 to 16 servings.

title: cordon bleu sauce
directions: Melt butter in saucepan over medium heat.
Blend in flour and salt.
Gradually add milk.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly, for 1 minute.
Reduce heat.
Add cream cheese and Swiss cheese. Stir until melted.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix the cream cheese, sour cream, Tabasco sauce, Worcestershire sauce and taco seasoning together.
Spread dip on platter.
Cover with salsa.
Add chopped onion, chopped lettuce, chopped tomatoes, shredded Cheddar cheese and black olives.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: creamy carrot soup
directions: Saute onion in butter a few minutes.
Add remaining ingredients and cook over medium heat until carrots are very soft (about 20 minutes).

title: artichoke dip
directions: Mix artichokes with mayonnaise and cheese.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes, or until browned on top.
Pour excess oil off before serving with corn chips.

title: baked apples
directions: Heat wine and juice until starts to boil.
Turn heat off.
Add raisins and cumin.
Stir and let stand 15 minutes.
Core apples. Score to within 1/2-inch of bottom.
Place apples in baking dish, not touching.
Stuff with juice soaked raisins.
Spoon remaining juice over apples.
Put water in dish 1/3-inch deep.
Cover with foil.
Bake 20 minutes.
Uncover and bake 20 minutes more.
Serve warm.

title: my mom's up and down biscuits
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Cut in shortening coarsely.
Add milk. Knead gently 1/2 minute.
Roll 1/4-inch thick.
Brush with margarine.
Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon.
Cut in 2-inch strips stack 5 high.
Cut off 2-inch pieces and place cut side down in greased muffin pans.
Bake 12 minutes at 425°.

title: mexican beef casserole
directions: In 2-quart casserole, crumble beef.
Add onion and pepper. Microwave at High 6 minutes, stirring after 3 minutes.
Drain well.
Drain tomatoes, reserving 1/4 cup juice.
Dice tomatoes and add to meat mixture with juice, corn, tomato sauce, olives and chili powder.
Cover.
Microwave at High 6 to 8 minutes until hot. Remove cover, stir and sprinkle corn chips and add cheese over top.
Microwave at High 2 minutes, uncovered, until cheese melts.

title: lime punch
directions: Mix and make Kool-Aid as directed; mix in pineapple juice. Stir together and freeze.
When ready to serve, place frozen mixture into punch bowl.
Pour ginger ale over it and chop up ice for a nice cold beverage.

title: peel deals
directions: Place roll on piece of aluminum foil (large enough to wrap for baking).
Spread mustard on roll; place slices of cheese and sliced hot dog.
Top hot dog with garnishes of choice: ketchup, relish and/or onions.
Then top with large quantity of pork and beans.
Wrap up and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients together; pour into ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: oreo cake
directions: First Layer:
Crush large portion of Oreo cookies and place in glass baking dish.
Melt margarine and pour over the Oreo cookies.

title: quick-easy meat loaf
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients, except ground beef; mix well.
Add ground beef; mix lightly but thoroughly. Press into an 8 x 4-inch loaf pan.
Bake 1 hour.
Drain.
Let stand for 5 minutes.

title: shrimp, lobster or crab mold
directions: Beat softened cheese until fluffy.
Soften gelatin in water and dissolve in hot soup.
Combine with cheese and beat in mixer until smooth.
Fold in other ingredients.
Pack into an oiled mold and chill.
Unmold to serve.
Serves 30.

title: curried tomatoes
directions: Saute onion with margarine in saucepan; add garlic, curry powder and cilantro.
If needed, add small amount of vegetable oil to prevent scorching.
Add tomatoes with all of the liquid and increase the heat to high.
Bring just to a boil and reduce heat to simmer.
Cover and simmer for 20 to 30 minutes.
Serve over rice or pasta.

title: low-fat macaroni and cheese
directions: Place macaroni in a baking dish and set aside.
Make sauce by adding flour, water, milk and Egg Beaters; mix until smooth.
Dice 2 slices cheese in sauce and flour over macaroni.
Place remainder of cheese on top and bake until firm.
Less than 1 gram fat per serving.
Serves 4.

title: baked beans
directions: Bake in covered baking dish, about 1 hour, at 375°.

title: seven layer nacho dip
directions: Decorate top with sliced black olives.
Could use these ingredients to decorate top, as well.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Mix by hand.
Bake at 325° until golden brown.
Test with toothpick.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Cut eggs in half lengthwise; remove yolks and place in mixing bowl.
Add cheese, pickle, onion, mayonnaise and mustard.
Mix well.
Place mixture in hollowed egg halves and garnish with paprika and parsley.
Keep chilled until ready to serve.

title: cinnamon swirl rounds(use with basic sweet dough)
directions: Mix well or with mixer brown sugar, sugar, butter, flour, cinnamon and nuts.
Roll out dough 10 x 30 x 1/4-inch rectangle. Spread sugar and cinnamon mixture evenly on dough.
Roll dough tightly from long side to form 30-inch roll.
Pinching seam together, cut into (21) 1 1/2-inch slices.
Place 7 rolls each in 3 greased 8 x 1 1/2-inch cake pans.
Cover, let rise in warm place, free from draft until doubled in bulk, about 1 hour.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes.
Remove from pans.
Spread on Caramel Glaze.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Shred the cabbage and cook until tender; drain.
Make white sauce.
Cook on low heat until thick.
In casserole dish, layer cabbage, cracker crumbs and sauce until all is used.
Top with grated cheese. Bake 25 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: homemade chalk
directions: You will also need a few 2-ounce paper cups.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken and debone.
Put in bottom of Pyrex dish.
Mix sour cream with soup.
Pour over chicken.
Crush crackers, melt butter and mix together.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: homemade salsa
directions: Peel, seed and cut tomatoes into small pieces.
Add remainder of ingredients.
Chill and serve with taco chips.
May be kept in refrigerator for 1 week.

title: ho ho cake
directions: Mix chocolate cake as package directions.
Bake in a large sheet cake pan 12-15 minutes.
Cool.
Beat together until smooth the vanilla, butter, Crisco, sugar, and evaporated milk.
Spread on cooled cake.
Heat one can chocolate frosting in microwave until melted.
Power over cake and filling.

title: wild rice baron
directions: Gently cook wild rice, water and salt for 45 minutes.
Drain. Brown ground beef and set aside.
Rinse mushrooms and cut off tips of stems.
Slice.
Saute mushrooms, onions and celery in butter for 5 to 10 minutes.
Combine soy sauce, sour cream, salt and pepper. Add cooked wild rice, browned hamburger, mushrooms, onion, and celery mixture and almonds.
Toss gently.
Place rice mixture in slightly buttered 3-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour uncovered.
Stir several times.
Garnish with almonds.

title: fettuccine with peas(serves 4)
directions: Heat butter with onion in saucepan.
Mix in flour and cook 2 minutes over low heat, stirring once.
Pour in half of milk; whisk well and add remaining milk, along with seasonings.
Cook sauce 10 minutes over low heat.
Stir at least 2 to 3 times.
Add pasta and peas to sauce; stir and cook 2 to 3 minutes more.
Correct seasoning and garnish portions with bacon and cheese.
(Mmm!)

title: chocolate sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter; gradually add sugar, beating well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Combine flour, cocoa, soda and salt; add to creamed mixture alternately with sour cream, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Mix well after each addition.
Add boiling water, and mix well.
Stir in vanilla.

title: peach muffins
directions: Beat eggs and milk together.
Add shortening, sugar, salt, vanilla and lemon juice.
Sift cinnamon, flour and baking powder. Fold in egg mixture until smooth.
Fold in peaches.
Fill greased muffin cups 2/3 full.
Bake in 450° oven for 15 minutes.

title: mounds candy
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except for the almond bark. Roll into small logs on wax paper, wrap and refrigerate overnight. Slice and dip into the almond bark.
(Can be frozen.)

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken until tender; cut in bite size pieces.
Mix together with chicken soup, celery soup, milk and chicken.
Set aside.
Mix dressing mix, broth and butter.
Put 1/3 of dressing mix in bottom of casserole dish.
Put chicken mixture next, then rest of dressing mixture on top.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
May be prepared ahead of time and also may be frozen.

title: walk to school cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Roll in rolls about 2 inches in diameter and roll up in wax paper.
Will make about 4 to 5 rolls. Refrigerate.
Slice in 1/4-inch thick slices.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 10 to 12 minutes only until light brown.
Do not bake beyond this light brown color.

title: candy cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix sugars, butter, shortening, vanilla and egg.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Drop dough by heaping teaspoonfuls, about 2 inches apart, onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake until light brown, 8 to 10 minutes.
Remove from cookie sheet.
Makes about 3 dozen cookies.

title: nacho pie
directions: Brown beef and add garlic powder, nacho sauce mix and tomato sauce.
Place nacho chips on cookie sheet or baking pan and heat in oven 5 minutes at 400°.
Place 12 to 15 chips on plate.
Top with hamburger mixture.
Sprinkle tomatoes, shredded lettuce and onion on top.
Top with squeeze cheese and jalapeno peppers. Makes 8 servings.

title: zucchini beef casserole
directions: Arrange zucchini in greased 2-quart casserole dish.
Fold in onion and green pepper.
Season with salt and pepper.
Cover with crumbs.
Pour undiluted soup over all.
Sprinkle with cheese. Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Brown ground beef in skillet, stirring until crumbly.
Season with salt and pepper.
Sprinkle over baked casserole.
Bake 25 minutes longer.

title: bubble buns
directions: Cut biscuits in quarters. Roll biscuit pieces in mayonnaise, then roll in nut mixture. Put 4 biscuit pieces in each muffin hole. Bake at 400° for 10 to 18 minutes.

title: no-fat barbecue sauce
directions: Boil tomato juice until it is reduced to 2/3.
Add rest of ingredients and simmer about 5 minutes.

title: apricot nectar cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into greased pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pineapple delight
directions: Mix pineapple and pudding together; fold in Cool Whip. Refrigerate.

title: spanish rice casserole
directions: Brown hamburger.
Add onion, salt and pepper.
Cook slowly until onion is soft and yellow.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: spinach balls
directions: Drain
spinach;
squeeze
out
liquid.	Combine spinach with ingredients.
Form into balls on a baking sheet.
Freeze. Put into bags.
Bake
at
350° for 15 minutes, until firm and lightly browned.
Makes 5 to 6 dozen.

title: spoon bread
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Beat egg whites until stiff peaks are formed.
Into a large mixing bowl, put the corn meal and slowly add the boiling water, stirring continuously.
Add butter, egg yolks and milk and stir or beat well.
Fold egg whites into batter and pour into an 8 or 9-inch cake pan.
Bake for 40 minutes at 400° or until done.
As the bread will be very soft, it is traditionally served using a spoon.

title: low calorie chicken oriental
directions: Place chicken pieces skin side up in a shallow baking dish and surround with pineapple chunks.
Mix juices with vinegar, soy sauce, mustard, salt and pepper and pour over chicken.
Bake, uncovered, in moderate oven at 350° for 40 minutes, basting occasionally.
Add pepper strips.
Combine cornstarch and water in a cup.
Stir into liquid in baking dish and bake an additional 15 minutes.

title: taffy tan fudge
directions: Combine sugar and milk.
Cook to soft ball stage, stirring frequently.
Stir in marshmallow cream, peanut butter and vanilla. Beat until mixture is blended and begins to thicken.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: grandma ruth's cherry delight
directions: Crush graham crackers.
Add 2 tablespoons powdered sugar and melted margarine.
Mix and press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool in freezer to help set.
Mix the Philly cream cheese and remaining powdered sugar.
Fold in Cool Whip; spread over crust.
Add the cherry pie filling over top.

title: sticky ribs
directions: Put
ribs
into
baking pan.
Combine sauce ingredients well; pour over ribs.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: italian spaghetti
directions: In a large skillet, cook onions until almost tender. Add the ground beef and garlic and brown lightly. Add sliced mushrooms. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Simmer, uncovered, for 2 to 2 1/2 hours or until thick.
Remove bay leaves.
Serve over spaghetti.

title: christmas or wedding punch
directions: Mix
Kool-Aid, pineapple juice, sugar, water and lemonade and chill.
Then add ginger ale and strawberry pop.
Makes 50 four ounce servings.

title: apple kuchen
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, mix butter, 1/2 cup sugar, flour, baking powder, vanilla and egg.
Pour half into a greased 8-inch square baking pan.
In another bowl, toss apples with remaining sugar and cinnamon.
Place on top of batter in pan. Pour in remaining batter.
Bake 50 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: smoked sausage casserole
directions: Melt margarine in a large saucepan, over medium heat.
Add cabbage, onion and carrots; saute 5 minutes.
Stir in beans, tomatoes and vinegar.
Sprinkle cheese, flour and pepper over cabbage mixture and mix.
Spoon into greased 2-quart casserole. Cut sausage into bite size slices and arrange on top of cabbage. Cover and bake 40 minutes.

title: el wifeo's lasagna mexicano
directions: Brown beef in frying pan and prepare per package instructions on taco seasoning mix. Line bottom of an oiled 9 x 13 casserole dish with 6 overlapping corn tortillas. Spread 1/2 taco mix over tortillas, 1/2 of onions and tomatoes and 1/2 of cheese. Cover with remaining tortillas and repeat process for second layer. Spread jar of taco sauce. Cover with foil. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Remove foil. Bake 5 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all this together and form ball.

title: crescent pizza pie
directions: Buy a big crust, get ham, black olives, pepperoni, sauce, cheese, mushrooms and any other toppings you want.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Saute meat with chopped regular onions, bell peppers, jalapeno peppers, garlic, chili powder, salt and pepper.
Put small amount of oil in 2 sheet pans and put layer of cornbread, layer of meat and layer of cheese on top with another layer of cornbread.
Bake in a 450° oven for 45 minutes.

title: dill pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers; cut in 1/2-inch lengthwise.
Combine salt, vinegar and water.
Heat to boiling.
Pack cucumbers in clean jars.
Add 2 sprigs dill weed and 4 peppercorns to each jar.
Pour boiling vinegar over cucumbers to 1/2-inch of top of jar.
Seal. Process 10 minutes in boiling water bath.
Makes 6 to 7 pints.

title: chicken crescent rolls
directions: Mix ingredients, except rolls and margarine.
Separate rolls individually and flatten.
Spoon 1/2 cup chicken into rolls and pull together.
Brush tops with melted margarine.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serves 32.
Good for a party!

title: beet salad
directions: Mix sour cream, mustard and vinegar.
Pour over beets and stir until well coated.
Chill.

title: cole slaw dressing
directions: Fold together gently.
Do not beat.
Makes enough for two medium heads of cabbage.

title: vegetarian chicken pot pie
directions: Prepare a 9-inch pie crust.
Set aside.
Combine all ingredients and simmer for about 5 minutes.
Put into pie shell. Cover with another crust.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until brown.
Spread butter over baked crust.

title: 5 cup salad
directions: Mix altogether and refrigerate overnight.

title: oatmeal chocolate chip crisp cookies
directions: Cream together margarine and sugars; add egg, vanilla and oil. Sift together flour, baking soda and salt.
Add sifted ingredients to sugar mixture, blending well.
Stir in Rice Krispies, oats and chocolate chips.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto greased baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes. Cool.
Store in tightly covered container.
Makes about 6 dozen. Can be frozen.

title: pizza tortillas
directions: *Or use your favorite toppings.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Boil shrimp in crab boil.
Cook macaroni and chill.
Cut up eggs, lettuce, tomatoes, celery and pepper.
Mix shrimp, macaroni, eggs, lettuce, tomatoes, celery, pepper and peas.
Season with celery seed, parsley and seasoning salt.
Mix salad dressing with mixture.

title: feathered rolls
directions: Melt margarine in warm milk.
Add sugar, salt and beaten eggs. Sprinkle yeast over mixture and stir well. Add flour gradually. Mix well.

title: coconut macaroons(no sugar)
directions: Mix ingredients; roll dough into small balls.
Bake at 275° until lightly browned (about 15 minutes).

title: meal in a dish
directions: Cook noodles according to directions on package. Cook frozen vegetables according to the directions. Brown ground beef and drain. Mix all the ingredients, except the cheese. Place in a casserole dish and sprinkle cheese on the top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: best gingerbread ever
directions: Stir together flour, baking powder, ginger, cinnamon and salt; set aside.
In a mixing bowl, beat remaining ingredients until well blended.
Stir in flour mixture for about 25 strokes just until moistened.
Turn into well greased 8-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cool on a rack 10 to 15 minutes.
Serve warm with whipped cream or lemon curd.

title: tuna fish pie
directions: Melt butter.
Add pepper and onions and cook until soft.
Add flour, stir until well blended.
Add salt.
Add milk slowly, stirring until smooth.
Boil 2 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients. Pour in large baking dish and cover with cheese rolls.
Serves 8.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Mix pecans and coconut together and spread evenly in the bottom of a well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan.

Mix cake according to package instructions. Spread over the coconut and pecan mixture. Mix confectioners sugar, cream cheese and margarine until smooth. Spread over cake mix, leaving about 1-inch from sides of pan. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: mexican salad
directions: Prepare lettuce as for any tossed salad.
Drain and wash chilled beans and add to lettuce.
Add diced tomatoes, onions, cheese and dressing.
Chill 30 minutes to 1 hour before serving. Add Fritos immediately before serving, mixing well.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli.
While broccoli is cooking, mix all other ingredients together in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Add broccoli and bake at 375° for 35 minutes.

title: 7-up pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter together; beat until light and fluffy. Add eggs one at a time, beating well.
Add flour.
Add lemon extract and 7-Up.
Pour batter into a well-greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 to 1 1/4 hours.

title: four layer casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Place beans into a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Top with slices of meat.
Mix soup, mayonnaise and mustard. Pour over ham and beans.
Top with cheese.
Toss bread crumbs in melted butter.
Sprinkle over cheese.
Bake, uncovered, for 30 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: low-fat holiday delight cheesecake(12 servings)
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine graham cracker crumbs, 2 tablespoons sugar and oleo.
Pat into bottom of 9 to 10-inch spring-form pan.
Set aside.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Cook shrimp for 5 minutes in boiling water. Drain. Peel and devein. In large bowl mix all ingredients together and chill. Serve with your favorite meal.

title: bisquick rolls
directions: Mix together all
ingredients.
Grease muffin pan.
Bake at 400° approximately 20 minutes.
Makes 12 rolls.

title: cheese cake
directions: Stir margarine and crushed cookies to make crust.
Blend and cream first 3 ingredients; put into crust and bake at 350° for 55 minutes.
Take out of oven and cool.
Top with canned pie filling (cherries or strawberries); put in refrigerator until cool.

title: yorkshire pudding
directions: Sift dry ingredients twice.
Break egg into dry ingredients, combine milk and water and add a little at a time to dry ingredients.
Beat smoothly until like thick cream.
Let stand 1 hour.
Put a dessert spoon of fat into a 9-inch square pan.
Heat fat in pan until hot at 450°.
Pour mixture into hot fat and bake for 20 minutes.
Serve immediately.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Place rice in bottom of large pan.
Mix soups and water; pour over rice.
Roll chicken in butter and place on top of other mixture.
Cook, covered, for 3 hours at 300°.

title: mince pie
directions: May substitute some of water with 2 tablespoons brandy and 3 tablespoons orange juice.

title: apricot baby food cake
directions: Combine oil and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Fold in all ingredients, except flour and nuts.
When well mixed, fold in flour and nuts.
Bake in well-greased and floured tube or Bundt pan for 1 hour in a 350° oven.

title: cheesy mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Steam mixed vegetables, celery and onions a few minutes, in microwave on High or in saucepan.
Veggies should still be crisp. Pour into a greased 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Top with crushed cheese crackers and margarine.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pineapple bread pudding
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Beat eggs in mixer until fluffy.
Cream butter and sugar.
Beat until real creamy.
Add vanilla.
Do not use the mixer now.
Fold in pineapple; fold in bread crumbs. Grease your dish; pour in batter.
Bake 40 minutes uncovered.

title: ham and cheese rolls
directions: Slice rolls in half in order to make top and bottom for sandwiches.
Melt butter in double boiler.
Add dry mustard, minced onion, poppy seed and Worcestershire sauce to make sauce. Put cheese and ham on bottom half of rolls.
Place top on ham and cheese and punch holes in the top.
Pour sauce over rolls and heat for 15 minutes at 350°.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Wash and peel potatoes.
Slice layer of potatoes in medium casserole dish.
Add layer of sliced onion. Add portion of margarine and salt and pepper.
Then make additional layer of potatoes and onion with margarine, salt and pepper.
Pour mushroom soup over top.
Add water.
Cover with Reynolds Wrap and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 6.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Cream sugar and margarine together and beat until light and fluffy. Add eggs one at a time and beat well. Add flour slowly and beat well. Beat in lemon extract and 7-Up into batter. Pour into well-greased and floured jumbo fluted pan. Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: carrot salad
directions: Place carrot mixture in colander or large strainer.
Add celery and raisins.
Mix together and let stand 30 minutes.
Sti rin mayonnaise and mix well.
Let stand in strainer over sink 15 to 20 minutes so extra mayonnaise can drain.
Serve in scoops on leaves of lettuce.
Refrigerate to store.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: mayonnaise cake
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, baking soda and cocoa.
Add mayonnaise, water and vanilla.
Mix all ingredients thoroughly. Bake in 2 greased layer pans or in a 2-quart baking dish at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until done.
May be served warm topped with ice cream or iced with favorite frosting.

title: orange chicken
directions: In a large non-stick skillet over medium-high heat, heat oil. Add chicken and brown.
Remove from skillet.
Add red pepper, green onion and garlic.
Cook, stirring occasionally, 5 minutes or until tender.
Return chicken to skillet.
Add orange juice, mustard, salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer about 20 minutes.
Transfer chicken to serving platter. Keep warm.
Add cornstarch mixture to skillet.

title: chicken stuffed with potatoes
directions: Mix together all of the ingredients.
Stuff chicken.
Bake at 375° for about 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: quiche
directions: Place pie crust in a 9 inch pan or a quiche dish. In a large bowl combine ingredients and pour into unbaked pie crust. Bake in a 350 degree oven for 35 to 40 minutes. After baking let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: easy chocolate cake(microwave)
directions: In casserole dish, make one 3 ounce package cooked chocolate pudding in microwave.
When cooked, stir in one package inexpensive generic chocolate cake mix.
Pour into greased and floured large baking pan.
Top with one small package chocolate chips and nuts.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes or until done.

title: mushroom meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Pack into a greased loaf pan. Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Drain off excess juices and turn meat loaf onto a serving plate.
Serve with mushroom sauce made from remaining 1/2 can of soup.
Thin with milk and heat.

title: onion blossom
directions: Peel onion, leaving root end intact.
Cut onion vertically into quarters.
Cut to 1/2-inch of root end.
Cut quarters vertically into thirds.
Place onion in boiling water 1 minute.
Remove and place in ice water for 5 minutes.
Loosen petals if necessary. Drain onion, cut side down.
Place flour in zipper plastic bag and onion and shake again.
Chill 1 hour.
Deep fry in 3 inches of oil until golden brown.
Drain well on paper towels.
Serve with Ranch style dressing, honey mustard or your choice.

title: venison enchiladas
directions: Place venison and onions in skillet and saute in oil until meat is browned and onion cooked through.
Stir in olives and salt and pepper to taste.
Heat enchilada sauce in large round pan.
Dip tortillas in sauce; remove immediately and place on flat surface and spread 1 tablespoon meat mixture over.
Roll and place in 9 x 14-inch baking dish.
Top with cheese and green onions.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 12.

title: scalloped tomatoes
directions: Cook celery, onion and green pepper until tender.
(Cook in saucepan.)
Add tomatoes.
Place in square casserole and cover with 1-inch square buttered bread with crusts removed (bread has been toasted).
Bake in 400° oven until delicately brown.

title: sour cream cake
directions: Cream together butter and sugar real good.
Add and beat in eggs, one at a time.
Add and beat in flour.
Add and beat in sour cream and vanilla flavoring.
Add and beat in flour mixture.
Beat well.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: fresh apple muffins
directions: Cook and cool apples before using.
Preheat oven to 400° (380° convection).
Put flour and salt in large bowl.
Cut in butter. Stir in sugar and cooled apples.
Whisk egg and milk together and stir into flour mixture.
Use muffin pan (12) pregreased, or may be dropped onto a cookie sheet.
Bake 20 minutes.

title: pizza crust
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water, sugar, salt and oil.
Mix in flour. Beat 60 strokes and turn out on floured board.
Knead.
Let rest 5 minutes. Dough is ready to spread into pizza pan.

title: hershey bar cake
directions: Melt Hershey bars in top of double boiler.
Cream butter and sugar, add Hershey bars, Hershey syrup and eggs, beat well.

Mix well, all dry ingredients add to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk, beating well, add vanilla and 1 cup nuts if desired. Pour into 2 (9 x 13-inch) pans, greased lightly and bake 30 minutes or until inserted wooden toothpick comes out clean, at 350°.
You can bake this in tube pan, bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
In large bowl, beat 1 1/2 cups sugar and margarine until light and fluffy.
Add vanilla and eggs; blend well.
Lightly spoon flour into measuring cup; level off.
Stir in flour, cream of tartar, baking soda and salt; mix well.

title: zucchini appetizers
directions: Mix all together.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix together and pour into a greased baking dish. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes until a knife comes out clean.
Can be put in a long pan.
Bakes more quickly.

title: baked ham glaze
directions: Pour over ham the last 25 minutes of baking.

title: big mac pancakes
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Add eggs and buttermilk.
Mix all together.
Add enough water to a pouring consistency.

title: hamburger soup
directions: Cook hamburger with onion until well done.
Add tomatoes, soup, water, seasonings and potatoes.
Cook 35 minutes.
May substitute 3/4 cup of macaroni for potatoes.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mash potatoes and combine with other ingredients in a 2-quart casserole.

title: no fail pie crust
directions: Mix flour and salt.
Add shortening and mix well.
Mix egg, vinegar and water and add all at once to flour mixture.
Round up and roll out.

title: essie's fruit cobbler
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt; add to creamed mixture, alternately with milk.
Beat until smooth.
Pour into a greased loaf pan.
Spoon drained fruit over batter. Sprinkle with sugar and juice.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream or ice cream.
Serves 6.

title: corey's peanut butter roll
directions: Mix sugar, cream cheese and milk together.
Roll out on wax paper in a rectangular shape.
Spread with peanut butter.
Roll up and chill in the waxed paper for several hours.
Slice.

title: blue cheese dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients well. If thick, thin with milk.

title: dump cake
directions: Spread pineapple on bottom of cake pan.
Then put the can of cherry pie filling on.
Next layer is the dry cake mix.
Next slice butter on top of cake mix.
Then spread nuts.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: mrs. sprouse's pineapple pound cake
directions: Cream butter or margarine, Crisco and sugar. Add eggs, one at a time. Add flour and milk alternately. Add flavoring, baking powder and pineapple. Bake in greased and floured pan in cold oven at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: hot pepper relish
directions: Grind peppers in food processor.
Mix peppers and remaining ingredients together and boil for 20 minutes.
Put in pint jars and seal.

title: marshmallow fudge
directions: Combine Milnot and sugar in heavy saucepan (4-quart).
Add marshmallows and butter and cook over low heat until melted. (Heat may be turned to medium.)
Bring mixture to full boil and stir 4 minutes.
Blend vanilla and nuts.
Pour into lightly buttered pan (9 x 13 x 2-inch).
Allow to cool.
Candy may be refrigerated or frozen once it is firm.
Makes 5 pounds.

title: cream chicken enchiladas
directions: Stir chicken, green peppers, cream cheese and 1/2 cup salsa into a saucepan on low heat until cream cheese is melted. Spoon 1/3 cup of the chicken mixture onto each tortilla and roll up. Place seam side down, in a greased 12 x 8 baking dish.

title: chili rellenos bake
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Drain.
Sprinkle meat with salt and pepper.
Halve chiles and remove seeds.
Place half of the chiles in a 10 x 6 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish; sprinkle with cheese and top with meat mixture.
Arrange remaining chiles over meat. Blend eggs, milk, flour, salt and Tabasco; beat until smooth. Pour over chiles.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes, until knife inserted comes out clean.

title: breakfast wellington
directions: Cook sausage in medium skillet; drain well.
Add broccoli, cheese, onion, sour cream and pepper.
Mix well.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Separate dough into 4 long rectangles on ungreased cookie sheet.
Overlap long sides of rectangles.
Spoon meat mixture down center of rectangle.
Fold strips over filling.
Mix egg with 1 tablespoon of water; brush over dough.
Sprinkle with sesame seed.
Bake at 375° for 18 to 22 minutes, until deep golden brown.

title: biscuits
directions: Roll out thick (1/2 inch).
Bake at 400° for 11 minutes or until golden brown.
Brush butter on top of biscuits before baking.
Yields 15 biscuits.

title: beef dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill 2 hours.

title: apple crisp
directions: Core and slice apples.
Place in a buttered baking dish and sprinkle with the mixed white sugar and cinnamon.
Add water. Blend the flour, brown sugar and butter together until crumbly. Sprinkle over the top of the apples.
Bake at 350° until brown, about 50 minutes.

title: chocolate and oat bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350° (325° for glass dish).
In bowl combine flour, oats, sugar and butter.
Mix well.
Reserving 1/2 cup, press remaining oat mixture on bottom of 13 x 9-inch baking pan. Bake 10 minutes.
Pour sweetened milk evenly over crust.
Sprinkle with nuts and morsels.
Top with remaining oat mixture; press down.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool. Store covered at room temperature.

title: tomato bread
directions: Heat V-8, tomato sauce and oil to 120°.
In large bowl, combine 3 cups of flour with dry yeast, sugar, salt and herbs. Add warmed tomato mixture and garlic.
Mix for 3 minutes, scraping sides of bowl frequently.
Add 3 to 3 1/2 cups flour and turn out onto well floured board.
Continue adding flour, small amounts
at a time so dough is not sticky and knead well.
Place in greased bowl and turn greased side up.
Cover and let rise in warm place until doubled, about 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Punch down and let rest 15 minutes.
Shape into two loaves; place in greased bread pans and cover loosely.

title: pork chops with beer
directions: Combine flour, salt and pepper in a plastic bag.
Add chops and shake to coat.
Brown chops on both sides in oil in a large skillet.
Remove and keep warm.
Drain off fat from skillet, leaving brown bits in bottom.
Add beer, broth, garlic, caraway seed and mustard.
Bring to boiling, stirring and scraping to loosen brown bits.
Lower heat, simmer until pan liquid is reduced to 1 cup.
Return chops to skillet.
Bring to boiling.
Cover and lower heat.
Simmer, turning once, about 45 minutes, until chops are tender.
Serve chops with pan liquid spooned over.

title: fried rabbit
directions: Beat eggs, milk and salt and blend with flour to make a smooth batter.
Wipe the rabbit with clean, damp cloth and cut into pieces of the right size for serving.
Dip each piece of rabbit into this batter and be sure it's thoroughly coated.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Roll out pie dough.
Cut dough to fit each apple.
Put 1 tablespoon sugar in center of each apple, along with a dot of margarine and cinnamon.
Wrap apple in pie dough.
Place in pan big enough to hold 6 apples.
Combine water, margarine and sugar in saucepan.
Heat until sugar is dissolved.
Pour syrup over apples and bake at 425° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: ground beef and macaroni casserole
directions: Heat oil in skillet.
Add onion and green pepper; cook until tender.
Add beef.
Brown, stirring often.
Pour out and save 1/8 cup liquid from tomatoes.
Add rest of tomatoes, syrup, salt, pepper, chili powder and bay leaf to meat mixture.
Bring to boil, cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Blend cornstarch with tomato juice. Stir into meat mixture.
Bring to a boil.
Add cooked macaroni. Pour into casserole dish.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into greased casserole dish.
Top with cheddar cheese if desired.
Bake at 350 degrees for approximately 45 minutes.
Makes one large or two small casseroles.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Bring oleo, cocoa and water to a boil.
Pour into sugar, salt and flour mixture.
Mix well the eggs, sour cream, vanilla and baking soda.
Pour into flour mixture and beat.
Bake 20 minutes at 400°.
Use cookie sheet, greased.

title: portuguese bean soup
directions: In
large
pot,
boil
Portuguese
sausage in water and tomato sauce.
Dice
carrot, celery and potatoes; add to pot. Add kidney
beans
and	string beans; bring to boil.
Boil on medium heat until vegetables are tender.
Add cabbage.
Cover and simmer for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: beef-garden casserole
directions: Cook onion in small amount of fat until tender, not brown. Add beef and seasoning; brown lightly.
Add green beans, corn and soup.
Pour into a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Top with Cheese Spins.

title: fried rabbit smothered in brown sauce
directions: Cut the rabbits like you would a chicken; wash.
Dip rabbit in salt, pepper and flour.
Fry in skillet until brown on all sides. When well browned on both sides, put the rabbit in a baking dish. Add 1 can of cream of mushroom soup; cook in oven at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serve with rice.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: microwave cheesy cabbage
directions: In
quart
casserole,
combine
cabbage, salt, milk, onion, butter
and nutmeg.
Cook, covered, 6 minutes or until almost tender, stirring once.
Stir in cheese and let stand 2 minutes before serving.
Serves four.

title: pickled shrimp
directions: Cover shrimp with boiling water; add celery tops, spices and salt.
Cover and simmer 5 to 7 minutes.
Drain, cool with cold water.
Peel and devein under cold water.

title: cheddar quick bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients; cut in butter until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Stir in cheese.
Add combined milk and egg; mix just until moistened.
Spoon into greased and floured 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes; remove from pan.

title: raisin cookies
directions: Put raisins in water, boil 1 minute, & cool.
Mix sugar, crisco, then put in the eggs.
Mix flour, soda, baking powder, salt, cinnamon, nutmeg and nuts separate & put the juice from raisins in your sugar mixture.
Then put your raisins in with your flour & nut mix and put in with your sugar, crisco & egg mixture. Drop by tsp. & bake & frost.

title: mom's cheese ball
directions: Blend cheeses.
Mix in package of Ranch Valley dressing.
Line a cookie sheet with Saran Wrap.
Cover (smear) cookie sheet with mixture.
Refrigerate for about 1 hour.
Sprinkle ham (and parsley) over cold mixture.
Roll up mixture pulling Saran Wrap away.
Shape into ball.
Press chopped nuts all over the ball. Put cherry on top.
Serve with crackers.

title: hawaiian stack-ups
directions: Brown meat and add soup.
Layer on your plate: Chinese noodles, cooked rice, meat mixture, cheese, pineapple and coconut.

title: dutch onion and green bean casserole
directions: Melt butter. Stir in flour and blend.
Add seasonings.
Drain and measure bean liquid, adding milk to make 1 1/4 cups. Add to flour mixture. Cook until thickened, stirring constantly. Add vegetables.
Pour into 1-quart greased casserole.
Border with buttered bread cubes.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until cubes are crisp and brown.

title: christmas candy wreath
directions: Cut coat hanger in center of wire base and then bring ends together.
Shape into approximately 10-inch circle; wire ends together with fine wire.
Cover circle by winding the 2-inch material using the entire 5 yards to form the base.
Then, wrap the foil around the material.
The fine wire for putting candy on the wreath should be in about 4 foot lengths or whatever length is convenient to work with.
When the preferred length is used, make a loop on the end by bending the end back and then twisting.
Place next wire through loop; bend end over and twist, thereby fastening ends.

title: applesauce puffs
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.

Grease small muffin pans lightly. Combine Bisquick, sugar and cinnamon together in a large bowl. Add applesauce, milk, egg and oil. Beat vigorously 2 minutes by hand. Fill pans 2/3 full. Bake at 400° for 12 minutes. When slightly cooled, brush tops with melted margarine and sprinkle with mixture of cinnamon and sugar.

title: roquefort cheesecake
directions: Preheat the oven to 325°.
Butter a 9-inch spring-form pan. In a small bowl, combine the bread crumbs and the Parmesan cheese. Sprinkle the mixture over the bottom and sides of the pan, turning to coat.
Refrigerate until set, at least 30 minutes.
Fry the bacon in a skillet until it is crisp; drain on paper toweling. Pour off all but about 1 tablespoon of the bacon fat (leaving 1 tablespoon in the pan).
Add the onion; cover and cook over low heat until the onion is translucent, about 10 minutes.

title: spaghetti glamerama
directions: Cook spaghetti with 1 teaspoon salt for 5 minutes.
Saute chopped onion and pepper; brown meat.
Stir in tomatoes, garlic salt, oregano and tomato paste.
Cook until well blended.

Soften cheeses; add sour cream and grated onion and stir until blended. In a 2-quart casserole dish, put one thin layer of spaghetti; layer 1/2 of sauce mix, all of cream mixture next, and (cheeses), spaghetti layer and sauce on top.
Bake, covered, in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: hot chocolate sauce
directions: Combine cocoa, sugar, salt, syrup and cold milk in saucepan. Place over low heat; stir until sugar is dissolved.
Cook, without stirring, until a jellied mass is formed when small amount is dropped in cold water.
Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla and margarine.

title: old fashioned pumpkin pie
directions: Combine eggs, brown sugar, spice and salt, mixing thoroughly. Add milk and evaporated milk; stir well.
Line a 9-inch pie pan with plain pastry; fill with pumpkin mixture.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes, then reduce heat to 325° for 35 minutes.

title: chicken delight
directions: Mix soup, mayonnaise and lemon juice.
Place frozen broccoli in baking dish.
Add chicken pieces, soup mixture and cheese.
Top with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: peach melba dessert
directions: Dissolve peach flavored gelatin in 1 cup of boiling water.
Add cold water.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Dissolve Raspberry flavor gelatine in remaining 1 cup boiling water.
Spoon in ice cream, stirring until melted and smooth.
Pour into serving bowl. Chill until set but not firm.
Arrange peach slices and raspberries on ice cream mixture in bowl.
Add mint leaves, if desired.
Spoon peach gelatine over fruit.
Chill about 3 hours.

title: deviled crab
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a small saucepan, melt butter; toss with bread crumbs and set aside.
Combine soup, crab meat, green peppers, onions, lemon juice and mustard.
Pour into 1-quart casserole.
Top with reserved crumbs.
Bake for 25 minutes. Makes 4 servings.

title: easy party punch
directions: Dissolve sugar in one quart hot water, then add one quart cold water.
Add kool-aid and juice to water and sugar.	Add ginger ale immediately before serving.
Yields 5 quarts.

title: banana cupcakes
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
In mixing bowl cream oleo and sugar, then add egg and vanilla.
Then add sour milk and mashed banana.
Add nuts with flour mixture.
Mix well.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Makes 1 dozen cupcakes.

title: angelic strawberry dessert
directions: In mixer bowl, mix pudding, sour cream, milk and orange peel until well mixed.
Fold in whipped cream.
In large clear serving or trifle bowl, layer cake pieces (1/2), strawberries (1/3) and pudding mixture (1/2).
Repeat layers.
Arrange remaining strawberries on top.
Chill 2 hours.

title: broccoli and mushrooms in sour cream sauce
directions: Cook broccoli until bright green.
Saute mushrooms in butter. Combine all ingredients and heat over low.
(Do not boil.)

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Brown beef and onion; drain grease.
Add tomato sauce and chili powder.
Heat thoroughly.
In saucepan, heat soup and milk together.

title: eggs with asparagus and chicken
directions: In a pan over medium heat, melt the 2 tablespoons butter. Stir in flour, salt, pepper, nutmeg and mustard; cook until bubbly.
Gradually stir in milk; cook, stirring constantly, until thick and smooth.
Stir in cheese until it is melted and the sauce is smooth.
Stir in asparagus pieces and chicken; remove from heat.

title: rice and chicken casserole
directions: Melt butter.
Add onion; saute until clear.
Add broccoli; stir thoroughly.
Add soup; simmer on low to heat.
Add cooked rice and cheese; stir.
Put in casserole dish.
Bake at 300° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Cool until bubbly.

title: kolbassi barbecue
directions: Cut kolbassi into 2-inch pieces and arrange in baking dish. Mix the jelly and chili sauce together and pour over kolbassi. Bake in 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours.

title: broiled marinated fish steaks
directions: In a shallow pan, combine oil, vinegar, Worcestershire sauce, pepper, bay leaf and parsley.
Add fish steaks; cover and refrigerate for at least 3 hours, turning occasionally so that the steaks are well coated.
Remove from marinade.
Place on a foil covered broiler pan.
Baste with marinade.
Place broiler pan about 3 inches from heat.
Broil about 10 minutes or until fish flakes easily when tested with a fork.
Baste with sauce.
Yield: 6 servings.
Approximate calories/serving:

title: harvard beets
directions: Mix all ingredients (except beets) in saucepan and boil for 5 minutes.
Add drained beets and heat through. Add butter and serve hot.

title: peanut butter crinkles
directions: Beat in bowl with mixer at medium speed until fluffy.
At low speed add 2 1/2 cups unsifted flour.
Shape mixture into 1-inch balls.
Roll in granulated sugar.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake in 350° oven for 12 to 15 minutes or until browned.
Immediately press nuts or chocolate kisses into cookies.
Cool.
Store in airtight container.
Addictive!

title: german beef supper
directions: Brown meat in hot Crisco.
Add apple, carrot, onion, 1/2 cup water, wine, salt, garlic, bouillon cubes, bay leaf and thyme. Cover and simmer for 2 hours or until beef is tender.
Remove bay leaf.
Combine cornstarch and the cold water; add to beef mixture. Cook and stir until thickened.
Stir in Kitchen Bouquet.
Serve over

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook sugar and milk to soft ball stage, about 5 minutes on medium.
Remove from heat.
Add Marshmallow Creme, peanut butter and vanilla.
Stir until smooth.
Pour into greased pan and cut into squares.

title: greek chicken salad
directions: Cut the chicken into 1/2 to 3/4 inch pieces.
Core and seed the tomatoes, then cut into 1/2-inch dice.
In a medium mixing bowl, toss together the chicken, tomatoes, Feta cheese and vinaigrette. To serve, separate the romaine lettuce into leaves.
Arrange 2 or 3 leaves on each plate.
Spoon the chicken salad onto the lettuce.

title: vegen-energy rice
directions: Cook rice as directed.
Saute all ingredients and add!!! Try summer squash, etc.
Add soy sauce and cook for 10 minutes.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown ground beef.
Boil eggs and peel.
Then cut eggs into small pieces.
Cook corn and drain.
(If using kidney beans, cook and drain also.)
Crush taco shells.
Shred lettuce or cut into small pieces.
Then mix all ingredients together and add cheese and salad dressing.

title: beef 'n potato casserole
directions: Cover the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch buttered dish with potatoes; bring up along sides.
Bake, uncovered, at 400° for 10 minutes. Drain beef and place on potatoes, then broccoli and 1/2 of onions.

title: crescent rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water, then add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Let mixture stand, covered, in refrigerator overnight.
Divide dough in half; roll each half at a time into 20-inch circle.
Spread 1/4 cup melted butter or margarine over dough.
Cut into 16 wedges as though cutting pie.
Roll dough pieces, starting with large end.
Place in lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Repeat for second half of dough.
Let stand 2 to 4 hours to rise.
Bake when doubled in size in 425° oven 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 32 rolls.

title: grilled chicken and sausage
directions: Wash chicken and sausage.
Cut up sausage in 1 1/2-inch chunks. Arrange chicken and sausage in pan and lightly salt and pepper. Pour salad dressing over top and turn to coat.
Let marinate at least 4 hours (this is better if left to marinate at least 12 hours).
Grill over medium-high heat until done.

title: hot mustard
directions: Mix dry mustard and vinegar together and set overnight.
In morning, whip the egg whites and sugar in mustard mixture.
Put in top of double boiler and cook until thick, stirring occasionally. Put in glass and store in refrigerator.
Keeps indefinitely. Excellent over cream cheese, served with Ritz or Town House crackers for a tea.

title: jello delight
directions: Mix all jellos in separate bowls.
Put lime jello in bottom of large loaf pan and refrigerate until firm.
Let lemon jello set until almost firm, then beat with electric mixer until light and fluffy.
Mix with drained crushed pineapple, cream cheese and whipped cream.
Put on top of lime jello.
When firm, pour cooled cherry jello on top.
May be used as a salad or a dessert.

title: mock cheese souffle
directions: Break up bread.
Spread in baking dish.
Grate cheese over it.
Beat eggs; add seasonings and milk.
Pour over bread and cheese.
Stir.
Cover.
Let stand in refrigerator at least 3 hours (can leave overnight).
Bake uncovered at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: spinach cheese bites
directions: Place one pepperoni slice in the bottom of each lightly greased miniature muffin pan.
Cut remaining pepperoni slices into 48 wedges.
Combine spinach and next 8 ingredients.
Spoon into muffin cups.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool 10 minutes.
Gently remove to plate.
Top each cup with sour cream and pepperoni wedge. Serve warm.
Bake ahead and freeze for up to 3 months.

title: homemade peanut butter cups
directions: Melt butter.
Combine crumbs, 1 cup peanut butter, 10x sugar and butter.
Press into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt 1/2 cup chocolate bits and 1/2 cup peanut butter over water.
Spread chocolate mixture over other mixture.
Refrigerate until firm. Store in fridge, but cut into squares before it gets too hard.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Use Italian dressing to marinate your meats.
The longer, the more tender and seasoned your meats.
Or, use buttermilk.
Example for chicken:
Marinate 30 minutes.
Place self-rising flour and seasonings of choice in a plastic bag.

Take each piece and coat it well with the flour mixture by placing it in the bag one at a time, shaking it until well coated and the frying until meat is done. Either marinade will bring rave reviews of the tenderness and good flavor.

title: spinach jalapeno
directions: Cook spinach.
Drain and save liquid.
Melt butter and add flour and onion; cook until soft.
Add liquid slowly.
Add milk, seasonings and cheese.
Add spinach and bread crumbs, if desired. Bake at 350° until bubbly.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: yellow summer squash casserole
directions: Mix butter with stuffing.
Put half of stuffing on the bottom of casserole dish.
Mix sour cream, soup and carrots.
Put on squash and onions, then top with the rest of the stuffing.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until vegetables are tender.

title: tea cakes
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs.
Mix baking powder with the flour.
Add flour mixture, a little at a time, to the butter mixture.
Add vanilla.
Chill.
When dough is firm, roll out on floured paper.
Cut out into squares or with a round cookie cutter.
Cook at 350° on a greased cookie sheet until brown.

title: hot fudge pudding
directions: Sift the first 5 ingredients together.
Stir in milk and oil. Spread in 9-inch square pan.
Sprinkle with mixture of brown sugar and 4 tablespoons of cocoa.
Pour hot water over entire batter. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
May serve with ice cream.

title: no bake banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding with 5 cups of milk.
Beat 2 minutes.
Fold in sour cream and 1/2 Cool Whip.
In a large dish, layer cookies, 1/2 of pudding mix and 1/2 of bananas.
Repeat.
Top dessert with other half of Cool Whip.

title: butter pecan cookies
directions: Cream butter until soft; add vanilla.
Add sugar gradually, beating until light and fluffy.
Sift flour; measure, then sift again, this time with salt and gradually add to sugar mixture. Add pecans and mix well.
Drop by teaspoonful onto greased cookie sheet.
Flatten with fork.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar; add beaten eggs.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to mixture along with juice. Mix well.
Simmer in 9-inch skillet butter and sugar; arrange pineapple slices on top of butter and sugar.
Place cherry in center of each slice; pour batter over all.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Turn out at once.
Have been baking this since 1971.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown beef and onions.
Add all else and simmer 1/2 to 1 hour or cook all day in crock-pot. Garnish last minute with chopped avocado and sour cream if desired.
Can serve with shredded Cheddar and corn chips.
Serves 7.

title: broccoli cauliflower salad
directions: Mix well in a large salad bowl.
Pour mayonnaise, vinegar and sugar over salad.
Chill for 1 hour or longer.
Crumble bacon over top at serving time.

title: outrageous chocolate chip cookies
directions: Beat the sugars, butter, peanut butter, vanilla and egg in medium bowl with wooden spoon until creamy and well blended.
Mix the flour, oats, baking soda and salt. Stir in chips. Drop dough by tablespoonfuls about 2-inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.
Cool 1 minute before removing from cookie sheet.
Makes about 2 dozen cookies.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Butter and line a 9 x 13-inch pan with whole crackers. Make pudding with 3 1/2 cups milk. Fold in Cool Whip. Pour 1/2 mixture over crackers. Add another layer of crackers. Pour remaining mix over crackers. Add another layer of crackers and top with chocolate mix. Serves 20.

title: whole wheat fruit cake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Butter a 9-inch spring pan or tube pan. In a bowl, mix whole wheat flour, flour, wheat germ and soda and set aside.
In a bowl, combine eggs and milk.
Blend well.
Stir in fruits and nuts.
Fold dry ingredients into fruit mixture. Pour into prepared pan.
Bake for 2 hours or until center springs back.
Place pan on a rack and cool before turning out.

title: horne's sweet potato cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together until blended.
Bake in 3 layers, 25 minutes, at 325°.
Cool and frost with Cream Cheese Frosting:

title: tropical spinach salad
directions: Drain pineapple; reserve 2 tablespoons juice. Toss pineapple, bacon, spinach, celery and onion. Combine reserved juice with remaining ingredients. Add to salad and toss. Serves 4 to 6.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Melt oleo and chocolate over low heat.
Stir in sugar, one cup at a time, being sure to blend well.
Mixture will be thick and dry.
Add salt and stir in milk gradually.
Continue to cook 7 to 8 minutes to blend and dissolve sugar.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla.
Serve over ice cream.
Serve hot or cold.

title: potato soup
directions: Cook diced potatoes, chopped onion and salt until potatoes are tender.
Drain off some liquid, if desired.
Add cheese,
ham chunks and wieners (meat of choice), if desired.
Sprinkle with parsley.

title: chicken and bacon bake
directions: Partially precook bacon.
Flatten chicken breasts.
Place bacon on each breast and roll up.
Secure with toothpick.
Place in a baking dish and pour soup and sour cream over chicken.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 1 1/2 to 1 3/4 hours or until tender. Serves 4 to 6.

title: oyster crackers
directions: Mix all ingredients except oyster crackers; heat well and drizzle over crackers.
Cool well and let stand 30 minutes.

title: pizza mac casserole
directions: Prepare dinner as directed on package except using 1/2 cup milk.
Brown meat and drain.
Stir in pizza sauce and onion. Heat.
Spoon half of dinner into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Top with beef mixture and remaining dinner.
Cover and bake at 350° for 25 or 30 minutes or until thoroughly heated.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: browned garlic with broccoli & carrots
directions: We may live without poetry, music and art,

title: potato bake
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Spread mixture into a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Crumble corn flakes and sprinkle on top.
Melt butter and pour over mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: tangy lemon streusel cake
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan. Reserve 2 tablespoons cake mix (dry).
Beat remaining mix, yogurt, oil, water and eggs in a large bowl on low speed for 30 seconds. Beat on medium speed for 2 minutes.
Mix nuts, brown sugar, cinnamon and reserved cake mix.
Pour half of batter into pan. Sprinkle with half of nut mixture.
Repeat with remaining batter and nut mixture.
Bake for 40 to 45 minutes.
Cool.
Serve with sweetened whipped cream, if desired.

title: golden secret meat loaf
directions: In large bowl combine the egg, applesauce, bread crumbs, onion, nutmeg, salt and pepper.
Add ground beef; mix well.
Fold in cheese.
Pat into 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until no pink remains.
Drain.
Let stand a few minutes before slicing.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: sugar-free puff pastries
directions: Bake pastries as directed.
Prepare pudding.
Fill pastries with pudding.
Top with sugar free whipped topping.
Add cherry on top.

title: cheese muffins
directions: Grease muffin pan.
Bake at 425 degrees for 25 minutes.
Yield: 12 muffin, can be made using mini muffin pans (24 muffins).

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Combine egg yolks, sugar, flour, salt and cream of tartar with 1/4 cup of the 2 cups milk. Heat the other 1 3/4 cup milk; stir in egg mixture. Let boil briefly. Take off heat and add coconut and vanilla. Pour into cooled crust.

title: endive with bacon dressing
directions: In a saucepan combine all ingredients.
Stir until thick. Pour over endive that has been washed and broken into small pieces.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all together in one bowl.
Refrigerate.

title: baked lasagne
directions: Boil Mueller's Italian style lasagne
in 4 quarts of rapidly boiling water (add 1 tablespoon salt to water) for 12 minutes. Stir gently. Drain. Add 1 tablespoon olive oil to prevent sticking. Let cool.

title: microwave broccoli casserole
directions: Saute pepper and onion in a tablespoon of margarine.
Add to other ingredients and mix well.
Top with cheese.
Microwave for 15 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes and serve.

title: strawberry margarita for two
directions: Blend all ingredients until the mixture is thick.

title: cheese pineapple salad
directions: Mix together.
Add miniature marshmallows and maraschino cherries, if desired.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix margarine, cocoa, sugar and milk in saucepan.
Cook over medium-high heat until boiling; boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter and vanilla.
Stir until melted.
Add oatmeal; stir.
Drop by teaspoon onto waxed paper.
Cool.

title: sunday corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until good and brown.

title: waldorf citrus supreme
directions: Heat lemon 15 to 20 seconds in microwave on High before squeezing (grate before).

title: veggie bacon and cabbage
directions: Cut breakfast strips in 2-inch pieces.
Mix with large, chunky pieces of the cabbage, diced onions and butter.
Season and either cook on stovetop or bake 30 minutes at 350°, or until cabbage is tender.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Cook mixed vegetables and drain.
Mix with other ingredients and put in buttered casserole (2 1/2-quart).
Top with 1 stack Ritz crackers, rolled and mixed with 1/2 stick of oleo.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: cream gravy
directions: Place drippings in skillet and stir in flour.
Cook over low heat until smooth and bubbly.
Stir in liquid and heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Boil and stir for 1 minute.

title: wild rice casserole
directions: Cook rice, salt and pepper.
Add mushrooms, pimentos and parsley.
Mix. Melt butter.
Add celery and saute gently.
Add mushroom soup and onion salt.
Pour over rice mixture.
Bake at 425° for 30 minutes.

title: parmesan pull-aparts
directions: Melt margarine in round cake or pie pan.
Sprinkle onion and parsley on melted margarine.
Cut biscuits into quarters and place on onion mixture.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 425° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Serve upside-down on a serving plate.

title: dirt cake for flowerpot arrangement
directions: Use a new flowerpot that has been washed.
Grind cookies in blender and set aside.
Mix together remaining ingredients.
Fill flowerpot with layers of Oreos and moist mixture.
Fold in slightly.
Refrigerate for several hours.

title: martha washington candy
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Roll into balls.
Melt chocolate; dip balls in chocolate.

title: vidalia onion pie
directions: Saute onions in 1 stick of margarine. Add remaining ingredients. Put in pie shell. Sprinkle with parmesan cheese. Bake 15 minutes at 400° then 300° until brown.

title: millionaire pie
directions: Mix milk and lemon juice; drain juice from fruit thoroughly. Cut peaches in small pieces.
Add all fruit to milk mixture. Blend in Cool Whip.
Pour into crusts and chill for several hours.

title: pork chops supreme
directions: Season pork with salt.
Place in ungreased shallow baking pan. Top each chop with an onion and lemon slice, 1 tablespoon brown sugar and 1 tablespoon catsup.
Cover and cook in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Uncover and cook, spooning sauce over chops occasionally, until done.

title: divinity
directions: Cook sugar, water and syrup until it forms a soft ball in water.
Beat egg whites.
Then put in with syrup.
Beat with mixer until thick and creamy.
Gradually fold in vanilla and nuts.
Pour on buttered plate or drop by tablespoons on waxed paper.

title: potato soup
directions: Mix all ingredients except cornstarch together and cook until tender.
Thicken with cornstarch.

title: aunt pearl's lemon pie filling
directions: Mix sugar, water, corn starch, and cook until creamy. Add egg yolks, lemon rind and lemon juice, return to heat, cook until clear. Add butter, pour into baked pie shell and cover with meringue.

title: dorothy's walnut kisses
directions: Beat vinegar into beaten egg whites.
Gradually beat in sugar. Fold in walnuts.
Drop by spoonfuls onto baking paper on a cookie sheet.
Bake at 250° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Carefully remove from paper when slightly cool.
These will develop a firm crust when cool.
(For a festive touch, sprinkle with colored sugar prior to baking.)

title: bean salad
directions: Combine all ingredients together. Mix well. Let set for three days to make sure all flavors blend.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Brown onions and flour in margarine until golden brown.
Add salt, pepper and paprika.
Add ground beef and brown.
Add bell pepper and mushroom soup and cook for 5 minutes.
Add sour cream and heat until mixture is hot.
Serve over cooked rice.

title: cherry jubilee
directions: Mix well together and refrigerate.

title: chess pie
directions: Melt
butter
in
saucepan.
Stir in sugar. Remove from heat. Add eggs, buttermilk and vanilla. Blend well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 425° for 10 minutes. Reduce heat to 350° and bake until filling shakes slightly, about 20 minutes.

title: halibut au gratin
directions: Top halibut with onion and bay leaves; steam 30 minutes.
Melt butter and add milk and flour.
Stir and cook until smooth and thick.
Add cheese and stir until melted.
Add salt and pepper. Butter a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Break halibut into serving size pieces.
Discard bay leaves and put halibut into casserole.
Top with cheese, sauce and bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: betty biscuits
directions: Bake at 450° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: divine lemon lush
directions: Mix together margarine, flour and pecans.
Spread in bottom of 11 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 400° 15 minutes or until brown. Let cool.
Blend cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Spread over crust.
Mix pudding with milk.
Let set up, pour over second layer.
Top with Cool Whip.
Chill in refrigerator.

title: whipped hot chocolate
directions: Heat milk to boiling with coffee and cinnamon.
Remove cinnamon stick.
Dissolve chocolate in hot water.
Add to hot milk.
Add remaining ingredients, stirring and heating until scalding.
Remove from fire and beat until foamy.

title: tamale casserole
directions: Place tamales on bottom of a shallow baking pan.
Layer with corn chips, chili, taco sauce and cheese.
Bake at 425° until cheese has melted.
Top with sour cream.

title: cheese topped fish fillets
directions: In shallow baking pan, sprinkle fish with salt, flour, paprika and garlic salt.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Top with cheese; place under broiler until cheese bubbles.

title: artichoke soup
directions: Saute onions and celery in butter.
Add flour.
Cook a little, but add chicken broth, lemon juice, thyme, bay leaf and artichokes; salt and pepper.
Cover.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Remove from heat; add beaten egg and cream.

title: sisti's seafood pasta
directions: Clean all seafood.
Cut salmon and swordfish into 1-inch cubes.
Crush tomatoes by hand.
Remove bay leaf from can.
In a 14-inch skillet, combine crushed tomatoes, tomato paste, 1 1/2 chopped garlic cloves and 1/4 ounce chopped basil.
Bring to boil. Add 1/2 cup Italian red wine.
Boil until wine aroma is gone, stirring constantly.
Lower to simmer, covered, for 15 to 20 minutes.
Bring back to boil, then add salmon and swordfish.

title: lasagna
directions: Sprinkle beef with next 5 ingredients.
Brown in frying pan with onion.
Drain grease drippings.
Add tomato sauce, sugar and water.
Bring to a boil.
Cook, uncovered, on low heat until thick.
Cook noodles as directed on box.
In 2 pans, alternate layers of noodles, Parmesan, cottage cheeses and beef mixture. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Place slices of Mozzarella cheese on top of lasagna during last 5 minutes of baking time.

title: potato beef quick meal
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In large ovenproof skillet, brown beef; drain.
Add onion, green pepper, brown sugar, cayenne pepper, water, chili sauce, Worcestershire sauce, potato slices, contents of seasoning mix envelope and tomatoes.
Mix well.
Bring mixture in skillet to a boil; stir.
Carefully place skillet in oven. Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes or until potatoes are tender, stirring occasionally.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake for an additional 1 to 2 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Makes 8 (1 cup) servings.

title: aunt bee's apple pie(opie's favorite)
directions: In a large bowl combine the 1/2 cup butter or margarine and the cream cheese and let come to room temperature.
Add 2 cups flour and blend well; chill.
Roll out half of dough and place in a 9-inch pie pan.
Reserve remaining dough for the top crust.

title: banana date muffins
directions: Mix flour, baking powder and soda in a mixing bowl.
Mix egg, banana, oil, salt and sugar together.
Pour banana mixture into flour mixture and mix, only until moistened good.
Fold in dates. Fill 12 muffin pan cups 2/3 full.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 400°.

title: cream puffs
directions: Melt butter in water; place on stove and while boiling, stir in flour and salt.
Cool slightly.
Add eggs one at a time and baking powder.
Drop on cookie sheet.
Bake until free from beads of moisture in moderate oven (375°) for 35 minutes.
Makes 8.

title: peach pie
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch together.
Add water and butter; bring to a boil.
Dice three peaches; add to the syrup.
Simmer 5 minutes or until thick; cool.
Slice remaining peaches into pie shell; pour the cooled peach syrup over the sliced peaches in the pie shell.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: camp out "puppy chow"
directions: Melt together the butter, chocolate chips and peanut butter. Pour mixture over Crispix cereal and stir to coat cereal well. Pour powdered sugar into a large bag.
Add chocolate covered cereal and shake well.
That's it! Serves 10.

title: strawberry bread
directions: In a large bowl, beat eggs until fluffy.
Add oil and sugar and continue to beat.
Mix dry ingredients
together; add to sugar mixture.
Add thawed berries; mix well.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into greased and floured pans (9 1/2 x 5-inch or 8 1/2 x 4 1/2-inch). Bake at 350° about 1 hour or until bread tests done.
Cool in pan for 10 to 15 minutes, then remove from pan and cool completely. Makes 2 loaves.
