title: microwave sugar cream pie
directions: Put sugar and butter in microwave until melted.
Add enough milk to the Milnot to make 5 cups.
Heat milk until scalded.
Put the two together and bring to a boil.

title: ginger dip
directions: Beat cream cheese, yogurt, honey and ginger root until creamy. Fold in pineapple. cover and refrigerate for 1 hour.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Drain
pineapple,
reserving juice.
Mix pineapple with cheese in	8
x 8-inch casserole.	Mix sugar, flour and juice. Heat enough
to	blend
well.
Pour over pineapple and cheese. Melt butter
and
toss
croutons
in this.
Top casserole with croutons.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: nana hawkin's macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni, following directions on package.
Add salt to water while cooking; drain.

title: b~b~q chicken
directions: Marinade chicken in zesty Italian dressing for 2 hours.
Simmer vinegar, margarine, and worcestershire sauce on range until margarine is melted.
Place chicken breasts on medium high grill. Baste with vinegar mixture throughout grilling, approximately 25 minutes.
When knife pierces easily, chicken is ready to eat. D-EEE-licious!!

title: bake beans
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 400° until thick.

title: chocolate chiffon pie
directions: Mix together the pudding mix and milk.
Fold in Cool Whip. Pour into baked pie shell.
Refrigerate for at least 3 hours before serving.
May be frozen.
That's the way we like it.

title: chocolate chip cherry pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Stir together pie filling and cornstarch until blended; pour into crust.
Beat cream cheese, sugar, eggs and extracts; pour evenly over pie filling.
Sprinkle chocolate chips evenly over top.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes or until almost set in center.
Cool completely on wire rack.
Cover and refrigerate. Refrigerate leftovers.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: tasty carrots
directions: Wash, scrape and slice carrots.
Cover with water in saucepan. Add 1 or 2 bouillon cubes.
Boil until carrots are tender.
Drain and toss with a spoon of honey or maple syrup.
Really, really good.

title: huber farm fried biscuits
directions: In large bowl, combine powdered milk, yeast and sugar.
In another bowl, mix water and oil.
Add liquids to dry ingredients and mix well until no yeast lumps remain.
Add flour, 1 cup at a time, stirring slowly.
After 5 cups are added, begin kneading in remaining flour slowly on a generously floured surface.
After all the flour is added, continue kneading 5 minutes more.
Roll out in sections, if necessary, to 1/2-inch thick on floured surface.
Cut with a floured 2-inch biscuit cutter.
Place biscuits on a greased cookie sheet.
Let rise in a warm area for 1 hour.
Heat deep shortening to 350°.
Add biscuits without crowding.
When edges turn brown, turn once.
Serve hot with apple butter or honey.

title: july 4th cold pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta; drain.
Chop bell peppers, onion, cucumber and tomato.
Mix all in big bowl; add Mrs. Dash and Italian dressing and stir together thoroughly.
Refrigerate overnight so it can marinate.
It is fantastic and has become a July 4th tradition!

title: strawberry salad
directions: Heat water to boiling. Add to jello. Add pineapple and sweetened strawberries.
Add the mashed bananas.
Divide in half. Put 1/2 in refrigerator until gelled.
When gelled, put Cool Whip on top.
Pour the other half of jello mixture on top.
Chill to set.

title: tuna cheese souffle
directions: Press pie shell into a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Combine tuna and onion; spread in bottom of pie shell.
In bowl, stir soup until smooth; gradually blend in flour.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Pour over tuna mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: baked catfish(low-fat)
directions: Combine the first 7 ingredients; set aside.
Whisk together the egg white and milk.
Dip fillets in milk mixture; dredge in cornmeal mixture.
Place on a foil lined baking sheet coated with cooking spray.
Sprinkle fillets with sesame seed; coat each fillet with cooking spray.

title: barbecued meat balls(appetizer)
directions: Roll meatball mix into quarter size balls.
Put in heavy pan.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Roll into small balls.
Bake for 12 to 18 minutes at 325°.

title: busy family homemade rolls
directions: Mix yeast, flour and sugar together; set aside.
Combine water, egg and melted margarine.
Add dry mixture to wet mixture. Put in covered bowl and, if time allows, let set out for about 2 hours.
Bake in muffin pan or roll out or pinch.

title: sour cream jello
directions: Stir jello, sugar and hot water until dissolved; add sour cream and whip until fluffy.
Add oranges and pineapple.
Mix together gently and refrigerate.
(The flavor of the jello may be varied).

title: hush pups
directions: Mix dry ingredients, pour in milk and egg.
Add onion, mix until batter comes out thin.
Fry in deep fat oil.

title: black-eyed peas casserole
directions: Brown ground beef with onion and bell pepper.
Mix together and top with cheese.
Bake until hot and bubbly.

title: fettucine-lasagna
directions: Saute mushrooms, onions and green pepper.
Then stir in spaghetti sauce.
Mix well. Combine spaghetti with Parmesan cheese and beaten eggs with butter in large pot. Mix well.
Place fettucine in the bottom of 13 x 9-inch casserole.
Spread Ricotta cheese over. Pour sauce over top.
Sprinkle with shredded Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes
Bon Appetit!

title: can-it-really-be-so-easy? roast beef
directions: Place beef roast on double layer of aluminum foil. Combine soup and dry soup mix. Spread on all sides of roast. Wrap foil around roast. Place in slow cooker. Pour water around roast. Cover. Cook on low 6 to 8 hours.

title: rocky road squares
directions: Melt chips, butter and shortening in microwave.
Remove from microwave.
Add marshmallows and nuts; blend well.
Put in buttered 8-inch square pan.
Chill until firm.
Cut into squares.

title: brown sugar cake
directions: Cream the sugar, eggs and butter together.
Sift dry ingredients and add alternately with the water.
Chop nuts and add to batter with the vanilla.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: black-eyed peas salad
directions: Mix together and chill one hour before serving.

title: chanukah fried chicken
directions: Sprinkle chicken with nutmeg, garlic, 1 1/2 teaspoons salt and 1/4 teaspoon pepper.
Place in heavy-duty plastic bag; add lemon juice and 2 tablespoons olive oil.
Seal bag; refrigerate several hours or overnight, turning bag occasionally to mix the chicken with the marinade.

title: zucchini fritters
directions: In medium
bowl, stir together flour, baking powder and salt. In another bowl combine milk, egg and zucchini.
Add to dry ingredients,
mix
just
until
moistened.
Drop by spoons into hot oil (375°).
Fry a few at a time until golden, 3 to 4 minutes. Drain on paper towels.
Makes about 24.

title: ground turkey casserole
directions: Brown ground turkey.
Place meat in bottom of shallow casserole dish (9 x 9 x 2-inch).
Sprinkle onion flakes and cover with catsup.
Cover with drained beans, then cover with prepared mashed potatoes.
Grate cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes until heated.

title: mom's no bake chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Put butter, milk and sugar in a saucepan and bring to a boil for 2 minutes; take off the heat.
Stir in the remaining ingredients.
Blend well and drop by teaspoon on wax paper or on foil lined cookie sheet.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill at least 1 hour before serving.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: lorene thomas' cherry pudding
directions: Cream sugar and butter; add egg.
Mix well, then add cherries and nuts.
Add flour with salt and soda.
Bake until brown at 325°.
Cut in serving squares and serve with cherry sauce and whipped cream.

title: corned beef salad(serves 16)
directions: Into the boiling water, dissolve the beef bouillon cubes, the lemon Jell-O and the gelatin, letting it sit until it cools.
Then add other items, mixing well.
Put into the refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Combine oil and sugar; add eggs, apples and vanilla.
Sift the dry ingredients together and add to the batter by hand.
Add nuts.

title: oatmeal bread
directions: Add salt to boiling water and stir in oatmeal and shortening. Let stand until entire mixture is lukewarm.
Crumble yeast in a large mixing bowl.
Add 1 teaspoon sugar and 1/4 cup lukewarm water.
Let stand 1 hour.
Dissolve brown sugar in 1/2 cup lukewarm water and add to yeast mixture.
Stir in one-half of the flour into the yeast mixture and beat until smooth.
Add the remaining flour and the oatmeal mixture to make a stiff dough. Knead lightly on a floured board until smooth.
Let the dough rise, covered, until doubled in bulk.
Punch the dough down and divide in two parts.
Let the dough stand covered on a lightly floured board, about 15 minutes.
Form each portion into loaves and place in greased bread pans and let rise until doubled in bulk.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes, then reduce the heat to 375° and finish baking for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: breakfast pie
directions: Put one-half of shredded cheese on bottom of pie shell.
Next put cooked and crumbled sausage.
Put rest of cheese.
Beat eggs, salt and pepper.
Pour egg mixture over cheese and sausage in pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Let set for 10 minutes before serving.

title: brown rice
directions: Brown onion and rice in butter.
Add consomme and mushrooms. Cook in covered casserole in 400° oven for 1 hour.

title: diet cheese cake
directions: Mix Jell-O and hot water and let cool until starting to gel. Blend cottage cheese and cream cheese.
Add Jell-O; blend.
Add Cool Whip.
Blend.
Pour into graham cracker crust.

title: cincinnati chili
directions: Reserve 1/2 of the diced onions to serve later with chili, if desired.
Brown beef with garlic and remaining onions.
Stir in chili powder, allspice, cinnamon, cumin and salt; cook 1 minute. Stir in tomato sauce, stewed tomatoes, Worcestershire sauce, vinegar and 3/4 cup water over high heat.
Heat to boiling. Reduce heat to low; cover and simmer for 1 hour, stirring occasionally.
Add drained kidney beans in last half hour.
About 25 minutes before chili is to be served, prepare spaghetti according to package directions.
Serve chili over spaghetti with grated cheese on top.

title: rice-pea casserole
directions: Brown
hamburger and onion.
Put into
casserole
dish. Add cooked rice, soup and peas.
Bake at 350°,	uncovered, for 1 hour.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until light and foamy.
Add next 5 ingredients. Mix lightly but well.
In a separate bowl, mix dry ingredients. Add flour mixture and blend.
Add nuts.
Put in 2 greased and floured loaf pans and bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: ham and potatoes casserole
directions: Saute green pepper and onion in butter until tender.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper; cook until bubbly.
Add milk gradually and cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until smooth and thickened.
Remove from heat and add cheese and mayonnaise, stirring until cheese is melted.
Stir in potatoes and ham.
Spoon mixture into Pam sprayed shallow 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Serves 6.

title: pace's famous baby back ribs
directions: Open ribs package. Turn ribs where the bone is up. Peel the thin layer of skin off the ribs. Put Ranch Style dressing on the back side of ribs. Bone up, add salt and pepper, then add butter all over the back side. Use the whole bottle, then get a handful of brown sugar. Add to the back of ribs. May take 2 handfuls. Don't be shy. Wrap in foil (heavy-duty). Bake at 300° for 2 hours, then open foil. Add handful of brown sugar. Cook 1 more hour. If using a grill, brown ribs for 30 minutes before wrapping in foil. Serves 1 if hungry. Can do ahead.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine first 9 ingredients and put in 2 casserole dishes. Mix almonds, chips and cheese and put on top of chicken. Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: banana split pie
directions: Slice banana and layer on bottom of pie crust.
Sprinkle pineapple over banana.
Mix pudding and milk according to package directions.
Pour over pineapple and banana.
Chill about 30 minutes.

title: barbecue spareribs
directions: Cut spareribs in serving size pieces.
Brown in skillet.
Pour off fat.
Put in baking pan.
Melt margarine in skillet; add onion.
Cook until browned.
Add next 9 ingredients.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Pour sauce over ribs.
Bake, uncovered, 1 hour at 350°.

title: mild salsa
directions: In a blender, mix well together tomatoes, cilantro and garlic, add chilis and onions and blend some more.

title: rosemary chops
directions: Marinate pork chops (not steaks) at least 4 hours, flipping halfway in between marinade time (8 hours is best).
Broil or grill until done.

title: arlene's chicken pot pie
directions: Put chicken, carrots, onion and celery into pot and cover with water.
On small-medium flame, cook chicken until done (falls off bone).
Remove chicken and when cooled, pull chicken off bone and put in large bowl.
Add frozen peas to pot and cook another 5 minutes.
With slotted spoon, remove the rest of the ingredients from pot and put in bowl with chicken.
Add can of soup and 1/2 cup of chicken stock from pot and mix together.
Mold 1 pie crust to bottom of casserole dish; add mixture.
Cover with second crust. Put 3 slits into top of crust.
Bake at 350° until the crust is golden brown, approximately 35 to 45 minutes.

title: low calorie cheesecake
directions: Make crust of crackers, margarine and 2 packages sugar substitute.
Pour into pie plate.
Dissolve jello in 1 cup of boiling water; cool.
In blender, combine cottage cheese and 6 packages sugar substitute; blend until smooth.
Gradually add jello and vanilla to cottage cheese mixture.
Blend until combined.
Pour into graham crust.
Chill.

title: chicken salad for two
directions: Toss chicken with celery, lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Stir in mayonnaise.
Fold in eggs, carefully. Chill thoroughly. Serve on salad greens and sprinkle with bacon.

title: grand canyon goulash
directions: Combine beef, onions and green pepper.
Cook until browned. Add other ingredients.
Stir often until completely heated.

title: marion seelhurst's brisket
directions: Place in roaster at 250° to 300°.
Bake until done.

title: drop cookies
directions: Put shortening and sugar in a bowl and cream until fluffy. Add egg and cream well.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Add 1/2 flour to creamed mixture.
Beat; add milk, vanilla and rest of flour.
Mix well and bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: dorito-delight
directions: Spread chips in 9 x 13-inch dish.
Brown hamburger meat, onion, salt and peppers.
Add soups, milk and chillies.
Spread mixture over chips.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: bacon-potato chowder
directions: In a large saucepan, over medium heat, cook bacon until browned.
Add onions.
Continue cooking until tender, about 3 minutes; drain.
Add potatoes, water, salt and pepper.
Cook until potatoes are tender, about 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to low.
Stir in soup, sour cream and milk.
Cook, stirring occasionally, until heated through, about 5 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: potato and cheese casserole
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch glass casserole dish, slice enough potatoes to cover bottom of dish.
Add cheese to desired taste.
Pour milk over mixture until potatoes are covered.
Sprinkle flour over top. Add salt and pepper to taste.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until brown on top.

title: egyptian bread
directions: Add the water to the flour and salt quite slowly, mixing thoroughly.
Knead the dough.
Shape into small rounds or triangles; cover with a cloth and leave overnight.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: bread pudding
directions: Sprinkle
in
a little cinnamon and nutmeg.
Soak bread in scalded milk 5 minutes.
Add butter, salt and sugar.
Pour hot mixture
slowly
over
beaten eggs, stirring as you pour. Add vanilla
and
mix
well.
Pour into buttered baking dish. Bake in pan
of water at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes until firm and
golden brown on top.
You can add seedless raisins if you desire before baking.

title: smores
directions: Fold chocolate chips and marshmallows into whipped topping. Spread mixture about 1/2-inch thick on one cracker.
Press another cracker lightly on top.
Repeat making sandwiches.
Freeze until firm, about 4 hours.
Wrap for freezer to store for up to 2 weeks.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until frothy; add sugar, oil and beat until thick and lemon color.
Add zucchini; sift and add flour, cinnamon, baking soda, baking powder and salt.
Stir in nuts and raisins. Pour into 3 greased and floured loaf pans (8 x 4 1/2 x 3-inch). Bake at 350° for 1 hour 10 minutes.
Invert and keep in pan until cool.

title: easy jello salad
directions: Make Jell-O according to directions on package.
When partially set, add prepared Dream Whip, mixed with cream cheese. Add pineapple and marshmallows and stir.
Chill in an 8-inch square dish.

title: chocolate gravy
directions: Combine all ingredients in a saucepan.
Heat and stir until thick.
Serve hot over fresh biscuits or pancakes.

title: chocolate-raspberry mousse trifle
directions: In a medium bowl, cream together margarine, cream cheese and powdered sugar. In a large bowl, mix together milk, pudding and Cool Whip. In a larger bowl, mix together the two mixtures. Put a layer of cookies in the bottom of the flowerpot, then a layer of the pudding mixture. Keep alternating layers, ending with cookie crumbs on top. Put in the refrigerator or freezer. Best if made the night before and refrigerated overnight. To serve, place flower in the center of pot and use shovel to scoop out to serve. This can be made in a 9 x 13-inch glass pan.

title: coca-cola salad
directions: Drain and reserve the liquid from the cans of fruit.
Heat juices and dissolve gelatin in the heated juice.
Then add Cokes, cherries, pineapple and nuts.
Grate frozen cream cheese on top. Place in refrigerator until set.

title: holiday breakfast casserole
directions: Spread hash browns in greased 8 x 8-inch greased pan.
Brush with melted butter.
Bake at 425° for 25 minutes to form crust. Layer ham, cheeses and chilies on crust.
Combine eggs, milk and salt.
Place on top of ham/cheese mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Place salsa on top when serving.

title: date pudding(recipe is over 150 years old.)
directions: Stir all well.
Makes a stiff batter.
Pour syrup into a 9 x 14-inch pan.
Drop batter by large spoonfuls into the syrup.
Bake at 350° until top is brown and a toothpick inserted comes out clean (about 40 minutes).

title: bologna boats
directions: Put 1/4 cup water in small Teflon frypan.
Heat to medium heat.
Place 1 slice thin sliced bologna in heated water (it wll form a bubble after cooked).
Cook for 1 minute.
Take out carefully and fill with scrambled eggs.
Nice breakfast treat for a cold school morning.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter; add sugar gradually.
Add one egg at a time, being sure to beat 3 minutes after each egg.
Fold in flour and vanilla last.
Bake in 1 large pan or 2 small loaf pans at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: bishop bread
directions: Mix all ingredients with electric mixer until ready for fruit, then fold into batter.
Pour into a loaf pan (greased) and bake at 350° for
1 hour.

title: ranger cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Roll in small balls.
Press flat on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Improves with age if kept in a covered jar (tight).

title: easy peachy dessert
directions: Melt butter in heavy skillet.
Add pecans; cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, 3 to 4 minutes or until toasted.
Stir in cereal crumbs, brown sugar and nutmeg.
Press half of crumb mixture into 8-inch square baking pan.
Put pan into freezer for 15 minutes.

title: easy beef stroganoff
directions: In skillet, cook 1/2 of the beef, onions and mushrooms (until beef is no longer pink).
Set aside.
Repeat with other 1/2 of the beef, onions and mushrooms.
Return mixture to skillet.
Stir in soup and heat through, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat and stir in sour cream.
Serve over cooked noodles.

title: hilda's famous biscuits and gravy
directions: In a double boiler, place milk, salt and pepper.
Cook 20 minutes, watching that double boiler does not run dry.
Fry sausage in a skillet, and do not drain grease.
When fully cooked, add oleo and flour; stir, mixing well.
Pour meat into hot milk and cook until gravy thickens, 10 minutes or longer.
Place opened biscuit on a plate or in a bowl and cover with sausage gravy.
(If you desire, you may add 2 teaspoons sugar to milk gravy while cooking.)

title: oven-baked chicken
directions: Heat oven to 425°. Melt butter in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish in oven. Stir together Bisquick, paprika, salt and pepper; coat chicken. Place skin side down in dish (dish and butter should be hot). Bake 35 minutes; turn chicken. Bake about 15 minutes longer or until juice is no longer pink when center of thickest piece is cut.

title: sour cream chocolate cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan, two 9-inch round pans, three 8-inch round pans or 3 dozen cupcakes.

title: party cookies
directions: Blend shortening and both kinds of sugar.
Beat in vanilla and eggs.
Sift remaining dry ingredients together and add to sugar and egg mixture.
Mix well.
Stir in 1/2 cup M&M's.
Drop from teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Decorate cookies with remaining M&M's.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown. After baking, some of the M&M's may be cracked.
This does not hurt the taste of the cookie.
Makes about 6 dozen 2 1/2-inch cookies.

title: lemon bars
directions: Pour mixture over baked bottom and bake 25 minutes at 350°. Cool in pan and cut.

title: twinkie banana pudding pie(weight watchers)
directions: Slice Twinkies lengthwise. Put them cream side up in bottom of 15 x 2 x 9 pan. Put bananas over Twinkies evenly. Prepare pudding according to box for filling. Pour filling over top. Top it with Cool Whip. Chill for 2 hours. Makes 12 servings.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Add egg yolks.
Sift together dry ingredients and add alternately with bananas.
Fold in beaten egg whites and nuts last.
Bake 60 minutes at 350° in two small loaf pans.

title: no crust spinach quiche(low carb)
directions: Saute the first 5 ingredients in oil. Drain and cool. Combine eggs and Ricotta cheese and beat until blended. Add veggies and all other ingredients.
Stir until blended. Pour mixture into lightly greased 10-inch deep dish quiche pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Let stand 10 minutes before cutting.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Wash and dry mushrooms.
Pull stems out.
May dice stems and add to sausage.
Brown sausage, onion and seasoning.
Add cheese and let melt.
Stuff mushrooms.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: pork chops
directions: Place pork chops in an ungreased shallow baking pan.
Top each pork chop with onion slice, 1 tablespoon brown sugar and 1 tablespoon ketchup.
Cover.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown hamburger.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Add onion and green pepper.
Cook noodles 3 to 5 minutes.
Drain.
Place noodles in bottom of baking dish.
Layer hamburger mixture on top.
Then layer the soup, pizza sauce, mushrooms and remaining ingredients. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: strawberry jello cake
directions: Bake cake in oblong pan as directed on box.
Let cool slightly. Punch holes in cake with a straw.
Mix Jell-O with boiling water. Stir until dissolved.
Pour Jell-O into holes on the cake.
Cover and place in refrigerator.
Mash strawberries, if whole, sweeten a little.
Drain juice and pour cream cheese and Cool Whip.
Put on top of strawberries.
Keep refrigerated.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown the hamburger.
Add the sauces, onion, beans, half the tortilla chips and half the cheese.
Pour into greased 9 x 9-inch casserole and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Top with sour cream and edge rest of tortilla chips.
Sprinkle rest of cheese over all. Return to oven for 10 minutes.

title: english toffee
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients, cook to light crack (285°).
Pour onto well-buttered jelly roll pan.
Cool. Melt chocolate chips. Spread 1/2 on toffee.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts.
Cool. Turn over and repeat with chocolate chips and nuts.
Cool.
Break into pieces.

title: wieners and macaroni
directions: Cook macaroni.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Blend Ro-Tel tomatoes in blender.
Combine all ingredients in casserole dish and bake, covered, for about 30 minutes.

title: polynesian sauce
directions: Drain fruit and keep liquid.
In saucepan, combine liquid, grape juice, honey, lime juice and heavy cream.
Simmer 5 minutes to blend flavors.
Dissolve cornstarch in water.
Stir into sauce. Cook, stirring until thickened and smooth.
Add fruit and coconut just before serving.
Makes about 2 cups sauce.

title: morning glory muffins
directions: Mix together dry ingredients in large bowl. Add the raisins, coconut, carrots, apple, pineapple (drained) and nuts. Stir well. In separate bowl, whisk the eggs with oil and vanilla. Pour mixture into the bowl with the dry ingredients/fruit and blend well. Spoon batter into cupcake tins, either greased or lined with muffin papers. Bake at 350° for about 35 minutes. Cool in pan for 10 minutes, then turn out on rack.

title: amazin raisin cake
directions: Grease and flour one long baking pan.
Mix at low speed the first 10 ingredients for 2 minutes, scraping bowl frequently. Batter will be thick.
Stir in apples, raisins and nuts with a spoon.
Pour into pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cool and serve with Cool Whip.

title: crab bisque
directions: Combine butter and flour in a saucepan.
Cook over medium heat until smooth, stirring constantly.
Stir in tomato paste, onions, celery, garlic, green pepper and parsley.
Cook until vegetables are tender, stirring constantly.

title: tender slow roast pork
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Place pork in pan with lid.
Sprinkle pork heavily with Worcestershire sauce.
Turn it over and sprinkle other side.
Take brown sugar and rub against meat to make a brown crust.
Pour apple juice in bottom of pan, not over meat.
Cover and place in oven.
Bake about 10 minutes on 400°, then turn down to 200° and bake for 4 hours.

title: escalloped corn
directions: Mix all ingredients and place in greased casserole dish.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: broken glass cake
directions: Make each flavor of Jell-O separately, using only 1 1/2 cups water; mold.
Bring to boil pineapple juice and sugar; add unflavored gelatin and water.
Cool until syrupy.
Add whipped cream to pineapple mixture.
Cut Jell-O into cubes; fold into whipped cream mixture in a spring pan (easy to remove when you use this type of pan).
Refrigerate for 12 to 24 hours.
Yields 8 to 10 pieces if cut in pie shape slices.

title: sausage quiche
directions: Put sausage and cheese in pie shell and evenly distribute. Combine remaining ingredients in blender or mixer and mix well. Pour custard mixture over cheese and sausage.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes until just set in center and lightly browned.

title: little tomato blt
directions: Cut bread rounds or buy round bread and bake 300° for 30 minutes.
Mix all the above ingredients and spread on bread.
Place a slice of tomato on top of mixture.
Sprinkle with bacon bits. This mixture is a large quantity - usually used for big receptions.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix together and let stand to blend in refrigerator.
Makes pretty much dip.
You can make half the recipe and it tastes just as good.

title: tea cakes
directions: Beat butter in a bowl for 30 seconds.
Add 1 1/4 cups sugar and 1 teaspoon vanilla; beat until fluffy.
Add eggs; beat well. Stir together flour, baking soda and salt in a mixing bowl.
Add to beaten mixture alternately with buttermilk.
Drop by spoonfuls onto a greased baking sheet.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Bake in a 350° oven for 10 to 12 minutes or until lightly brown.

title: cheryl's mexican dip
directions: Mix cream cheese and salsa until well blended.
Refrigerate overnight.
Place in dish and sprinkle bell pepper and cheese. Eat with tostados chips.

title: cheese cake
directions: Combine cracker crumbs and melted butter; line bottom of pan. Mix sugar with cream cheese; add cooled jello.
Mix well.
Add whipped milk to mixture.
Pour over crust and chill.

title: zucchini bake
directions: Using a food processor or grater, coarsely shred zucchini (you should have about 4 cups). Sprinkle with salt; let stand in a colander for 15 minutes. Squeeze with your hands to press out moisture.

title: barbecue steak sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Simmer while grill is heating.
Brown steak on one side, turn over and baste with steak sauce.
Complete cooking.
Turn and baste other side.
Brown sauce, turn and baste again.
Remove and eat.

title: iowa butterscotch cookies
directions: Cream Crisco and sugars; add eggs, nuts and vanilla.
Sift flour, salt, soda and baking powder together.
Stir into batter and mix well.
Divide batter in half and shape into 2 rolls. Refrigerate overnight.
Slice in 1/4-inch slices and place on greased and floured cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: cheese bread
directions: Mix flour, cheese, baking powder, sugar, oregano, mustard and salt.
Combine egg, milk and butter and add to dry ingredients along with onions, stirring until combined.
Grease and flour 8 1/2 x 4 1/2-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes. Serve warm.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Add 3 eggs, oil, sugar and vanilla in small bowl.
Mix flour, zucchini, salt, baking soda, cinnamon and baking powder in larger bowl.
Add liquid ingredients to dry ingredients. Blend.
Add walnuts.
Grease and flour pans (2).
Bake in oven at 325°.

title: 1, 2, 3, 4 pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until smooth, not grainy.
Add flour and eggs.
Beat well.
Add milk, vanilla and almond extract.
Add baking powder.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.
Bake in Bundt pan.

title: stuffing
directions: Melt oleo; add celery and onion.
Cook until transparent.
Add to bread and seasonings; mix well.
Add broth and lightly mix well.
Make into balls and bake at 350° for about 20 minutes. Makes 1-inch balls.

title: mom's special beets
directions: Fry onion in butter until soft.
Add beets and some of the juice.
Add remaining ingredients.
Heat and stir until sugar is dissolved and flavors have blended.
Serve warm.

title: super six salad
directions: Layer in large bowl in order as listed using enough mayonnaise to spread over and enough cheese to cover well.
Refrigerate overnight.
Stir well before serving.

title: seafoam peach frosting
directions: Combine egg white, sugar, salt, water and peach preserves in top of double boiler.
Beat one minute to blend, then place over rapidly boiling water.
Beat for 7 minutes or until frosting stands in peaks.
Remove from water and add vanilla.
Beat until thick enough to spread on cake.
Sprinkle with nuts.

title: three bean salad
directions: Drain beans.
Mix all ingredients together. Cover. Let stand in refrigerator for a few hours or overnight before serving.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Add reserved half of orange juice.
Pour batter into prepared 8-inch round pans.
Bake according to package directions.
Cool and frost.

title: baked zucchini(zucchini is good anytime.)
directions: In a skillet, saute the onions with butter until a golden brown.
Add zucchini and cook over low heat, about 10 minutes, stirring often.
Add tomatoes, salt and pepper; simmer, covered, 5 more minutes.
Place in a casserole dish, cover top with cheese and bake in a 375° oven for 20 minutes or more.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix in usual manner.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: marshmallow cream fudge
directions: Three cups sugar, three-fourths cup Karo syrup, three-fourths cup cold water.
Boil until forms a stiff ball when dropped in cold water.
Beat the whites of two eggs very stiff.
Pour syrup over whites of eggs and beat until cold.
After beating awhile, add two cups broken walnuts.
Turn into buttered plate and cut into squares.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar together; add eggs and beat well.
Add vanilla.
Combine dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture alternately with sour cream and milk.
Spoon into a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: chicken chop suey
directions: Saute onions and green pepper in oil with salt for 5 minutes. Add celery, mushrooms and stock. Cover and cook slowly until celery is done.
Add chestnuts and bean sprouts.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Cut off stems from mushrooms and wash well.
Chop stems and cook in olive oil with garlic and onion, about 5 minutes.
Add crab meat, parsley, salt and pepper.
Cook about 5 minutes longer. Remove from heat, allow to cool.
Add bread and egg.
Mix well.

title: freezer type strawberry preserves
directions: Go by directions on Sure-Jell paper.
This recipe makes more.

title: sausage dip
directions: Mix soups and salsa.
Brown sausage.
Mix together and heat through.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: goulash
directions: Brown
meat
and
drain.
Add
onions
and bell pepper. Steam for
5 minutes.
Add corn, tomatoes, half of the cheese and other seasonings to taste.
Cook 20 to 30 minutes over low heat.	Cook noodles and drain.	Add to meat mixture.
Pour in casserole
dish; sprinkle remaining cheese on top and heat in oven before serving.

title: bang-up baked beans
directions: Mix ingredients in baking dish.
Bake 45 minutes at 300°.

title: jeannie salad
directions: Drain juice from pineapple into sauce pan, add 1/2 c. orange juice.
Mix corn starch with sugar then stir into sauce pan and bring to a boil until thickens.
Set aside, let cool.
(Can pour hot over marshmallows, if desired.)

title: rich chocolate caramel brownies
directions: In large bowl, combine cake mix and nuts; stir in butter. Stir in 2/3 cup evaporated milk (batter will be thick).
Spread half of batter into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 15 minutes.
In small saucepan, combine caramels and remaining 1/3 cup evaporated milk.
Stir over low heat until caramels are melted.
Sprinkle chocolate morsels over baked layer; drizzle caramel mixture over top.
Drop remaining batter by heaping teaspoonfuls over caramel mixture.
Return to 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes (top will be soft).
Cool completely before cutting into bars.

title: stacy's snicker pops
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix sugars, butter, peanut butter, vanilla and egg.
Add dry ingredients and mix well.
Take Snickers bar and form dough around to make a ball (covering completely).
Place on ungreased cookie sheet 3 inches apart.
Bake for 13 to 16 minutes. Cool and remove.
Enjoy!

title: country pineapple casserole
directions: In a mixing bowl, cream butter and sugar. Add the eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Stir in pineapple and lemon juice. Fold in the bread cubes. Pour into a greased 13x9x2 inch baking dish. Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 35-40 minutes or until set. Yield 12-16 servings.
Good for breakfast, Great!

title: chocolate delight
directions: Mix all ingredients and press in 9 x 13 pan. Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Melt butter in large skillet.
Saute onion until clear.
Add broccoli; stir thoroughly.
Add soup; stir and simmer a few minutes.
Add Cheez Whiz and rice.
Put in a 2-quart buttered dish.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: "grandma's chili"
directions: Mix all ingredients together and let come to a boil.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Add 1 1/2 tablespoons chili powder.
Turn down to simmer and cook 2 hours.

title: egyptian cheese salad(serves 6)
directions: Score cucumber with fork. Sprinkle with salt and let stand 20 minutes. Crush cheese with fingertips or fork and blend in onion, lemon juice and oil. Season with pepper. Drain, rinse and slice cucumber. Combine with cheese mixture. Place in shallow serving dish and decorate with mint. Chill salad for 30 minutes before serving.

title: potato soup
directions: Bring to a boil and turn heat down; simmer 5 minutes.

title: pea cashew salad
directions: Mix well.
Place in serving container.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Remove from refrigerator 15 minutes before serving and stir.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream shortening; mix with sugar, egg and applesauce.
Add flour, salt, spices, soda and hot water.
Mix well and add chopped nuts.
Bake in large pan at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: chicken salad bake
directions: Sprinkle 1 package potato chips into greased baking dish. Combine chicken, eggs, celery, almonds, onion, pimento, lemon juice, soup and mayonnaise in bowl; mix well.
Spoon into prepared dish.
Top with remaining package potato chips.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes or until bubbly.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: low calorie dill garden dip
directions: Blend cottage cheese and lemon juice until smooth. Stir in remaining ingredients and allow to blend flavors for an hour or two.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: spiced pecans
directions: Beat egg whites and water.
Stir in pecans to coat.
Mix all other ingredients and sprinkle over pecans, mixing well.
Spread pecans on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake in 300° oven for 30 minutes.
Stir twice during baking time to crisp and dry pecans.

title: german potato salad
directions: In a covered saucepan, cook potatoes in boiling, salted water for 25 to 30 minutes or until tender; drain well.
Peel and slice potatoes.

title: steamed broccoli parmesan
directions: Steam broccoli for 10 minutes; drain.
Saute garlic and mushrooms in 3 tablespoons water.
Add broccoli and saute 2 minutes or until crisply tender.
Top with Parmesan cheese and pepper.
Makes 1 serving.

title: baked whole apples
directions: Wash and core apples.
Mix oleo, sugar and cinnamon.
Fill centers of apples.
Place in glass baking dish.
Microwave until apples are tender.
Exact time will depend on size of apples.

title: pecan pie
directions: Combine eggs, sugar and syrup.
Mix well.
Add butter, salt, vanilla and nut meats.
Pour into unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 350° to 375° for 30 minutes, or until set.
Makes 1 large pie.
(One and one-half recipes make 2 small pies.)

title: sour cream cake
directions: Mix ingredients as listed, except cinnamon and 3 tablespoons sugar.
Mix cinnamon and sugar separately.
Pour 1/2 batter in tube pan.
Put cinnamon and sugar mixture on top of the batter in pan.
Pour the other batter on top.
Bake at 350° about 45 minutes.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Drain asparagus, reserving a small amount of liquid.
Butter a 1-quart casserole and arrange half of the asparagus on the bottom. Cover with the sliced eggs.

title: cherry cream cheese pie
directions: Beat cream cheese until light and fluffy.
Beat in milk, lemon juice, and vanilla; mix well.
Pour into crust.
Chill several hours.
Before serving, pour cherries on top.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into pie crusts.
Top with second pie crust and paint with egg (optional).
Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: orange basil marinated chicken
directions: Arrange chicken in ungreased 13 x 9-inch non-metal baking dish. In a small bowl, combine remaining ingredients. Pour over chicken.
Cover with foil.
Refrigerate 4 to 6 hours.

title: sausage cheese dip
directions: Mix cheese cubes and salsa in microwave bowl. Microwave until cheese melts, stirring often. Add sausage. Keep warm in crockpot. Serve with corn chips or nachos.

title: quick-easy spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown bacon, onion and hamburger in skillet.
Drain off grease.
Combine with other ingredients in saucepan and simmer 15 minutes or so.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Sift flour, sugar and salt together.
Add eggs.
Melt 1 cup margarine and 1/3 cup cocoa together.
Pour over flour mixture, mixing well.
Stir in pecans.
Spread in floured and greased cake pan.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.

title: french dressing
directions: Shake all together in a quart jar.
(If too thick, add vinegar.)
Very good over cooled, cooked vegetables.

title: spiced pecans
directions: Combine all ingredients, except pecans, in a saucepan. Simmer until mixture "spins a thread" and is thick of consistency. Remove from heat. Add the pecans and stir quickly until the sugar crystallizes on the nuts. Break apart and allow to cool before storing in a container with a tight lid.

title: sour cream taco casserole
directions: In a skillet, cook onion in 2 tablespoons shortening until soft.
Remove from skillet and set aside.
Brown ground beef in skillet.
Then, mix sour cream, tomatoes, pepper, cheese and onion into the ground beef.
Line bottom of a large casserole dish with tortillas and top with beef mixture.
Let stand for 2 hours.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: fruit balls
directions: Mix coconut, cut up fruit, pecans and raisins together with crushed wafers and crackers.
Melt butter and marshmallows.
Pour over other ingredients.
Knead with hands until well blended. Roll into small balls and roll in confectioners sugar.
Store tightly covered.
Makes 300 balls.

title: jo's fruit punch
directions: Mix all ingredients; put in freezer to get slushy.
This is very good and keeps well.
You can make ahead.
Serves 150.

title: texas beef skillet
directions: Cook hamburger and onion.
Drain. Add rice, tomatoes, kidney beans, salt, chili powder, garlic salt and Tabasco sauce. Cover and simmer on low for 20 minutes.
Add cheese and crushed Fritos. Put into oven until cheese melts.

title: microwave zucchini parmesan
directions: In baking dish, combine zucchini, Parmesan cheese and tomato sauce.
Heat, covered, on High for 9 minutes.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese and let it stand for 5 minutes. Serve.

title: squash casserole
directions: Combine first 2 ingredients.
Cook, drain and mash.
Add remaining ingredients, reserving 1/2 cup cheese to sprinkle over top.
Pour into buttered casserole.
Bake at 375°until firm and cheese is brown.
This is good with a few onion rings sprinkled on during the last 5 minutes of baking.

title: roasted pecans
directions: Melt butter.
Spread pecans in a broiler tray and stir to coat nuts with melted butter.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour or until done, stirring frequently.
Salt to taste.

title: apple cake
directions: Blend oil and sugar well.
Add eggs and beat well.
Mix dry ingredients and add to the mixture.
Add vanilla.
Fold in apples and nuts.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: italian lenten buns
directions: Combine 1/4 cup water, 1 teaspoon sugar and yeast.
Let stand.
Soak raisins in warm water until soft and swollen.
Pat dry before using.
Combine milk, 4 tablespoons sugar, shortening, olive oil, pine nuts, raisins, drained and chopped cherries and about 1 cup flour.
Beat until flour is well blended.
Stir in softened yeast.
Add about 1 1/4 cups flour and stir.
Sprinkle dough lightly with flour and knead for about 5 minutes on well floured board.
Add more flour as needed to prevent sticking.
Let rise in greased bowl in warm place until doubled, about 45 minutes.
Punch down.
Break off small pieces and shape into buns. Place on greased baking sheet.
Let rise.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: old fashioned apple butter(michigan style)
directions: Place apples and apple cider in a large heavy saucepan or Dutch oven.
Over medium heat, bring apples to a boil.
Reduce heat to low, cover and simmer 30 minutes or until apples are tender.
Drain apples, reserving liquid.
Press apples through a sieve, discarding peels.
Return apples to original pan with reserved liquid.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until apple mixture mounds on spoon, about 15 minutes.
Add sugar and spices.
Reduce heat to low and cook 1 hour longer, stirring frequently.
Mixture should thicken.
Quickly ladle hot mixture into sterilized jars and cover with lids and bands.
Process covered with boiling water for 5 minutes.
Yield:
3 1/2 cups.
Great on toast and biscuits.
This recipe contains no fat and it's only 40 calories per tablespoon.

title: bread or hot rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water with 1 teaspoon of sugar added. Pour milk in microwave container with salt.
Heat to scalding. Add sugar and oil.
Cool and add yeast mixture.
Add enough flour for a stiff dough.
Let rise until double in size.
Make into rolls by pinching off pieces of dough and making into rolls. Place in greased pan and let rise again until double in size. Bake in 400° oven for 10 minutes.

title: muffin corn bread
directions: Grease pan and put in oven to get hot before you put the
corn bread in.
Cook in iron skillet at 400° in oven.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: In a glass pan, put 4 to 6 pork chops or chicken breasts. Salt and pepper to taste. Add a little garlic, dried onion chips, a little Mrs. Dash. Turn over meat and be sure all is seasoned. Pour in one can cream of mushroom soup and a little water to mix. Cook in oven at 350 or 375 until done or brown if you like.

title: country chicken
directions: About 1 Hour Before Serving:
In a large open roasting pan, mix potatoes, sausage links and salad oil. Bake in a 425° oven for 15 minutes.

title: chocolate kahlua layered dessert
directions: Stir in until smooth.
Spoon into 12 individual 1/2 cup ramekins:

title: travis' yummy graham crackers
directions: Divide graham crackers into sections.
Fill a cookie sheet or jelly roll pan full of graham crackers.
Melt butter in saucepan and add sugar.
Boil two minutes and stir constantly.
Mixture will thicken.
Add cinnamon and nuts.
Pour mixture over graham crackers in pan.

title: coffee cake
directions: Mix and melt brown sugar, margarine and cinnamon; let cool. Roll 2 packages of the biscuits in sauce and put in greased Bundt pan. Pour some sauce in pan before biscuits and the rest over the top. Sprinkle nuts over top and bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix with spoon the sugar, fruit cocktail and juice, eggs, flour, soda and salt.
Pour into greased 8 x 12-inch pan and sprinkle brown sugar and pecans on top.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°. While cake is still hot, ice.

title: creamy rice pudding
directions: Combine all ingredients, except vanilla, cinnamon and nutmeg; place in saucepan.
Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture comes to full boil, about 8 to 10 minutes.
Remove from heat; cool 5 minutes, stirring once or twice.
Add vanilla.
Pour into serving bowl.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and nutmeg.
Serve warm with cream, if desired.
Makes 8 servings.

title: dill vegetable dip
directions: Combine and chill.
Serve with celery and carrot sticks, cucumber, green pepper and cauliflower.

title: pound cake
directions: Mix Crisco, butter and sugar together; add eggs, one at a time.
Mix	flour,	baking	powder	and
salt together.
Add flour mixture
and
milk	alternately
with
butter
and sugar mixture. Add vanilla and beat.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours. Makes good layer cake (3 layers).

title: stuffed meat loaf
directions: Stir together ground beef, soup mix and egg.
Line bread pan with meat mixture.
(Leave some for top.)
Cook stuffing and put it in the lined pan.
Cover with leftover meat.
Cook in oven 45 minutes at 350°.

title: zabaione
directions: Place the egg yolks, sugar and warm water in a bowl over a saucepan of hot water.
Beat with a rotary whisk (not electric beater) until pale in color and frothy.
Whisk in the Marsala a little at a time and continue whisking over heat for 5 to 10 minutes until mixture becomes thick and foamy and holds its shape in a spoon.
Remove from the heat and spoon into tall wine glasses.
Serve immediately with ladyfingers.

title: pecan chewies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each.
Add flour, blend well.
Stir in vanilla and pecans.
Pour into greased 13 x 9 x 2 pan or glass casserole.
Best in pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Heat oven to 325°. Grease 9 x 13 pan. Layer 1/2 the Rice Krispies, sausage and cheese. Mix soup, milk and eggs. Pour over the layered ingredients. Top with the reserved Rice Krispies. Bake for 45 minutes. Cover and let set 10 minutes prior to serving. Serves 8 to 10.
Can make the day before and pop in oven in morning.

title: barbecue chicken topping
directions: Heat on stove.
Pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for about 1 1/4 hours.

title: friday casserole
directions: Melt margarine.
Add flour, onion, sauce, mustard, salt and pepper to make sauce.
Add milk and stir until thickened to make white sauce.
Combine noodles, peas and shrimp.
Combine white sauce and shrimp mix.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Freezes well before cooking.

title: white wine chicken
directions: Arrange chicken in large pan (1 layer).
Pour melted butter over chicken and sprinkle seasonings.
Cover with Swiss cheese. Mix soup and wine.
Pour over chicken.

title: school house peanut butter sandwiches
directions: Put peanut butter, karo syrup, and peach syrup in bowl and mix.
Spread on bread and enjoy.

title: caribbean fudge pie
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Beat margarine and sugar in a large bowl until fluffy. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Add chocolate, coffee and rum extract.
Mix well. Stir in flour and chopped nuts.
Pour into pie shell. Decorate top of pie with walnut halves.
Bake in lower third of oven for 25 minutes. Cool on wire rack.
Refrigerate
at least 1 hour.

title: frozen strawberry salad
directions: Beat cream cheese and sugar.
In another bowl, put pineapple, strawberries, nuts, bananas and Cool Whip.
Mix thoroughly, but gently.
Combine with cream cheese mixture and spoon into cupcake paper liners in muffin tins.
Freeze.

title: beef noodle casserole
directions: Brown onion and ground beef.
Drain off fat.
Combine mushroom soup, tomato soup, Worcestershire sauce and 1/2 can water.
Cook noodles as directed on package.
Drain off water.
In casserole dish mix soups, water, noodles, ground beef and onion mixture together.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts.

title: chex party mix
directions: Melt butter in 9 x 13-inch pan in preheated 250° oven, stir in seasonings.
Gradually add cereals, nuts and pretzels; stir to coat evenly.
Bake 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.
Spread on absorbent paper to cool.
Store in airtight container.

title: sweet potato pudding
directions: Beat together and pour into buttered pan.
Add 1 tablespoon butter on top before baking about 2 hours at 375°.
Serve with cream, either warm or cold.

title: pineapple-cheese christmas casserole
directions: Mix pineapple, juice and Cheddar cheese together.
Set aside. Mix sugar and flour together and add to pineapple and cheese mixture.
Spread in 8 x 11-inch or 9 x 12-inch dish.
Spread crackers over mixture.
Pour butter (oleo) over top of crackers. Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: dirt cake
directions: Make pudding according to directions.
Beat in softened cream cheese.
Layer cookies, pudding mixture and Cool Whip, starting and ending with cookies.

title: coconut-pecan frosting
directions: Combine milk, sugar, egg yolks, butter and vanilla.
Cook and stir over medium heat until thickened, about 12 minutes (use double boiler).
Remove from stove and add coconut.
Add pecans. Stir until thick enough to spread.
Makes 2 1/2 cups.
Can be used on German chocolate cake.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and cocoa together.
Add eggs and vanilla. mix well.
Add flour, coconut and nuts.
Beat 1 to 2 minutes. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: mrs. young's "no peek" stew
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
Mix all ingredients together (do not brown meat).
Cover and bake for 5 hours.
Serves 6.

title: oyster stew
directions: Heat butter until sizzling.
Add oysters, Worcestershire sauce, celery salt, salt, pepper and paprika.
Heat only until edges of oysters curl slightly.
Add milk and heat quickly but do not boil. Serve with a dash of paprika and a lump of butter in each bowl. Makes 4 servings.

title: italian vegetable soup
directions: In large saucepan, saute onions and garlic in butter or margarine for 3 minutes.
Add chicken broth, tomatoes, carrots, celery, cabbage, salt, thyme, basil and pepper; simmer for 15 minutes.
Serve in bowls topped with toast and sprinkled with cheese.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: orange sugar pecans
directions: In a small saucepan, combine sugar and milk.
Cook over medium heat to soft ball stage.
Stir occasionally.
Add butter and orange peel.
Stir to blend; add pecan halves.
Stir until all are coated.
Spread pecans on greased cookie sheet.
When coating is firm, gently break pecans apart.
Store in container.

title: kraut salad
directions: Boil vinegar and sugar for 5 minutes.
Pour over other ingredients and mix well, then chill.
Will keep in refrigerator for several days.

title: haystacks
directions: In top of a double boiler melt butterscotch bits.
Stir in chow mein noodles and peanuts.
Drop by spoonful onto waxed paper.

title: plum perfect parfait
directions: Rinse plums.
Slice, removing pits.
Measure 3 cups.
Combine cornstarch, sugar, and salt in saucepan.
Stir in plums, spices, and lemon juice.
Cover and bring to boil.
Simmer 8 to 10 minutes. Cool.
Layer with vanilla ice cream in parfait glasses.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: plain cake
directions: Mix all together and bake at 350°.
Makes layers or sheet cake.

title: crescent caramel roll swirl
directions: Melt butter. Coat bundt pan with 2 tablespoons of the melted butter. Sprinkle 3 tablespoons of the nuts into the pan. Boil rest of the nuts, brown sugar and water to boiling, stirring occasionally. Do not unroll the crescent rolls, but cut each can into 8 slices. Add 8 slices to pan. Spoon 1/2 of the sauce over the rolls. Repeat with the other 8 slices, and the rest of the sauce. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Cool 3 minutes and turn onto platter and serve.

title: fat-free meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Mold and bake in oven at 350° for approximately 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: barbecue beef
directions: In skillet, brown beef in shortening.
Pour off fat.
Add soup, 1/4 cup water, ketchup, mustard, garlic, Tabasco sauce and seasonings.
Cover and simmer 1 1/2 hours.
Add onions; cook 40 minutes more.
Add green pepper; cook 20 minutes longer or until tender.
Stir now and then.
Gradually blend 1/4 cup water into flour until smooth; slowly stir into stew.
Cook, stirring, until thickened.
Serve over rice, if desired.

title: coquille st. jacques
directions: Saute onion and 1 tablespoon margarine until soft.
Coat scallops with flour seasoned with salt and white pepper.
In a large skillet, saute the scallops in 2 tablespoons olive oil and 2 tablespoons margarine for 2 minutes.
Add basil, Vermouth, water and sauteed onions.
Simmer for 5 minutes, covered.
Pour into deep pie plate; sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and broil for 2 to 3 minutes, until brown.
Serve over white rice.

title: no-bake peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine peanut butter, margarine, light corn syrup, vanilla and salt; blend well.
Gradually stir in powdered sugar until creamy
consistency is reached.
Knead until smooth.
Add nuts. Pack into buttered 8-inch square pan.
When firm, cut in squares. Makes about 2 pounds.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Use 1 cup of boiling water to dissolve Jell-O.
Grind or chop cranberries and orange (rind included).
Add to Jell-O and sugar. Chill.

title: impossible broccoli pie
directions: Cook broccoli until separated.
Mix all ingredients together. Pour in a greased pan, casserole or 2 small pie plates (8-inch). Bake at 350° for 3/4 hour.

title: summer sausage
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Shape into 6 to 8-inch rolls, 1 1/2-inches in diameter.
Cover with foil and refrigerate for 24 hours.
Unwrap and cook at 300° for 1 hour.

title: peanut butter crackers
directions: Sandwich together two Ritz crackers with a generous amount of peanut butter.
Press together so peanut butter spreads to the edge.
Using tongs, dip crackers into melted candy coating.
Place on foil or waxed paper to harden.

title: strawberry surprise cake
directions: Mix in order listed.
Cook in 3 round or 1 oblong pan, well-greased and floured, at 350° until done.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all together and bake 40 minutes at 350° or until done. Ovens may vary. This is a very heavy and thick bread.

title: orangey carrots
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Place carrots in ungreased 1 1/2 or 2-quart casserole.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Bake, covered, for 50 to 60 minutes or until tender.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chicken breasts stuffed with crab
directions: Place chicken breasts between wax paper; pound gently with mallet until 1/4-inch thick.
Melt 2 tablespoons butter in skillet.
Blend 2 teaspoons flour, 1/4 teaspoon salt, pepper and milk.
Cook, stirring, until smooth.
Add crab, mushrooms and Parmesan cheese.
Spread mixture over chicken breasts.
Roll up tightly; secure with skewers.

title: pear cake
directions: In large bowl, cream butter and sugar together.
Add eggs, pears, cherries and nuts.
Sift together 3 times the cinnamon, nutmeg and flour.
Add to mixture alternately with buttermilk to which soda has been added.
Pour in well-greased Bundt or angel food pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: christmas sugar cookies
directions: Cream together sugar and shortening.
Add water, beaten eggs and vanilla.
Mix sifted dry ingredients; add to the mixture to form a stiff dough.
(More flour may be required if the eggs are large.)
Roll in small quantities to 1/8-inch thickness on a floured board.
Cut into rings like doughnuts, using two sizes of plastic cups.
Arrange both rings and holes on a greased baking sheet; decorate with sprinkled sugar.
Bake in a preheated 375° oven for 10 minutes.
Makes 8 dozen cookies.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Combine sugar with cocoa.
Add milk, margarine and corn syrup. Boil one minute.
Add confectioners sugar and vanilla.
Pour into greased 8 x 8-inch pan and cool.
Add nuts, if desired.

title: spanish fordhooks
directions: Prepare beans according to cooking directions; drain.
Brown onions and peppers in margarine; add tomatoes.
Simmer on low for 10 minutes.
Add cooked beans.
Sprinkle croutons on top and heat an additional 10 minutes.

title: easy and quick party punch
directions: In large punch bowl, mix lemonade and fruit punch; stir until well blended.
Top the punch with quart of sherbet.
Serve.

title: hearty potato salad
directions: Peel and slice potatoes while warm.
Fry bacon until crisp; add onion, celery and pickle and cook 3 minutes.
Combine water, vinegar, sugar, paprika and mustard.
Heat to boiling.
Add to bacon mixture.
Pour over sliced potatoes.
Add salt and pepper. Mix.

title: taco bake
directions: Brown hamburger meat; drain excess oil. Add taco seasoning as directed on pack. Spray 13 x 9 baking dish with Pam cooking spray. Take one tube of crescent rolls and line bottom of dish. Then add one layer of refried beans and one layer of meat. Then add the next tube of crescent rolls. Layer the beans and meat again and add your shredded cheese to the top. Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes. Take out of oven and let it cool. Top with sour cream.

title: cocktail wieners
directions: Mix cranberry sauce and mustard.
Add wieners to sauce. Simmer 15 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: cocktail meatballs
directions: Heat in saucepan before adding meatballs.
Can use immediately or keep on low for several hours.

title: split pea soup
directions: Bring water to a boil.
Add peas, salt, pepper, butter, celery, onion, carrots and ham bone.
Cover; cook slowly for 2 hours, stirring occasionally to prevent sticking.
Serves 6.

title: never-fail meringue
directions: Use clean, dry utensils that are free of grease.
Mix cornstarch with the 2 tablespoons cold water.
Add the 1/2 cup boiling water and cook, stirring constantly until the mixture thickens and is clear.
Remove from heat and allow the mixture to cool.
With electric mixer at high speed, beat egg whites until stiff.
With low speed, add the sugar, salt, cooled cornstarch mix.
Return to high speed and beat well.
Put on pie and bake at 350° until browned, 8 to 10 minutes.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Roll out and press around sides (crescent rolls).
Bake rolls at 350° for 12 minutes or until light brown.
Let rolls cool.
Mix together cream cheese, mayonnaise, Ranch dressing and dill weed; mix well.

title: carrot cake(rabbits would love this cake.)
directions: In a bowl, cream the oil and sugar.
Add eggs and beat well. Add carrots, nuts and dry ingredients.
Pour into a lightly greased tube or Bundt pan and bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour. When cooled, spread on frosting.

title: bing cherry-coca-cola salad(jackie brunson's)
directions: Drain juice from cherries and pineapple.
Heat juice to boiling point and pour over Jell-O.
Stir until dissolved.
Add cream cheese which has been softened to liquid.
Add Coca-Cola, cherries and pineapple. Congeal. Serve on lettuce with mayonnaise dressing. Serves 8 to 10.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix peanut butter and sugar together.
Melt chocolate bar and wax down.
Roll peanut butter mix into quarter size balls.
Dip in chocolate.
Place on wax paper.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well and pour into greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle 3/4 cup brown sugar and 1/2 cup nuts on top of batter.
Bake at 350° about 45 minutes.

title: impossible taco pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease pie plate.
Cook and stir beef and onion until brown; drain.
Stir in taco mix.
Spread in pie plate and top with green chilies.
Beat milk, baking mix and eggs until smooth.
Bake for 25 minutes.
Top with tomatoes and cheese.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes longer.
Serve with sour cream, chopped tomatoes and shredded lettuce.

title: bread stuffing for turkey
directions: Put 1/2 cup butter in a heavy frying pan.
Add onions and cook over low heat until soft.
Do not brown.
Mix together bread crumbs, salt, pepper, poultry seasoning, parsley and celery leaves.
Add onions and moisten with balance of butter melted in hot water.
Mix thoroughly and stuff the bird.

title: skillet cornbread
directions: Combine cornmeal, flour, salt and baking powder.
Combine beaten eggs and milk.
Stir into cornmeal mixture.
Mix well.
Put shortening into a 10-inch skillet and heat.
As soon as shortening is very hot, coat side of skillet with oil.
Add remaining shortening to cornbread mixture.
Spoon mixture into hot skillet and bake for about 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Yield:
12 servings.

title: graham cracker frosty bar
directions: Bring sugar, margarine, egg and milk or water to a boil; stir constantly.
Add nuts, coconut and graham crackers in boiling mixture.
Line cookie sheet with whole graham crackers and pour mixture over crackers.
Cover mixture with whole crackers.
Press lightly.

title: just-like wendy's frosty
directions: Blend in blender and refrigerate for 1 hour to harden a little.

title: strawberries and cake
directions: Break cake in small chunks.
Put in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Dissolve jello in 2 cups very hot water.
Add strawberries frozen to jello. Stir until jello starts to congeal.
Pour over cake and fold in Cool Whip.
Keep refrigerated.

title: broccoli cheese casserole
directions: Cook broccoli.
Drain well.
Place in 1 1/2-quart casserole. Blend soup, milk, salt and pepper.
Stir into broccoli.
Combine crumbs and butter and sprinkle on casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: eggs lorraine
directions: Melt margarine in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with 1/2 of cheese (1/4 pound).
Crack eggs on top of cheese (3 rows of 4).
Break yolks but do not mix.
Salt and pepper.
Add half and half.
Add the ham and remaining cheese.
Must set overnight.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: thin mint cookies*
directions: Melt semi-sweet chocolate over low heat or in microwave.
Add peppermint oil.
Dip crackers in chocolate and place on waxed paper to cool.

title: better than potato salad
directions: Cook rice according to package directions.
Chill.
Add mayonnaise, celery, onion, mustard and salt.
Mix well.
Chill and stir in eggs, radishes and cucumber before serving.

title: three cheese tuna casserole
directions: Prepare macaroni according to package directions; drain.
Heat soup, milk and cheeses together; stir until cheeses are melted. Combine macaroni, cheese sauce, vegetables, tuna, 1 cup French fried onions and seasonings.
Pour into a 2-quart baking dish. Bake, covered, in a 350° oven for 25 minutes or until heated thoroughly.
Top with remaining onions; bake uncovered for 5 minutes or until onions are golden brown.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: gooey butter cake
directions: Mix cake mix, 2 eggs and margarine.
Will be very stiff. Spread on ungreased cookie sheet with sides or an ungreased jelly roll pan.

title: pecan tarts(serves 36)
directions: Mix 3/4 stick oleo and cream cheese well.
Add flour; press a small piece of dough into small greased muffin cups.

title: cheese soup
directions: *Any variety:
such as carrots, peas, beans, broccoli, etc.

title: hush puppies
directions: Sift meal, baking powder and salt together.
Add oil, onion and juice and vinegar to dry ingredients.
Add beaten egg and enough milk to make a soft dough.
Drop by spoonfuls into deep fat heated to 375° to 400° for 4 to 5 minutes.
The addition of vinegar lessons the absorption of grease.

title: tessie's rice pudding
directions: Bring first three ingredients to a boil.
Add rice.
Lower flame to simmer and cook 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Beat together egg, cream, vanilla and Amaretto and add to the cooked rice.
Mix thoroughly.
Put into serving dish and let cool. Sprinkle with cinnamon and refrigerate.

title: fresh vegetable dip
directions: Mix together.
Let stand overnight in refrigerator.
Use on any vegetable.

title: tapioca jello dessert
directions: Cook water, tapioca pudding and jello together until thick, stirring constantly.
Cool in refrigerator.
Drain oranges and add to Cool Whip.
Add crushed pineapple and juice to Cool Whip. Combine Cool Whip mixture and jello mixture and refrigerate.

title: freda's brown edged cookies
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add egg, flour and baking powder.
Add vanilla. Drop by teaspoon far apart on greased cookie sheet. Bake in a 375° oven until lightly brown on edge. Cool slightly before removing from lightly greased cookie sheet.

title: jalapeno cheese dip
directions: Finely chop onion and peppers.
Grate cheese.
Mix onion, peppers, cheese, garlic, salt and mayonnaise.
Blend 3 minutes or until fluffy.
Will last up to 3 months in the refrigerator. Serve with tortilla chips or crackers.

title: cardamon flavored loaf
directions: * Pound seed first and then add to flour.
(You can also add currants or candied fruit, etc., into your flour.)

title: chicken bundles
directions: Beat in mixing bowl, cream cheese, milk, dill weed, salt and pepper until smooth.
Stir in chicken, celery and onions.
Unroll crescent roll dough and separate into 12 triangles.
Place on greased cookie sheet and press edges together.
Spoon 1/3 cup of chicken mixture into center of each rectangle.
Bring edges up to center and pinch to seal.
Brush with butter; sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Yields 6 servings.

title: fruit and honey dip
directions: Beat cream cheese, marshmallow cream, honey and cinnamon until smooth.
Serve with fruit for dipping.

title: chili
directions: Brown and drain meat.
Mix remaining ingredients and cook until thick.

title: yankee noodle bake(great for those on a tight budget!)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown hot dogs and cook onions in butter until tender.
Combine noodles, soup, water and mustard in greased casserole dish.
Add hot dogs and onions; mix well.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake for 25 minutes.
Serves 3.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together and cook until peanuts start to pop.
Add baking soda. Stir well.
Pour onto buttered cookie sheet.
Let cool. Break into pieces.

title: harvest salad
directions: Mix well; fill up and pour into tomatoes.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix together pudding, Cool Whip and cottage cheese.
Fold in drained fruit and marshmallows.
Chill well.

title: lisa's taco chicken
directions: Mix taco seasoning and flour.
Coat chicken and fry in skillet with a little oil.
Turn once.

title: pickled eggs
directions: Simmer all ingredients, except eggs, uncovered for ten minutes.
Peel hard-cooked eggs and put them in a one-quart glass jar, loosely, so that the pickling solution can circulate freely. Pour hot mixture over eggs, seal and refrigerate.
The pickling process takes several days.

title: chocolate mint brownies
directions: Melt chips and butter over boiling water.
Pour over frosted brownies.
Let set.

title: coconut kisses
directions: Heat oven to 325°. Line cookie pans with foil and butter lightly. Mix coconut, milk and flavorings with wooden spoon. Drop onto cookie pans with teaspoon. Bake 8 to 10 minutes, until golden brown on top. Makes 30.

title: blackberry and apple pie
directions: Combine tapioca, sugar, salt, berries and apples.
Add lemon juice; let stand about 15 minutes.
Put in pie crust, then top with butter and top crust.
Bake at 425° for 55 minutes, or until syrup boils with heavy bubbles that do not burst.

title: cowboy cookies
directions: Cream sugars, eggs and vanilla until fluffy.
Stir dry ingredients and stir in.
Add oatmeal, chocolate chips and nuts. Drop by teaspoonfuls on a cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.
Also great with butterscotch chips added.

title: manicotti
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix cottage cheese, Mozzarella, 1/3 cup Parmesan cheese, eggs, salt, pepper and butter.
Pour a thin layer of tomato sauce into bottom of a large shallow baking dish.
Spoon some of the cheese filling into each manicotti and place in a single layer over sauce.
Pour remaining sauce over manicotti and sprinkle with the 1/4 cup Parmesan.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes. Serves 5 to 6.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Alternating, layer each vegetable in a greased casserole. Place hamburger around on top.
Mix soups together and pour over hamburger.
Cover and bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter; add eggs.
Beat until creamy.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add slowly with milk to creamy mixture. Add vanilla and stir in the rhubarb.
Put topping on cake after batter is in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in casserole dish.
Cook on 350° about 30 minutes or until brown.

title: savory squash
directions: Cook the squash in boiling water until tender; drain and mash. Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Pour into a greased baking dish.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Beat in eggs.
Stir in remaining pie ingredients, blending well.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until set.

title: scalloped potatoes and vegetables
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine potatoes and onions in a large saucepan and parboil until almost tender.
Drain and arrange in a shallow baking dish.
Distribute tomatoes and mushrooms over the potatoes; dot with butter and top with cheese and then crumbs. Bake, uncovered, 30 minutes, or until potatoes are tender and juices have mostly evaporated.
Serves 8.

title: chocolate chip nut pumpkin bread
directions: Cream sugar and oil together.
Add eggs and pumpkin; mix well. Add dry ingredients alternately with water.
Stir in chocolate chips and pecan pieces.
Pour into two well-greased and floured 9 x 5-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until tests done.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Remove from pan to cool.

title: spinach roll-ups
directions: Drain and press moisture from spinach.
Mix with next five ingredients.
Spread on flour tortillas.
Roll up tortillas, jelly roll fashion.
Wrap individually in plastic wrap and let set in refrigerator several hours or overnight.
Slice and serve.

title: baked rabbit milano
directions: Marinate rabbit in the refrigerator in a mixture of the next 7 ingredients overnight.
Cut into serving size pieces.
Cover each piece with a bacon slice, sprinkle with sage, brown in oil and bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: crunchy pops
directions: Cut the banana in half; put it on a popsicle stick.
Put in the freezer for an hour or more.
Spread honey on each pop with a knife.
Roll in the Rice Krispies.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Layer in baking dish in order.
Mix soups and water together. Salt and pepper to taste.
Cover with foil and bake 2 to 2 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: asparagus pea casserole
directions: Layer uncooked peas, asparagus, eggs, soup and butter in Pyrex dish.
Put cracker crumbs on top.
Cook at 350° until thoroughly hot.

title: grandma's favorite potato salad
directions: Scrub and cook potatoes until well done, but not mushy.
Best if cooked "in jackets".
Cool and slice (do not cube).
Add onion and parsley.
Whisk oil, vinegar, salt, pepper and garlic.
Pour over potatoes in onion and turn over lightly.
Chill and serve.

title: pineapple jello salad
directions: In a 9 x 9 x 2-inch plastic container, make jello according to package.
Add pineapple (with juice) and cottage cheese.
Stir until well mixed.
Chill for 15 to 30 minutes or until slightly jelled.
Stir in Cool Whip.
Refrigerate until well set (about 2 hours).
Makes 16 to 20 servings.
Calories:
58, Protein:
3.86 g, carbohydrate:
6.3 g, total fat:
1.85 g, sodium:

title: strawberry pie
directions: Cook about 5 minutes.
Cool slightly.
Pour over arranged strawberries in precooked pie shell.
Top with whipped cream.

title: easy pineapple dessert
directions: In glass casserole dish, layer pineapple and juice, then yellow cake mix, then cut up oleo over top of cake mix.
Next add chopped nuts. Bake at 325° to 350° for 1 hour.
Serve with Cool Whip.

title: mozzarella meat pie
directions: Brown onion, celery, pepper, mushrooms and ground beef.
Then drain.
Add tomato paste, 1/2 cheese and seasonings.
Mix well. Place crescent rolls in 9-inch pie plate, pressing together to form a crust.
Flute edge.
Fill with meat mixture.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes or until crust is golden brown.

title: parsley-lemon splash
directions: Whisk all ingredients together.
Chill 30 minutes.
Ready to serve.

title: potato casserole
directions: Butter dish.
Place hash browns in buttered dish.
Mix sour cream, onion, 3/4 cup butter, salt, pepper, cheese and soup.
Pour over hash browns.
Sprinkle corn flakes on top and pour 1/4 cup butter on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: bread
directions: Mix well the first 4 ingredients and let sit at least 1 hour. Add the remaining ingredients.
Let rise.
Divide in 3 loaves. Put in loaf pans and let rise until doubled.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: beat 'n eat frosting
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients in a small deep bowl.
Add boiling water and beat until stiff peaks.
Spread between layers and on top and sides of cake.
Spread with coconut.
It makes 3 cups. Also good without the coconut and good base for decorating.

title: yummy cake
directions: Cream oil and sugar; add beaten eggs.
Sift dry ingredients and add alternately with apples.
Add nuts and vanilla.
Mix. Bake at 300° for about 40 minutes.
Egg White Frosting recommended.

title: masi goring
directions: Cook rice; cool or chill.
Saute onions in butter.
Add beef and rice; brown lightly.
Add celery leaves, seasonings and shrimp.
Cook only long enough to heat.

title: carrot soup
directions: Put ingredients into blender or food processor.
Chop until creamy.
Pour into saucepan and heat well.

title: hermits
directions: Mix shortening, sugar, egg and molasses together thoroughly. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Mix raisins and nuts last.
Use an ungreased jelly roll pan.
Shape into sausage-like rolls; 2 or 3 strips.
Press down.
Bake at 375° for 9 to 10 minutes.
Cracks may make them appear uncooked, but remove and cool.
Cut into bars.
Sprinkle granulated sugar on top while they are still hot.

title: angel buns
directions: Dissolve yeast and sugar in warm water in medium bowl.
Mix in baking mix and milk until dough forms.
Gently smooth into ball on surface dusted with baking mix.
Knead 10 times.
Roll 1/2 inch thick.
Cut with 2-inch biscuit cutters dipped in baking mix.

title: lemon pie
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients together well.
Pour into pie shells and let set in refrigerator overnight.

title: karen's lasagna
directions: Cook noodles in salted water; drain.
Brown ground beef; drain.
Mix ground beef with spaghetti sauce (spices of your choice may be added).

title: hawaiian wedding cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
If batter is dry, add more liquid.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes in a 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: frangainbo pirpiri (broiled marinated chicken)(mozambique)
directions: Combine the
chilies,
garlic and 1/2 cup of the oil in the jar
of
an electric blender and blend at high speed until the seasonings	are
thoroughly pulverized.
Pour the mixture into a large,
shallow
glass
baking
dish
and
stir in the remaining 1/2
cup
of oil, the lemon juice and the salt.
(To make the marinade
by hand, pound the chilies and garlic to a paste with a mortar and pestle or in a bowl with the back of a spoon. Gradually beat in the oil, lemon juice and salt.)

title: lasagne
directions: Brown meat slowly.
Pour off excess fat.
Add next 3 ingredients.
Cover and simmer 40 minutes.
Cook noodles in boiling water until tender.
Drain and rinse in cold water.
Place half the noodles in an 11 1/2 x 7 1/2 x 1 1/2-inch baking pan.
Cover with 1/3 of the sauce.
Add half the Mozzarella and half the cottage cheese.
Repeat layers, ending with sauce.
Top with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until it bubbles. Let stand 15 minutes to set.
Cut into squares.

title: garden vegetable pasta
directions: Cook pasta in a large pot of boiling water about 5 minutes. Before the pasta is done, stir in frozen vegetables.
While this cooks, in a large bowl, mix low-fat sour cream with packet of garden vegetable party dip mix.
Drain pasta and vegetables well, then add to the sour cream mixture and toss well to mix.
Serve with grated Parmesan cheese.
Serves 4.

title: buck eyes
directions: Mix Rice Krispies and peanut butter, add melted butter. Gradually add powdered sugar, mixing well each time. Roll in melted chocolate and place on waxed paper until cool.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Combine sugar,	cocoa,	butter	and
milk
in
a
large saucepan.
Bring to
a
boil
over	medium	heat
and boil for exactly 2
minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add remaining ingredients (it
helps	to pre-measure before beginning the recipe). Stir well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto cookie sheets lined with waxed paper.
Chill for 10 minutes in refrigerator and serve.

title: cornbread sausage
directions: Heat oven to 350°F.
Grease 3-quart casserole dish.
Cut sausage patties into pieces.
