Melt 1 Tablespoon of margarine in large skillet over medium-high heat, add walnuts;
cook and stir until lightly browned.
Remove nuts from skillet.
Melt the remaining margarine in skillet.
Add celery and onion;
cook until tender.
Toss together all ingredients except juice and water in a large bowl.
Add juice and water;
stir together.
Spoon into casserole dish and cover.
Bake 1 hour or until hot.

title: party flavored bread strips
directions: Spread or dot butter on bread slices.
Sprinkle soup mix on top of buttered bread.
Cut bread into strips.
Bake for 1 hour at 225°.
(Will keep in tin indefinitely.)

title: venison loaf
directions: In an 8-inch skillet, over medium heat in hot butter, cook onion and celery until tender (about 5 minutes).
Meanwhile, in large bowl, beat eggs slightly.
Stir in bread crumbs, milk, salt and thyme leaves.
Add venison, ground beef and onion mixture. Mix well.
Spoon mixture into a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake meat loaf in oven at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Pour off pan juice.
Serve hot or cold.
Makes 10 servings.

title: sparkling christmas punch
directions: Combine all ingredients except for ginger ale.
Mix well until sugar and Kool-Aid are dissolved.
Add ginger ale to taste. Decorate punch with an ice ring, if desired, by freezing some of the concentrate juice.

title: broccoli-cauliflower salad
directions: Separate broccoli and cauliflower into small pieces.
Add cucumber, onion and dressing made from mayonnaise and sour cream. Chill.
Right before serving, add chopped tomato or cherry tomatoes, cut in halves.
Sprinkle with bacon bits.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Trim crusts from bread and cut into cubes.
Beat eggs and milk; add seasonings.
Lightly butter a 2 quart casserole dish. Line bottom with one half of the bread cubes and sprinkle with 1/3 of the cheese.
Repeat cheese and bread layers, then pour milk and egg mixture over all.

title: crazy chocolate cake
directions: Place all ingredients in a mixing bowl, but do not stir until last ingredient is added. Beat well. Bake at 350° until done.

title: cracker brittle
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Line 15 x 10-inch jelly roll pan with foil. Arrange crackers over bottom of prepared pan.
In small saucepan, combine butter and sugar.
Bring to boil over medium heat; boil 2 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat; pour and spread evenly over crackers.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 18 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool completely.
Break into pieces.
Makes 36 servings.

title: aunt joan's cheese cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix crumbs with 1/4 cup sugar and butter in bowl.
Press mixture in bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan.
Mix cream cheese and remaining cup of sugar until smooth.
Add eggs, 1 at a time, beating just to blend after each addition.
Mix in vanilla.
Fold in sour cream thoroughly.
Pour batter into prepared pan.
Set cheese cake on center rack.
Fill small pan with water and place on bottom rack.
Bake 30 minutes, turn off oven and leave in oven for 1 hour.
Do not open door.
Remove and let cool.

title: oat cakes
directions: Combine rolled oats, flour, sugar, salt and soda.
Work in margarine as if in pastry.
Moisten with water.
Roll them with rolled oats on board.
I use cookie cutter for holidays or squares or circles for every day.
Bake in oven at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: spanish chicken bake
directions: Shake chicken with flour in plastic bag to coat well.
Brown a few pieces at a time in oil in large skillet.
Drain on paper toweling.

title: pork chops casserole
directions: Cover bottom of 8 x 13-inch dish with uncooked rice.
Combine soup and water.
Pour over rice; salt and pepper pork chops and lay on top of rice.
Bake covered at 300° for about 1 1/2 hours.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together thoroughly.
Stir in sour milk and banana.
Sift together next four ingredients and stir in. Blend in chopped nuts.
Pour into well-greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Let stand 20 minutes before baking.
Bake until it tests done in a 350° oven for 50 to 60 minutes.
Serve warm or cold.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: In a 13 x 9-inch baking dish, melt oleo.
Add brown sugar and drained pineapple.
Mix cake mix according to directions on box. Pour over ingredients in baking dish; bake at 350° for 1/2 hour. Immediately turn into a large container.
I use a large cookie sheet.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Mix into batter and pour in 9 x 12-inch pan.
Then put peaches over batter.
Bake at 350° until brown.
You may substitute peaches with any other fruit.

title: sin
directions: Melt oleo and mix with flour.
Pack in bottom of 8 x 8-inch Pyrex dish.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup pecans.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Let cool.
Mix cream cheese, sugar and 1/2 carton Cool Whip.
Melt this in microwave for a few minutes.
Beat well and spread over first layer.
Mix the chocolate pudding with milk. Mix this well with mixer and spread on second layer.
Spread third layer well with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with pecans, then refrigerate.

title: easy chicken pie
directions: Mix together chicken, chicken soup, mushroom soup, chicken broth, salt and pepper in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Dot top with butter.
Bake for 10 minutes at 400°.
Add biscuits to top; bake until done at 450°.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Cream the cheese; add lemon juice and mayonnaise.
Cut shrimp into small pieces.
Add shrimp, celery and green onion to cheese. Mix well.
Let stand in refrigerator at least 2 hours.

title: chocolate angel pie
directions: In a double boiler over hot, not boiling water, combine chocolate, water, egg yolks, sugar and salt.
Cook until chocolate melts and mixture is very thick and mounds when dropped from a spoon, about 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and set aside.
Beat cream and vanilla until soft peaks form. With a wire whisk, gently fold chocolate mixture into whipped cream mixture.
Spoon mixture into meringue shell.
Refrigerate until filling is set, about 4 hours.

title: butter cream ribbon chocolate fudge cake
directions: Combine cream cheese, 1 egg and 1/4 cup sugar in a medium mixing bowl; beat at high speed of an electric mixer until smooth. Gradually add 3 tablespoons milk and next 3 ingredients, beating well.
Set aside.
Place chocolate squares in top of a double boiler; bring water to a boil.
Reduce heat to low; cook until chocolate melts, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat and let cool.
Cream 1/2 cup butter, gradually add 2 cups sugar, beating well at medium speed.
Add 2 eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Combine flour, baking powder, soda and salt; stir well.
Add flour mixture to creamed mixture alternately with 1 1/3 cups milk, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Mix after each addition.
Stir in melted chocolate and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Spread half of chocolate batter in a greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Spoon reserved cream cheese mixture evenly over chocolate batter; top with remaining half of chocolate batter.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Let cool completely in pan on a wire rack.
Spread frosting over cake.
Yield: 15 servings.

title: grandmama's (zora's) sugar cookies
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, cream and vanilla.
Stir together flour and baking powder, then mix rest of ingredients.

title: cajun chicken strips
directions: In a large resealable plastic bag, combine the first 6 ingredients. Cut the chicken into 1/2-inch strips and add to the bag, one-half at a time. Shake bag to coat. In a large skillet, cook chicken in butter for 8 to 10 minutes or until the juices run clear. Garnish with parsley and peppers, if desired. Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: jay's steak and sauce
directions: Brown steak in butter in large skillet. Add onions, mushrooms and garlic in the amounts your family likes and cook until tender.

title: clam dip
directions: Drain juice from clams; add to softened cream cheese.
Add all other ingredients.
Heat mixture over boiling water and serve at once.
It is nice served in chafing dish.
Yields about 1 cupful.

title: party potato casserole
directions: Bake potatoes.
Scoop potato out of shell when cool enough to handle.
Discard shell.
Leave potatoes chunky, do not mash.
Add sour cream, chives, salt, pepper, 1/2 cheese and milk.
Add enough milk to make mixture soft, but not soupy; mix ingredients lightly.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix together.
Roll into small balls.
Space 2 inches apart on baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Can be frozen for later use prior to baking.

title: yellow cake dream
directions: Bake cake as directed and cool.
Split both layers and fill with cooked pudding.
Put layers together and frost with 7 Minute Icing.

title: apricot-pineapple salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water in saucepan.
Add cream cheese; stir over low flame until completely dissolved.
Add crushed pineapple and cold water.
Allow to set until quite firm.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Allow to set for several hours or overnight.

title: celery scalloped potatoes
directions: Put potatoes in a greased casserole dish and add salt and pepper.
Combine the soup, milk, water and cheese together in a saucepan and heat until cheese is melted.
Mix well with potatoes and bake at 400° for about 1 hour.
Cover for first part of cooking and then remove cover so it can brown.

title: down home sausage and rice
directions: Crumble sausage in skillet and saute until brown.
Add onions, celery, bell pepper and saute lightly.
Add salt and pepper and water; bring to a boil.
Add rice; stir in well.
Cover and remove from heat.
Let set for 5 minutes fluff with fork and serve.

title: holiday casserole
directions: Prepare macaroni according to directions on package; drain. Combine soup, milk and cheese until cheese is melted.
Mix macaroni, cheese sauce, green pepper, onion and black pepper. Pour into a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Arrange luncheon meat on top of casserole.
Bake in a 325° oven for 30 minutes.

title: potato cheese soup
directions: Cook first nine ingredients until potatoes are done.
Mash potatoes, add cream, cheese and pepperoni.
Stir until cheese is melted.

title: pan cream puffs
directions: Boil water and oleo.
Add flour all at once.
Remove from heat.
Beat in one egg at a time.
Spread on cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Do not open oven during baking time.

title: wonder frosting
directions: Blend flour and milk. Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens; cool. Cream the shortening, butter and sugar until fluffy. Add vanilla and salt.
Beat in flour mixture in portions until soft and fluffy with electric mixer.

title: cheese bread
directions: Cube the cheese and butter; keep cold.
Mix together the eggs, buttermilk, chilies and Bisquick.
Fold in the cubes of cheese and butter.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Cut into squares and serve warm.

title: oatmeal cookies(diabetic)
directions: Measure oats into a mixing bowl.
Stir in melted butter and mix well.
Blend in eggs and sweetener.
Add dry ingredients alternately with milk and vanilla.
Add raisins.
Drop by level teaspoons onto greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 72 cookies.
Two cookies contain 70 calories and equals 1 starch exchange.

title: barbecups
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
In large skillet, brown beef; drain fat. Add barbecue sauce, brown sugar and onions.
Separate dough into biscuits.
Place each biscuit in an ungreased muffin cup, pressing dough up sides to edges of cup.
Spoon meat into cups.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes, until golden brown.
Sprinkle cheese over top.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: chocolate heath dessert
directions: Use an oblong pan and line with 1 package ladyfingers.
Whip the whipping cream and fold in crumbled Heath bars.
Use 1/2 of mixture and lay over ladyfingers.
Then layer the other package of ladyfingers and rest of cream mixture.
Top with shaved chocolate. Chill and serve.

title: pochero
directions: Cut the chicken and pork into serving pieces.
Bring to a boil and simmer with ham and chorizos until tender.
Season with salt. Remove meat from casserole and use meat stock to boil in cabbage and potatoes.
Cook bananas separately.

title: red sherbet smash
directions: Combine all but the sherbet and chill.
Just before serving, float small scoops of sherbet on top.
Garnish with lemon slices.

title: pear honey
directions: Wash, peel and core pears.
Slice before measuring.
Put through a food chopper, using fine blade.
Combine pears and pineapple.
Add lemon rind and juice.
Add sugar and cook over slow heat, stirring frequently.
Cook for 20 minutes.
Pour into jars and seal.
Process in boiling water bath for 15 minutes. Yields 4 pints.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain fruits; mix sour cream and marshmallows and nuts.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix all together. Bake for 15 minutes at 425°.
Start topping about 5 minutes before potato mixture is done.

title: apple burritos
directions: Place pie filling in tortillas; roll in burrito fashion and place in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix remaining ingredients, reserving 1/2 cup sugar and cinnamon.
Bring to a boil and pour over burritos.
Sprinkle with the remaining sugar and cinnamon mixture. Bake for 45 minutes in a 350° oven.
Baste burritos with the juice to keep moist during cooking time.

title: blueberry ice cream muffins
directions: Combine flour and ice cream in bowl.
Stir until just moistened.
Fold in blueberries.
Fill paper-lined muffin cups 1/2 full.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Makes 12 servings.

title: pork chop dinner
directions: Place pork chop in center of 1 piece of foil; salt and pepper. Next, place onion slices, then place the potato and carrot on top.
Fold the foil so you can fold the ends together and down. Place in oven on a cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 1 hour. Prepare one for each individual person.

title: fried chicken
directions: Cut up chicken, wash and pat dry.
Combine flour, dry mustard and garlic powder.
(I use a plastic bag to dredge chicken in.) Dip chicken in buttermilk and then in flour mixture.
Brown in oil or fat of your choice.
Place browned chicken in shallow roaster or pan.
Bake in 350° oven until fork-tender.

title: hot slaw
directions: Shred cabbage.
Place in large crock in layers, first one of cabbage and then onion until both are used up.
Cover with sugar. Make dressing of vinegar, salt, celery salt, mustard and oil. Bring to a boil.
Pour sauce while hot over cabbage and place in refrigerator for 3 hours.
Remove and toss.
Return to refrigerator.
Keeps indefinitely.

title: shortcut banana cream pie
directions: In a small pan over low heat, stir oleo, sugar and cinnamon until the bubbles form.
Remove from heat.
Mix in crumbs.
Press evenly in a 9-inch pie pan to form the crust. Chill.

title: dump cake
directions: Drain pineapple; spread in bottom of pan and drop cherry pie filling on top.
Spread cake mix on top of that.
Melt stick of butter and pour over cake mix, then cover all with coconut.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: sloppy toms
directions: Combine turkey, garlic, onion, pepper and celery in a large skillet.
Cook, stirring until turkey is brown.
Add remaining ingredients and cook 10 minutes.

title: no cook fruit cake
directions: Melt marshmallows in milk.
Pour over the rest of ingredients and mix well.
Pack in tube pan.
Let set for a few days.
This cake will keep for a year or longer in a tightly closed container in freezer or refrigerator.

title: caramel corn
directions: Combine all ingredients, except popcorn and baking soda. Bring to a boil for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in baking soda.
Put popped popcorn in paper bag and pour syrup over.
Stir and shake.
Then put in microwave for 1 1/2 minutes.
Remove and shake.
Then put in microwave for 1 1/2 minutes more.
Let cool in pan, then eat.

title: strawberry jello mold
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in the 1 cup of boiling water.
Add berries and juice, drained pineapple, bananas and nuts.
Mix well.
Pour half of mixture into 10 x 8-inch dish (or Bundt pan).
Refrigerate until firm.
Spread sour cream over it and cover with remaining Jell-O mixture.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: rachel's chewy oatmeal cookies
directions: In a bowl, sift together the flour, soda, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg. Add shortening, sugar, eggs and vanilla; beat until smooth. Stir in oats and raisins.
Drop by heaping teaspoonful onto greased cookie sheet. Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 3 to 3 1/2 dozen.

title: texas style jambalya
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In large skillet, heat oil; add onion, pepper and celery.
Cook 5 to 7 minutes, stirring occasionally. Add garlic, rice and meats.
Cook 2 to 3 minutes to coat rice, stirring frequently.
Add all other ingredients.
Heat to a boil. Pour into 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Cover tightly with foil; place in oven.
Bake 18 to 20 minutes until rice is tender and liquid absorbed.
Let sit for 10 minutes before serving.
Makes 6 servings.

title: honey-mustard dressing
directions: Combine mayonnaise and honey and mix well.
Add mustard, a little at a time, and taste.
Keep adding mustard until it is the way you like it.
Put in jar, cover and refrigerate.
Can be kept indefinitely.
Great on sandwiches, with chicken nuggets and as a salad dressing.

title: four layer lemon cheesecake
directions: Melt oleo.
Stir in flour and pecans.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish.
Bake for 30 minutes at 325°.
Let cool.

title: frozen daiquiris
directions: Makes 24 ounce batch; can be doubled.
Freeze and spoon out to serve.

title: carrot and apple casserole
directions: Clean and slice carrots into 1-inch diagonal pieces and cook until barely tender.
Drain.
Mix with apple pie filling and pineapple.
Spread mixture in large casserole dish that has been sprayed with Pam.
Sprinkle with brown sugar.
Dot with butter and sprinkle lightly with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Makes a nice accompaniment to ham.

title: carrot casserole
directions: *It is ok to use some of the cooking liquid, maybe about 1/2 cup.

title: easy golden mushroom chicken
directions: Sprinkle chicken breasts with salt, pepper and paprika. Place in	a baking dish, skin side up.
Mix soup with 1/2 can water and pour over chicken.	Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until browned.
May serve over rice.

title: stir-fry sauce
directions: Dissolve bouillon cube in water.
Add soy sauce, cornstarch, sugar and garlic powder.
Mix well.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Cook chicken and remove from bones. Place meat in a 13 x 9-inch buttered dish.
Mix soup and sour cream.
Pour over chicken.
Crush crackers and combine with poppy seed.
Sprinkle over mixture. Melt margarine and pour over top.
Cook 30 to 40 minutes at 350° until bubbly.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Press in a 9 x 12-inch pan and bake at 400° for 8 minutes.

title: "captain jim's" hush puppies
directions: Mix all dry ingredients except baking soda.
Combine baking soda and buttermilk.
Add to dry ingredients with beaten eggs and chopped onions.
Add melted margarine; mix well.
Drop by spoonfuls into hot oil.
Fry until golden brown.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and rice by directions.
Then mix all ingredients in a casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: glazed walnuts
directions: Bring sugar and sour cream to boil. Boil for 5 minutes. Add vanilla; mix well. Stir in walnuts. Pour onto waxed paper. Separate.

title: chicken cheese ball
directions: Let cream cheese stand to get soft.
Mix together all ingredients and roll in nuts.

title: zucchini pickles
directions: Wash zucchini thoroughly using a vegetable brush and drain. Trim ends and slice 1/8 and 1/4-inch slices.
Add onion, garlic and salt.
Mix thoroughly.
Cover with ice and let stand for 3 hours.
Drain thoroughly and remove garlic cloves.

title: chocolate pie filling
directions: Heat milk, sugar and butter.
Mix flour and cocoa together. Slowly add milk, egg yolk and vanilla to hot mixture.
Cook until thick, beating a little to smooth.
Pour into baked pie shell.

title: coco lopez coconut cake
directions: Bake cake as directed on box.
While cake is baking, mix Coco Lopez and Eagle Brand milk together.
When cake is done, remove and punch holes in cake.
Pour the Coco Lopez and Eagle Brand milk mixture over the cake.
When cake is completely cooled, spread whipped cream on top, then sprinkle coconut over it; refrigerate.

title: caramel crispie bars
directions: Stir in Rice Krispies and peanuts.
Press in well-buttered 12 x 8-inch baking dish.
Place chocolate chips, shortening and peanut butter in 2-cup glass measuring cup.
Microwave at 50% for 2 to 4 minutes or until chocolate chips are soft; blend well.
Spread this topping over cereal mixture.
Cut into bars when cool.

title: quick and easy chicken pie
directions: Debone chicken and place in casserole dish.
Add all canned goods and mix well.
Smooth evenly in pan.
Mix last 3 ingredients with mixer and pour over chicken and vegetables.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: barbecued beef patties
directions: Moisten bread crumbs in milk.
Combine with meat, salt, pepper and onion. Shape into 4 or 5 patties and place in a dish.
Cover with remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chess pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well and pour into deep dish pie shell and bake at 325°
for 45 minutes.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Mix spaghetti, margarine, Parmesan cheese and eggs.
Pour into 1 1/2 quart casserole dish pushing spaghetti up on side and bottom like a crust.
Put cottage cheese on the bottom of crust (2nd layer).
Brown beef and drain.
Add onion and green pepper, tomatoes, paste, sugar and spices.
Simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
Pour on top of cottage cheese.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Cover top with grated cheese and return to oven until melted.
Serve with garlic bread and salad.

title: country steak
directions: Brown steak in skillet on both sides, then place in casserole dish.
Mix soup and milk in skillet with meat drippings. After blended together well, pour over meat.
Bake in oven at 300° for 1 hour.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Melt butter in a big bowl in microwave.
Add sugar and milk. Stir.
Microwave for 8 minutes, stirring every 3 minutes.
Add marshmallows, chips, walnuts and vanilla.
Stir well.
Turn into an 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan lined with foil and buttered.
Score while warm. Cool on counter and then put in refrigerator and chill 1 to 2 hours.

title: veggie-beef medley
directions: Season beef with salt and pepper.
In a large skillet, over high heat, heat oil.
Add beef and garlic to skillet; cook, stirring constantly, until beef is brown.
Add pepper, mushrooms, zucchini, corn and onion.
Stir-fry 3 to 4 minutes or until vegetables are tender-crisp.
Stir in rice; heat through.

title: easy pasta salad
directions: Cook rotini until tender.
Add carrots last minute or so of cooking.
Cool; toss rest of ingredients in and pour dressing over.
Toss again.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Let chill for at least 1 hour before serving.
Add chopped basil as garnish.

title: branhams (hot) slaw
directions: Makes 8 to 10 small servings.

title: summer coolers
directions: Place banana and peanut butter in a blender.
Mix until smooth. Slowly add ice cream, then milk.
Mix until smooth.
Serves 2.

title: spice cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix all ingredients.
Drop dough by rounded teaspoonfuls about 2 inches apart onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake until light brown, 12 to 15 minutes.
Immediately remove from cookie sheet.
Makes about 2 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: fried okra patties
directions: Mix well; drop by tablespoon into skillet with hot oil. Flatten; cook until brown.
Serve hot.

title: baked potatoes filled with vegetables
directions: Bake potatoes until done.
Melt butter; stir in flour and milk.
Add salt, cheese, peas, carrots and peppers.
Cut the potatoes lengthwise into halves.
Remove the pulp without breaking the skin.
Mash the pulp and add it to the vegetable mixture. Season with paprika.
Fill the shells with mixture.
Top with bread crumbs browned in butter.
Place the potatoes in oven at 400° until the tops are brown.
Goes great with lamb chops or ham.

title: breakfast sausage casserole
directions: Cook sausage over medium heat until done, stirring to crumble well.
Drain sausage on paper towel, set aside.
Spread each side of bread with butter, cut into cubes in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with sausage and top with cheese.
Combine remaining ingredients. Beat well and pour over mixture in pan.
Chill at least 8 hours. Remove from refrigerator and bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes. Serves 12 or 13.

title: acorn squash delight
directions: Cut squash in half; remove seeds.
Put 1 tablespoon butter,
1 teaspoon sugar and 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon in each squash half. Place squash, cut side up, in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Pour water into dish and cover.
Bake at 400° for about 45 minutes or until squash is tender.
Serves 4.

title: beef-barley soup
directions: In a large soup pot, heat the oil.
Add beef; cook until browned.
Add 8 cups of water; bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer 1 hour, or until meat is tender.
Remove meat; shred into small pieces.
Dissolve bouillon in hot water.
Add bouillon, tomatoes, carrots, onion, celery, barley, parsley, shredded meat, salt and pepper.
Cover; simmer for 1 1/2 to 2 hours, or until vegetables are tender.
Serves 8.

title: party oyster crackers
directions: Mix all dry ingredients (except crackers).
Shake over crackers in a large roasting pan (this makes it easier to stir). Pour oil over crackers and stir well to mix.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes, stirring twice.
Cool completely before storing in an airtight container.

title: orange spread
directions: Cream together butter, orange juice, sugar and orange rind. Add spices.
Store in refrigerator.

title: sherbet punch
directions: Mix Kool-Aid and sugar with 2 quarts of water.
Add sherbet and pour 7-Up over sherbet.

title: oven baked potatoes
directions: Heat oven
to
Put
all	ingredients
in a large plastic bag.
Shake
well until coated.
Put in shallow baking dish and bake, uncovered, stirring occasionally for 40 minutes or until browned.

title: fruited cream cheese dip
directions: Beat cream cheese at medium speed of an electric mixer until creamy.
Add next 4 ingredients, mixing until light and fluffy. Spoon into serving dish and garnish with a strawberry fan, if desired.
Serve with fresh fruit.
Yields 1 1/3 cups.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add eggs one at a time.
Alternate adding flour and sour cream.
(Mix soda with last tablespoon sour cream.)
Add flavoring.
Bake 1 hour and 25 minutes at 325°.

title: chicken cordon bleu
directions: Pound chicken with a meat mallet to 1/4 inch thickness. Sprinkle each piece with 1 teaspoon of the parsley.
Top each with 1 slice cheese and 1/2 slice ham.
Roll up tightly; secure with wooden picks.
Mix mayonnaise and water in a shallow dish.
Roll chicken in mayonnaise mixture, then in bread crumbs to coat. Place in a greased baking pan.
Bake in a preheated 425° oven until cooked through, 15 to 20 minutes.
Remove wooden picks.

title: peanut butter marshmallow fudge
directions: Cook sugar and canned milk to soft ball stage; remove from heat.
Add marshmallows, peanut butter and vanilla.
Spread onto buttered platter; cut when cool.

title: tuna salad
directions: Soften gelatin in water; set aside.
Combine soup and cream cheese in saucepan and heat until blended.
Stir in softened gelatin until dissolved and cool.
When cool, add remaining ingredients.
Cool several hours, overnight is best.
Fill a 1 1/2-quart mold.

title: frozen cranberry salad
directions: Crush cranberry sauce with fork.
Add lemon juice.
Pour into refrigerator tray or glass loaf dish.
Combine remaining ingredients and spread over cranberry mixture.
Freeze until firm. Serve on crisp lettuce.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: green tomato mincemeat
directions: Drain tomatoes, then cover with cold water.
Cook 1/2 hour. Drain again.
Add remaining ingredients; cook slowly 2 hours. Makes 4 quarts.

title: pineapple casserole(good with sliced ham)
directions: Mix until sugar is dissolved.
Add
bread
broken
into small pieces (remove dark crust).
Put into casserole dish and drizzle 1/2 stick melted margarine.
Cook at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes. (It is like bread pudding, but good!)

title: baked beans with kielbasa
directions: Squeeze sausage from meat casing into pan and saute with onion and green pepper until meat is browned.
Drain and add drained beans, then mix in ketchup, sugar and mustard.
Pour into 2 qt casserole dish and bake at 325 degrees for 1 hour or more.

title: crab meat platter
directions: Let cream cheese set out to room temperature.
Spread cream cheese on platter.
Pour cocktail sauce on top.
Sprinkle with crab meat.
Serve with Wheatsworth crackers.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Mix flour, sugar and salt together.
Beat the 3 egg yolks and 1 egg white together.
Stir in milk and vanilla. Beat in flour and sugar mixture.
Heat in saucepan over medium heat until thick. Add coconut.
Pour into baked pastry shell. Top with the two well beaten egg whites. Brown in oven.

title: cajun cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Add pineapple and beaten eggs. Beat well.
Grease pan with oil (not shortening).
Bake in a 350° oven for 40 minutes or until done.

title: kielbasa
directions: Mix crushed pineapple (juice also) and brown sugar together. Stir to get lumps out.
Put in roaster.
Lay kielbasa on top.
Put lid on.
Cook 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350°.

title: pie crust
directions: Crumb together and store in a refrigerator in a covered container. Add 3 1/2 to 4 tablespoons of water to 1 cup of mix for a two-crust pie-roll.

title: broc-aroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni as directed. Steam fresh broccoli 6 minutes or cook frozen as directed.
In saucepan, melt margarine.
Stir in flour until thick and smooth. Remove from heat.
Add milk, salt, pepper, all the Mozzarella and 1/2 of the Cheddar.
Stir well until cheese melts.
Add macaroni, crumbs, remaining Cheddar and broccoli; mix thoroughly.
Turn into an 8 x 8-inch shallow baking dish sprayed with nonstick spray. Bake at 375° until bubbly, 10 to 15 minutes.

title: 60 minute dinner rolls
directions: Put yeast, sugar, salt and 1 cup flour in mixing bowl.
In saucepan, put milk, water and oleo.
Heat to 120° to 130°.
Dump into flour mixture.
Beat 4 to 5 minutes.
Add 1 cup flour, then 1/2 cup flour.
Mix after each addition, until not sticky.
Put in buttered bowl.
Rise 15 to 20 minutes.
Divide in half, 12 rolls each half, 9 x 13-inch.
Rise 15 to 20 minutes.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: chilled strawberry soup
directions: Place strawberries in blender or food processor.
Process until well blended.
Remove to bowl; add remaining ingredients. Mix well.
Chill overnight.
Serve with dollop of whipped cream or sour cream on top.

title: baked beans with beef
directions: Cook beef and onion in skillet very slowly; drain.
Add remaining ingredients; mix.
Pour into casserole dish and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cheese straws
directions: Sift together the flour and red pepper.
Mix cheese and butter together.
Add flour mixture to cheese mixture, stirring until smooth.
Put into a cookie press, making 2-inch pieces.
Bake at 400° for about 9 minutes.

title: raisin-spice squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Boil raisins rapidly in water, uncovered, for 10 minutes.
Put in large bowl and cool to lukewarm.
Stir in egg, then shortening and sugar, flour mixture.
Add nuts.
Turn into pan and bake for 25 minutes.
Cool in pan and cut into squares.

title: potluck potatoes
directions: Place the potatoes in large saucepan.
Cover with cold water for 15 minutes.
Boil, drain and cut potatoes into cubes.
In a 2 1/2-quart baking dish, buttered, add potatoes, onions and pimentos.
Toss gently with salt, onion salt and cheese.
Put cubed bread on top with grated cheese and 1/4 cup butter.
Serve with biscuits, muffins or garlic bread, salad and pork chops or spareribs.

title: overnight cookies
directions: Mix in order given.
Mold in rolls.
Let stand overnight. Slice and bake in moderate oven at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: sausage omelet
directions: Layer 1:
3 to 4 raw potatoes, sliced.

title: cherries
directions: Mix together first 6 ingredients and roll cherries in graham cracker crumbs.
Refrigerate.

title: play dough
directions: Combine all ingredients except food coloring.
Cook 3 minutes until dough separates from pan.
Knead.
Add food coloring.
Work in until dough is a uniform color.
Store in airtight container.

title: angel salad
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together until thick.
Add cherry pie filling or pineapple.
Fold.
Put in a 12 x 9-inch Pyrex dish. Decorate with pecan
halves.

title: strawberry or raspberry fruit bars
directions: Mix ingredients; press into a 9 x 13-inch oblong pan.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until golden brown.

title: nuts and bolts party mix
directions: Heat butter in saucepan until melted.
Add salts.
Pour in Worcestershire sauce.
Spoon over cereals, mixing thoroughly as you add.
Try to get all cereals moist.
Put in roaster pan (225°).
Cook 1 hour covered and 1 hour uncovered.
Stir well each 1/2 hour.
Let cool.
Store in a sealed container.

title: frosted cranberry salad
directions: Drain pineapple (save syrup).
Add water to syrup to make 1 cup.
Heat to a boil.
Dissolve jello in hot liquid; cool.
Gently stir in ginger ale; chill to partially set.

title: easy bean and pasta soup
directions: Saute onion, chopped, in
olive
oil in saucepan, being careful not to burn the onion.
Add kidney beans;
include the liquid.
Add the V-8
juice.
Cook	the
macaroni according to the directions on the package.	Drain and add to bean mixture. Stir together and bring to a boil.
Top with grated cheese.

title: poor man's swiss steak
directions: Mix crackers and water; let stand 20 minutes.
Add meat, salt and pepper (to taste).
Spread to 1/2-inch thick on cookie sheet; refrigerate overnight.
Cut into squares; roll in flour and brown in skillet.
Place in rectangular casserole dish.
Cover with mushroom soup.
Bake for 1 hour in a 350° oven.

title: no-fail bread
directions: Place water, yeast, milk, sugar, shortening, eggs, salt and 6 cups flour in mixer bowl.
Beat at low speed for 3 minutes, scraping bowl from time to time.
Pour over 6 1/2 to 7 cups flour and mix with spoon.
Knead; let rise.
Punch down and shape into 4 loaves.
Rise again and bake at 375° for 35 minutes.

title: barbecue sandwiches
directions: Cook meat.
In broth from meat cook celery, apples and onion until tender.
Add last 3 ingredients.
This may be frozen.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Mix together in a very large bowl the oil, sugar and pumpkin. Sift together and stir in dry ingredients.
Stir in vanilla. Blend in nuts and dates.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls 2 inches apart in a lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for about 10 minutes.
Yield: 9 dozen.

title: meat loaf
directions: Soak bread in small bowl with just enough milk to make soft. Mix all ingredients together.
Pat out 3 long loaves in 9 x 9-inch casserole pan.
Cook at 350° for 30 minutes.
Drain off fat and return to oven for 15 minutes or until brown.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Cook onion in butter until tender.
In 1 1/2-quart casserole, mix remaining ingredients.
Cover and bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: meaty mexican cornbread
directions: Brown meat with the onion.
Drain well.
Mix cornmeal, oil, milk, eggs, salt, soda and cream-style corn.
Pour half of cornmeal mixture into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Add meat and onion mix, spreading evenly across dish.
Sprinkle cheese and jalapenos over meat.
Add remaining cornmeal mixture.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: shrimp in garlic butter
directions: Thaw shrimp if frozen.
In a large skillet, heat margarine or butter over medium-high heat.
Add shrimp and garlic.
Cook, stirring frequently, for 1 to 3 minutes or until shrimp turn pink. Stir in parsley.
Makes 4 servings.

title: rocky road bars
directions: Cream together margarine, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Stir in flour, pecans, cocoa, baking powder and salt.
Put in 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Sprinkle with miniature marshmallows and bake for 3 minutes.
Cool.
Melt chocolate chips (half semi-sweet and half milk chocolate) and peanut butter.
Stir in Rice Krispies.
Spread on top of cooled bars.
Chill and cut.

title: mexican potato salad
directions: Mix onions, pepper, pimento, salt, pepper, mayonnaise and half and half.
Grease bottom and sides of a shallow baking dish. Alternate layers; potatoes, filling and cheese.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Top with sliced olives if desired.
Serve warm.

title: asparagus with sauce
directions: Heat the salad oil in a skillet.
Add bacon and cook, stirring, until the bacon is golden and crisp.
Add the asparagus; cook until heated through, then slowly add the bouillon and soy sauce and cook for 3 minutes.

While this is cooking, stir the cornstarch into the cold water until it forms a smooth paste, then stir this into the mixture in the skillet and continue cooking, stirring constantly, until the sauce is smooth and thick and clear.
Add the Accent; give it one last stir, then serve.
Serves 4.

title: french dressing
directions: Put everything in blender and process until well mixed.

title: fried jalepenos
directions: Strip seeds from peppers. Grate cheeses and mix. Stuff the peppers. Dip in egg wash (milk and egg), and roll in flour.
Fry in deep fat til golden (use basket to keep peppers together.

title: garden patch vegetable soup
directions: *For a vegetarian soup, increase tomatoes to 3 pounds and add 2 beef or chicken bouillon cubes.

title: vegetarian tuno finger sandwichi
directions: Chop onion, apple and celery and put in a bowl.
Mix tuno and add mayonnaise to taste.

title: sausage dip
directions: Brown sausage in a deep sauce pan; drain.
Then add cheese. Stir until melted.
Then add salsa and stir until mixed.
Remove from heat and serve while hot.
Serve with Tostitos Chips.

title: reuben sandwich(with leftover corned beef, make reubens.)
directions: In a small bowl, mix mustard, mayonnaise and horseradish (if desired).
Place 6 slices of rye bread on a tray.
Make sandwiches by placing 3 slices of corned beef, 1 slice of Swiss cheese and 1 tablespoon sauerkraut on each slice of bread.
With a knife, spread some of the mayonnaise mixture on a slice of rye bread and place on top, completing the sandwich.
Butter both sides of sandwich and lightly grill until Swiss cheese has melted.
Serve hot.

title: cavatini
directions: Brown hamburger, onion and green pepper together.
Cook and drain pasta; mix pasta and hamburger together.
Add spaghetti sauce, mushrooms, pepperoni and oregano.
Place in a 13 x 9-inch baking dish and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.
Then add Mozzarella cheese on top and bake 8 to 10 minutes longer.

title: stuffed peppers(serves 4)
directions: Cut the tops of green peppers

off. Rinse seeds out. Then mix all ingredients and stuff the peppers. Put peppers in a small cake pan touching each other. Cover with spaghetti sauce. Bake at 325° for 1 hour. Put grated cheese (optional) on top, then bake 15 more minutes. Serve with rice.

title: microwave leche quemada(candy)
directions: Place pecans on large glass plate and microwave for 8 minutes, stirring at 2 minute intervals.
Set aside.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together and form in a 9 x 13 casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for about 30 to 40 minutes.
Remove and top with ketchup, brown sugar and mustard mixture.
Mix all together and spread on top of cooked meat loaf.

title: california dip
directions: Blend together and chill.
Makes 2 cups.
Good served with chips.

title: boiled cookies
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, salt, milk and margarine.
Bring to a rolling boil.
Remove from heat; add peanut butter, oats and vanilla. Spoon out on wax paper or greased cookie sheet.
Let set until cool.

title: meaty bean burritos
directions: Mix all ingredients together. The mixture will be soupy. Cook in pan on low-medium heat. Take 1/2 to 3/4 cup of batter and swirl around in the pan. Cook a few minutes, until batter thickens. Turn over and cook the other side.

title: english pea salad
directions: Drain first 4 ingredients.
Heat oil, vinegar and sugar until sugar is dissolved.
Pour second mixture into first mixture.
Add chopped onion.
Refrigerate.

title: turnip green casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and put into greased casserole dish.
Put grated cheese on top and bake 1 hour at 350°.
I cover it to keep cheese from browning too much.

title: buckeyes
directions: Melt margarine; add peanut butter.
Set off burner.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Roll into balls the size of a walnut.
Place on cookie sheet lined with wax paper.
Refrigerate one hour.
Melt 6 ounces chocolate bits with paraffin wax.
Impale balls on toothpick and dip in chocolate mixture.
Drop on wax paper and refrigerate.

title: pan am mango ice cream
directions: Cut fruit of mango from around pit of peeled mango and puree in blender or food processor.
Combine with sugar and lime juice, mixing well.
Stir in eggs and both creams.
Freeze in container of ice cream freezer according to manufacturer's directions.
When frozen, transfer to covered plastic container and store in freezer overnight.
Serve with a lime wedge.
Makes about 1 quart.

title: string bean casserole
directions: Simmer the first 5 ingredients.
Blend	with the cheese and pimento.
Pour sauce over beans in	a
greased
casserole. Sprinkle crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: potato soup
directions: Combine potatoes, celery and onion with 3 cups water in medium saucepan.
Cook, covered, until potatoes are tender.
Add milk, bouillon cubes and butter.
Mix well.
Mix sour cream with cornstarch in small bowl until smooth; add to soup mixture.
Cook until thickened and bouillon cubes are dissolved, stirring constantly.
Stir in salt and pepper.

title: cherry lollipops
directions: You will need 20 sucker sticks.

title: tapioca fruit salad
directions: Save 3 cups liquid from pineapple and oranges.
Add orange juice to make up the 3 cups.
Pour liquid over pudding mix in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil, stirring, until thickened (not hard). Let cool.
Add oranges, pineapple and bananas.
Refrigerate until cool and serve.
(This may be kept several days in refrigerator.)

title: pound cream cheese cake
directions: Mix and beat well.
Bake in 10-inch tube pan at 350° for 60 minutes.
Sprinkle confectioners sugar on top.

title: gingies
directions: Mix together.
Thin, roll out, cut and bake 15 minutes in 350° oven.

title: potato bake
directions: Mix all together.
Put into a greased casserole dish. Optional:
Sprinkle top with corn flakes or potato chips.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: lazy man's soup
directions: Combine all ingredients and cook over medium heat until tender.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Core and dice apples to make about 4 cups. In a large bowl, sprinkle apples with lemon juice. Add celery, grapes, nuts and raisins. Combine mayonnaise, sugar and 1/2 teaspoon lemon juice. Spoon over apple mixture until well blended. Cover and chill. Serve on lettuce. Yields 8 servings.

title: garland's biscuits
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Mix all ingredients together.
Roll out about 1/4 to 1/2-inch thick on floured wax paper.
Cut out about 16 medium sized biscuits.
Bake about 10 to 12 minutes on cookie sheet.
Add 1/2 pound sausage to this mixture to make sausage balls.
One cup Cheddar cheese is optional.

title: barbecue brisket
directions: In large roast pan, place brisket.
Pour liquid smoke over brisket, generously sprinkle both sides with celery, garlic and onion salt.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Next day, sprinkle both sides with pepper and Worcestershire sauce; cover and cook. Trim excess fat from brisket.
Cook 5 hours at 275°, uncovered and pour 3 ounces barbecue sauce on meat.
Cook 1 hour, uncovered. Remove meat to platter and sauce.
Cool.
Skim fat.
Mix 2 tablespoons flour with 1/2 cup water, stir into meat sauce.
Add more barbecue sauce to taste, slice brisket and serve with piping hot sauce.

title: chicken breast casserole
directions: Boil chicken breast until tender.
Let cool.
Cut into strips. Mix together Ro-Tel tomatoes and Cheddar cheese soup.
Stir over medium heat until creamy.
In casserole dish place a layer of Tostados, a layer of chicken, then pour enough sauce to cover. Continue layering until dish is full or chicken and tomato-cheese mixture is used.
Bake, uncovered, at 400° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: lovers wedding cake
directions: Put the flour of love, good looks and sweet temper into a well furnished house.
Beat the butter to a cream.
Mix together blindness of faults, self forgetfulness, powdered wits, dry humor into sweet argument.
Add them to the ingredients.
Pour gently rippling laughter and common sense.
Work it together until all is well mixed; then bake it gently FOREVER.
(November, 1919)

title: best 7 minute frosting(amish recipe)
directions: Mix egg whites, water, salt, sugar and corn syrup in top of double boiler over boiling water.
Stir together, then beat constantly with egg beater until frosting stands in peaks, about 7 minutes.
Add vanilla and marshmallows.
Beat until marshmallows are melted.

title: marshmallow squares
directions: Add 2 tablespoons water to plain gelatine.
Stir to dissolve. Add granulated sugar, Karo and hot water.
Boil this until it spins a thread.
In large bowl have ready 3 well beaten egg whites and vanilla.
Add cooked mixture slowly, beating constantly.
Takes about 30 minutes.
Have ready a 9 x 12-inch cake pan lined with wax paper, leaving a couple of inches up sides.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Pour mixture into pan.
Wait until firm, about 3 hours. Cut into squares.
Dip each square into melted chocolate and place on wax paper to cool.
I use toothpicks to dip squares into chocolate.
I triple the recipe and freeze them.
I use a big cookie sheet instead of a cake pan.

title: coconut ball bonbon
directions: Combine coconut, sugar, milk, butter and vanilla.
Mix well. In a saucepan, melt chocolate chips and paraffin over very low heat.
Shape coconut mixture into balls and dip in chocolate mixture until coated well.
Makes a lot.

title: saucy drumettes
directions: Season drumettes with black pepper.
Mix sugar, oil and soy sauce in saucepan.
Heat.
Add drumettes and cook until tender. Serve as an appetizer.
Keep warm in a chafing dish or crock pot.

title: beef burgundy
directions: Brown beef in
oil
in	a large skillet.
Add all other ingredients and simmer,
covered
for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients and form loaves or put in bread pans. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cauliflower soup
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Thaw cauliflower in mixture.
Add soups and milk.
Simmer for 30 minutes.

title: fresh apple custard pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Bake pastry shell for 15 minutes.
Beat sour cream, sweetened condensed milk, apple juice, egg, vanilla and cinnamon.
Pour into pastry shell.
Bake 30 minutes at 375°. Cool.

title: cheesy macaroni bake
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Spray baking dish with vegetable spray. Cut cheeses into 1/4-inch cubes or use shredded cheeses.
In large saucepan of boiling water; cook macaroni according to package direction.
If using fresh broccoli, add to pasta 3 minutes before pasta is done.
(If using thawed frozen broccoli, pat it dry with paper towel.) Drain macaroni and return it to the saucepan where it was cooked.
Add cheeses, wheat germ, mustard and ground red pepper.
If using thawed frozen broccoli, add it here.
Spoon mixture into the baking dish.
Pour the milk evenly over the top and bake until bubbly and golden, 18 to 21 minutes.

title: 1957 chicken with almonds(serves 4)
directions: About 1 hour before serving:

In a 12-inch skillet over medium-high heat, in hot butter, cook chicken pieces until browned on all sides, removing chicken pieces to plate as they brown. Discard all but 2 tablespoons of fat from the skillet.

title: date cake
directions: Cream together butter, sugar and eggs.
Pour boiling water over dates, then add soda and cool.
Add date mixture alternately with flour.
Bake at 325° for 40 or 50 minutes.
Top with Caramel Frosting.

title: granny's dark rolls
directions: Combine oatmeal, whole wheat flour, salt, shortening, molasses and honey.
Stir boiling water over and cool slightly.
Add egg and blend.
Stir in yeast.
Add enough regular flour to make a stiff dough.
Knead for 5 minutes.
Let rise until double. Continue as for any other roll.
If I want more rolls, I make my oatmeal and whole wheat flour to 1 cup each and 1 1/2 cups boiling water.
I use 2 instead of 1 egg.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Stir boiled water into large bowl over jello mix.
Pour mashed bananas, pecans and thawed strawberries in and mix together.
Pour half in serving dish and chill until molded.
Mix together cream cheese and sour cream; spread on top.
Put the other half of jello mixture on top.
Chill until molded.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Mix with Velveeta, cream cheese, 1/2 tube Ritz crackers and butter.
Put remaining 1/2 tube of crushed crackers on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until bubbly.

title: egg-sausage casserole
directions: Beat together eggs and milk.
Brown and drain sausage.
Mix together all ingredients.
Cover and place in the refrigerator overnight in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake the next morning for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: chess pie
directions: Beat eggs with fork until light; add sugar, cornmeal and vinegar.
Stir to mix well; do not beat.
Add cooled butter and vanilla.
Stir to mix well.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Cream together sugar and shortening.
Beat in egg.
Sift next 4 ingredients together and add to creamed mixture. Add pumpkin, mixing well. Fold in pecans.
Drop on greased cookie sheets and bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes about 5 dozen.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix all the ingredients together and refrigerate.

title: hamburger cookies
directions: Spread 1/2 teaspoon of frosting on the flat side of each vanilla wafer.
Place 1 teaspoon of coconut on top of 6 wafers. Place a mint candy on top of coconut; top with remaining frosted vanilla wafer. Brush top of "hamburger" with honey; sprinkle with sesame seed.
Makes 6 "hamburgers."

title: taco dip
directions: In glass casserole pan, cover bottom with refried beans.
In small bowl, combine sour cream and taco seasoning.
Mix well. Cover beans with sour cream mixture.
Layer with cheese and remaining ingredients.
Serve with tortilla chips and salsa.

title: praline graham crunches
directions: Line 4 sided cookie sheet with foil.
Then place graham crackers on foil.
Boil oleo or butter and sugar for 2 minutes. Pour over graham crackers.
Sprinkle cut-up pecans over mixture. Bake 8 minutes at 350°.
Cut or rather slice mixture before it cools.

title: campfire potatoes
directions: Boil the potatoes, peel and dice.
Saute the other ingredients until soft. While potatoes are soft, mix with sauteed ingredients.

title: angel salad
directions: Drain juice from pineapple, oranges and cherries.
Cut oranges and cherries in half.
Pour all ingredients into a large mixing bowl and mix thoroughly.
Allow to chill for 12 to 24 hours before serving.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Melt butter over low heat (or use microwave).
Remove from heat.
Mix in sugar and corn syrup.
Blend in eggs and vanilla extract.
Add pecans.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until well done.

title: ginger cookies
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar.
Add molasses and mix well.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Add egg and flour mixture to shortening mixture.
Shape into balls and roll in sugar.
Place on a greased baking sheet and bake at 350° for 12 minutes.
Leave on a sheet a few minutes before removing.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients thoroughly in a large mixing bowl.
Bake in an iron skillet for 35 minutes.

title: spiced cranberries
directions: Mix water, spices and cranberries.
Cook, covered, until berries burst or approximately 10 minutes.
Remove from fire; add sugar, then cook for 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Serve warm or chilled.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix pineapple, Jell-O and cranberry sauce in water.
Heat until dissolved.
Mix in sugar and nuts. Chill.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients in doubler boiler; cook until thick. Add 11 ounces of cream cheese, 1 small jar chopped pimentos with juice and a small onion, chopped fine.

title: yum-yum cake
directions: Boil the raisins in 2 cups of water for 15 minutes.
Take from heat and add the remaining 2 cups of water.
Let stand until lukewarm.
Pour raisin mixture into a mixing bowl; add the sugar, shortening, cinnamon, cloves, salt, vanilla, flour and baking soda.
Mix well by hand.
Pour into well-greased pan (tube or Bundt) and bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.
Check (test) and if not done, bake a bit longer, checking frequently until cake is done.

title: english toffee
directions: Cook butter, sugar and water to 300°.
Remove from heat and add vanilla and chopped pecans.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Cover with Hershey bars while hot and spread on top when melted. Cover with a small amount of ground nuts.
When cool, break into pieces.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix and put in a greased and floured 10 cup Bundt pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: cornflake bars
directions: Put white syrup and brown sugar in a pan; set over low flame until syrupy.
Do not boil.

title: baked tuna chow mein casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except chow mein noodles and nuts.

title: fried okra
directions: Wash okra and cut off tips and stem ends.
Cut pods into crosswise slices 1/4-inch thick.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Roll in corn meal mixed with flour.
Saute in hot bacon drippings until okra is golden brown.
Serve hot.
Makes 6 servings.

title: marshmallow fruit dip
directions: Mix in container and chill.
Serve with fresh fruit.
Use as dip for fruit tray at parties.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream well the first 4 ingredients together, then add the remaining ingredients.
Mix together.
Spoon onto cookie sheet by small teaspoons.
Bake at 350° for 11 to 12 minutes, until they are golden on the edge.
Yields 30 cookies.

title: favorite pancakes(makes eight 4-inch cakes)
directions: Cream some butter or margarine with either powdered garlic or liquid garlic juice.
Slice some French-style bread into thick slices and butter generously with garlic spread.

Sprinkle the buttered side of the bread slices generously with grated Parmesan cheese and then sprinkle on a little sweet paprika for color. Slip under a broiler for a minute or two, watching carefully, until the cheese has started to melt and bubble.
Serve at once.

title: cucumber sandwiches
directions: Mix cream cheese and Italian dressing; spread on rye bread. Place a thin slice of cucumber on each slice of bread.
Lightly sprinkle each with dill weed.

title: eve's delite
directions: Cover bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan with 1 roll slightly frozen cookie dough.
Cream together the cream cheese, eggs, vanilla and sugar.
Place on top of dough in pan.
Cover the mixture with remaining roll of cookie dough.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes, until browned.
Refrigerate before cutting.

title: country biscuits(for 3 dozen biscuits)
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Cut in shortening.
Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add to dry ingredients with buttermilk.
Knead until smooth.
Roll out and cut with biscuit cutter.
Dip each in melted butter and fold over.
Place on baking sheet and let rise until double in size. Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: easy beef quiche
directions: Brown meat in skillet over medium heat.
Drain fat and set aside.
Blend next 4 ingredients until smooth.
Stir in meat, cheese, onion and pepper.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 35 or 40 minutes.
Serve with salad.

title: white clam sauce for pasta(linguine)
directions: Chop garlic fine and make a garlic butter with olive oil in heavy skillet.
Add all ingredients except shrimp.
Simmer 3 to 5 minutes; thicken with water and flour.
Simmer 3 minutes; add shrimp.
Cook shrimp 1 to 2 minutes.
Serve over pasta the grated cheese.
This recipe will be enough for 1 pound pasta.

title: chicken livers(serves 6)
directions: Remove fat and tissue from livers; separate them.
Place flour, salt and pepper in a plastic bag.
Shake livers, a few of them at a time, in the bag to coat well.
Saute them in 2 tablespoons butter and 2 tablespoons oil in a frying pan.
In a second pan, add 1 tablespoon oil and 1 tablespoon butter and saute mushrooms and onions.
Combine the two.
Dissolve cornstarch in water.
In the second pan, make a gravy by thickening the liquid with cornstarch mixture.
Add vermouth and 1 cup chicken broth.
Pour over livers and bring to a boil.
Serve on rice.

title: onion cake
directions: Cook onions in butter until tender.
Cool.
Mix rest of ingredients in bowl, except rolls.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Mix cream cheese, mayonnaise and dressing.
Spread on cooled crust.
Top with chopped vegetables and grated cheese.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Step 1:
Go out in yard and chase chicken until you catch him. Grab chicken by the neck and twirl around and around until you hear his neck pop.
Drop chicken on ground.
If he gets up and starts running around, repeat step 1.
If chicken lays there continue on to step 2.

title: congealed strawberry salad
directions: Mix fruits and nuts.
Dissolve gelatin with hot water.
Mix gelatin and fruit mixture together.
In a 9 x 13-inch dish, pour 1/2 gelatin mixture.
Refrigerate until set.
The other half of the mixture can be left out.
After gelatin has set, spread light sour cream on top.
Add remaining gelatin on top of sour cream layer.
Allow to set until firm.
Makes 12 to 15 servings.

title: sweet and sour cucumbers
directions: About 1 hour before serving in large bowl, combine all ingredients.
Cover to blend flavors, stirring occasionally. Serve with hamburgers, frankfurters or grilled fish.
Makes 4 cups.

title: garlic cheese grits
directions: Boil water, grits and salt until thickened, then add garlic cheese.
Cut up cheese so it will melt quickly.
Add melted butter; add eggs.
(Put small amount of hot grits in eggs, then add all to grits.)
Put in baking dish and bake for 20 minutes in 350° oven.

title: white velvet cookies
directions: Cream the margarine until light and fluffy. Beat in sugar, egg yolk and cream cheese which has been softened at room temperature. Beat until light and fluffy. Add remaining ingredients and work until well mixed. Drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 12 to 14 minutes.

title: cappuccino coffee mix
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Store in tightly sealed glass jar.

title: pie crust
directions: Put water in oil (do not stir); add flour and salt.
Mix together and roll out between 2 pieces of wax paper.

title: chicken and pasta tuscany
directions: Boil penne pasta in salted water until done.
Drain, rinse and reserve.
In a large saute pan, melt butter over medium heat.
Add garlic and chicken and saute until chicken is fully cooked.
Add sun-dried tomatoes and artichoke hearts; toss while cooking for 3 minutes.
Add pine nuts, pasta and cream.
Turn heat high while stirring and cook until cream begins to thicken.
Add salt, pepper, basil and spinach.
Turn heat down and stir until spinach wilts.
Shut heat and serve.
Top each plate with grated Parmesan cheese.
Serves 4.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash down.
Stir in chicken soup and Velveeta.
Cover with crumbled crackers.
Bake at 350° until casserole is golden on top and cheese is melted and bubbling.

title: mill run grange sloppy joes
directions: Cook until tender in 1 tablespoon oil the onion, pepper and celery. Do not brown. Add hamburg. Cook for 15 minutes, stirring frequently. Add soup, sugar, salt, pepper and small amount of chilli sauce. Cover them and let steam for 30 minutes. Stir occasionally.

title: no work chicken
directions: Place chicken, skin side down, in flat baking dish in one layer.
Mix all other ingredients together.
Pour over chicken and refrigerate 6 hours or overnight.
When ready to cook, turn chicken, cover dish with foil and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Remove foil; baste well.
Continue baking, uncovered, for 15 minutes. Serves 4.

title: lemon cheese pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325 degrees. Grease and flour a large tube pan.
In a large mixing bowl, cream together the butter and cream cheese.
Add the sugar and beat until smooth.
Add the eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.

Add the flour alternately with the lemon juice. Pour into the prepared pan and bake for about 1 hour 15 minutes or until a toothpick comes out clean when inserted into center of cake. Allow to cool in pan for about 10 minutes and then invert onto cake plate.

title: pretty pear salad
directions: Drain pears; save juice.
Combine syrup with cinnamon candies; heat until dissolved.
Add pears; bring to a boil.
Chill pears in syrup several hours or overnight.
Blend cream cheese with milk and lemon juice.
Add remaining ingredients.
Drain pears thoroughly.
Place filling in center of pear halves and spread almost to edge.
Can use as halves or put together for a whole pear.
Keep chilled.
Serve.

title: six layer dinner
directions: Layer first 6 ingredients in a greased 2-quart casserole. Sprinkle each layer with salt and pepper. Garnish with pepper rings, if desired.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours. Serves 6.

title: cheese cake
directions: Mix jello with water and let get partially set in refrigerator.
Crush graham crackers and melt butter.
Mix together and press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
(Leave a few graham crackers for topping.)
Mix cream cheese, sugar and lemon juice. In separate bowl, beat 1 can Milnot.
Add vanilla.
Add jello mix to cream cheese mix, then to Milnot mix.
Mix well.
Pour over crumbs.
Top with remaining crumbs.
Cool.

title: potatoes supreme
directions: Cook potatoes unpeeled.
Drain.
Refrigerate overnight.
Peel and grate coarsely in large bowl.
Mix with remaining ingredients. Put in shallow 2 qt. baking dish.

title: hamburg pie
directions: Mix together the ground chuck, onion, green pepper, bread crumbs, eggs and seasonings.
Spread in a 9 x 8 x 2-inch pan sprayed with cooking spray.
This will be the crust.
Bake at 350° until cooked through.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Mix beaten eggs, milk, cubed bread, salt and mustard in large bowl.
Mix by hand with large spoon.
Add sausage and cheese. Stir well.
Pour into greased Pyrex 9 x 9-inch or 8 x 10 1/2-inch pan.
Cover and set overnight in refrigerator.
Bake, uncovered, for 45 minutes at 350°.
Let stand 5 minutes before cutting into squares.
Makes 6 servings.

title: granola
directions: Heat oats in shallow pan at 350° for 15 minutes.
Heat sugar, oil and honey in saucepan until sugar is dissolved.
Add vanilla to liquid ingredients.
Add remaining dry ingredients to oats, stir in liquid ingredients, mixing to coat dry ingredients.
Toast in oven, stirring every 5 minutes.
Makes 10 cups or 40 servings.

title: no fail pie crust
directions: With fork, mix first 4 ingredients.
In small bowl, beat 1/2 cup water and remaining ingredients together.
Add to first mixture and blend with fork until dry ingredients are moistened. With hands, mold dough in a ball and chill at least 15 minutes. Makes 2 double crust 9-inch pies and 1 shell.

title: baked parmesan chicken breasts
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Spray baking pan with no-stick spray. Dip chicken in melted butter then in combined remaining ingredients.
Place in prepared pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until tender.
Easy and good.

title: lemon bars
directions: Crumble 2 cups flour, butter and 1/2 cup powdered sugar. Press into 9 x 13-inch ungreased pan. Bake 15 minutes at 350° until firm, not brown.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Reserve one cup of cake mix for topping.
Mix together the rest of the cake mix,
melted butter and egg and pat into the bottom and sides of a greased 9 x 13 inch pan.
Mix together the pumpkin,
eggs, sugars, milk and cinnamon and pour over crust. Sprinkle with topping and bake at 350° for 50-60 minutes.
Cool and serve with whipped cream.

title: chewy bread
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mixture will be very thick.
Spread into greased sheet cake pan.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Mix in order given.
Do not stir until hot water is added. Bake at 350° until no dough shows on toothpick.
Better if it is not overcooked.

title: cracker jacks
directions: Spread popcorn out in 17 x 12 x 2-inch pan; set aside.

title: upside-down german chocolate cake
directions: Grease a 13 x 9-inch pan. Spread nuts and coconut on the bottom of the pan. Mix cake mix as directed on the box. Pour over nuts and coconut. Mix the cream cheese, butter and box of powdered sugar to a creamy mixture. Put "globs" on top of the cake mix. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: edna's chicken casserole
directions: Cook macaroni and drain.
Combine soup, milk, onion and peppers.
Place over low heat.
Add cheese.
Stir until melted. Add chicken, macaroni and margarine.
Blend together.
Put in casserole dish and bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: coca-cola salad
directions: Mix cherries, water and sugar; bring to a boil.
Add remaining ingredients to cherry-sugar mixture.
Congeal.

title: company corn bread
directions: Mix.
Pour into greased 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
This bread will keep for several days refrigerated.

title: yellow squash supreme
directions: Cook and drain squash.
Add next 5 ingredients.
Put in buttered casserole dish.
Start with layer of stuffing, then squash.
Top with layer of stuffing mix.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: butter sauce(for noodles and spaghetti)
directions: In a mixer, whip butter until light and fluffy (consistency of heavy whipped cream).
Add a dash of white pepper and grated cheese, mixing well.
Keep mixture in refrigerator and use as desired.

title: saffron rice with currants(from connie)
directions: Melt butter in large heavy skillet over medium heat.
Add rice, onions and garlic and stir until golden brown.
Add stock and bring to a boil.
Stir in saffron until dissolved.
Reduce heat and cook for 20 minutes.
Drain currants and stir into rice with the 3 tablespoons butter, salt and pepper.

title: pumpkin pecan bread
directions: Make at least 2 hours before serving.
Grease a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Preheat oven to 350°.

title: pea & peanut salad
directions: Cook peas; drain and chill. Combine with all other ingredients. Mix well. Chill and serve.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Put cucumbers and onions to soak for 2 hours in brine made of salt and water.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Crush crackers and mix with Parmesan cheese, salt and pepper. Dip chicken into melted butter.
Roll buttered chicken in cracker crumb mixture.

title: lemon bread
directions: Cream
shortening;
gradually
add
1 cup sugar, beating well. Add eggs, 1 at a time, beating well after each addition. Combine flour, baking powder
and
salt; add to creamed mixture alternately with milk, beginning and ending with flour mixture. Mix well after each addition.
Stir
in
rind and pecans.
Pour batter into a greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until
a
wooden pick
inserted
in
center
comes
out
clean. Combine 1/3 cup sugar
and
lemon juice, stirring well; immediately pour over bread in
pan.
Cool
in pan 10 minutes; remove from pan and cool completely on wire rack.

title: twinkie cake
directions: Use a 9 x 13 glass container and lay Twinkies to fill the bottom of the pan.
Use a straw to poke several holes in each Twinkie.
Prepare the Jell-O and pour over the Twinkies, making sure to cover each of them.
Place container in the refrigerator. When the Jell-O has molded, spread Cool Whip over the top.
If desired, top off with your favorite fruit.

title: rustic lasagna
directions: Cook noodles according to package.
Preheat oven at 350°. Spray 13 x 9-inch baking dish with cooking spray.

title: turkey tenderloin supreme
directions: In large skillet, brown Turkey in Butter.
Add Onions; cook for 1 - 2 minutes.
Combine Soup and Water; Pour over Turkey.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer 8 - 10 minutes or until meat juices run clear.
Yield 6 servings.

title: german cold salad
directions: Shred cabbage.
Combine cabbage, onion and sugar.
Let stand for 1 hour.
Mix remaining ingredients; bring to a boil.
Pour over cabbage mixture; cool.
Yield: 6 to 8 servings.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large mixer bowl, cream peanut butter, shortening, brown sugar and granulated sugar.
Add eggs and continue to mix.
Add dry ingredients to mixture.
Knead until ingredients are thoroughly combined.
Roll dough into balls the size of walnuts.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Flatten in crisscross fashion with
a fork.
Bake 15 minutes.
Yields 6 dozen.

title: shrimp victoria
directions: In large skillet, saut shrimp and onions in 4 tablespoons butter until shrimp are pink.
Add mushrooms and cook 5 minutes. Stir in 1 tablespoon butter, the flour, salt and pepper and cook for 1 minute.
Slowly stir in sour cream, blending until hot and smooth.
Pour into chafing dish and garnish with strips of red and yellow pepper.
Excellent over rice or pasta.

title: extra easy peach cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in an 11 x 7-inch baking dish in a 350° oven. Mix peaches and 1/2 cup sugar.
Set aside.
Combine flour, 1/2 cup sugar and milk until moistened.
Pour batter evenly into melted margarine.
Do not stir.
Spoon peaches over batter. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: cheese broccoli
directions: Cook the broccoli according to package directions and drain. Combine remaining ingredients except cracker crumbs and butter and mix with broccoli.
Place in a greased casserole.
Melt butter and stir in cracker crumbs.
Sprinkle buttery crumbs on top and bake at 350°.
Makes 12 servings.

title: hash browns fantastic
directions: Mix margarine or butter, soup, sour cream, onion and cheese. Pour over thawed hash browns.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: fresh peach pie
directions: Puree 1 cup peaches with orange juice.
Mix sugar and cornstarch; add puree.
Bring to boil over high heat, stirring constantly until mixture thickens.
Cool quickly.
Slice remaining peaches.
Mix with lemon juice and puree.
Pour into baked shell and garnish with orange peel.

title: sugar free holiday nog
directions: Combine pudding mix, 2 cups of milk, vanilla or rum, and sugar substitute in a bowl.
Mix according to pudding directions.
Pour into tightly closed container.
Add 3 cups milk; shake well.
Add evaporated milk; shake.
Add remaining milk; shake well.
Chill. Makes 8 servings.

title: chicken breasts supreme
directions: Brush boneless and skinless chicken breasts with mixture of all 3 ingredients and refrigerate at least 4 hours.
You may use thighs and legs if you so desire.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour. Baste several times during baking.
Serve over rice.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Beat eggs.
Add flour and sugar.
Add pineapple and mix well. Pour in greased baking dish and place bread on top.
Pour melted butter over and bake.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 6. Prep Time 20 minutes.

title: somerville meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients and turn into a greased or oiled 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour.
Serves 6.

title: london broil
directions: Marinate the London broil in soy sauce for at least 24 hours, turning as often as possible.
Cook for 1 hour or until done on barbecue grill.

title: oriental dip
directions: In medium bowl combine all ingredients.
Mix well.
Cover and chill.
Stir before serving.

title: doritos casserole
directions: Saute onion and bell pepper.
Add to meat mixture.
Add milk and cook 20 minutes.
In a large casserole dish, crumble 1
1/2 cups
Doritos,
then
add
1/2 meat mixture and grated cheese. Add
another
layer
of crushed Doritos, meat mixture and cheese. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: naturally sweet carrots
directions: Cut carrots into slices and cook in about 1 cup water and margarine until crisp-tender.
Do not overcook!
Be sure to watch and stir them often.
I cook them part of the time covered and then uncover them and cook until all the liquid has evaporated. They will start to turn a light brown.
This is what makes them naturally sweet.

title: lemon squares
directions: Crush graham crackers.
Pack in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan. Mix softened cream cheese with Cool Whip.
Mix lemon pudding with milk.
Beat well.
Spread on top of cracker crumbs.
Top with cream cheese mixture.
Add topping of your choice.

title: deep freeze corn
directions: Boil 5 minutes, stirring to mix thoroughly.
Cool to room temperature.
Pack and freeze.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, cornstarch, milk, vanilla and baking powder. Add Cool Whip, Eagle Brand milk and instant pudding.
Pour into ice cream container and add milk to fill line.
Mix in freezer until done.
If desired, nuts or crushed fruit may be added.

title: three bean soup
directions: Heat oil in heavy 3-quart pot over medium heat.
Add onion and garlic; cook 2 minutes, until onion has softened.
Increase heat to high.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat, cover and simmer 3 minutes, until rice is cooked and green beans are tender.
Makes 4 servings.

title: j l's chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream margarine and shortening; add sugars.
Beat with electric mixer until fluffy.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Gradually add flour, baking soda and salt to sugar mixture until well beaten. Add chips and nuts; stir with fork.
Spoon batter onto well-greased cookie sheets.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes or until golden brown.
Oops don't forget to preheat oven to 350°.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Cook chicken breasts; remove skin and bone.
Cut chicken into bite-size pieces.
Add sour cream and soup; mix well.
Pour into baking dish.
Crumble Ritz crackers on top.
Slice butter and place on top of cracker crumbs.
Sprinkle with poppy seed.
Bake at 350° approximately 30 minutes.

title: casserole for a crowd
directions: Once you have browned the meat and cooked the noodles, combine all ingredients into a large bowl; mix well.
Pour mixture into a casserole dish.
Top with buttered bread squares.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve with salad and baked potato.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Drop by teaspoons in hot grease.

title: cheese brunch casserole
directions: In 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish, place bacon between layers of paper towels.
Cook full power for 4 1/2 minutes.
Crumble bacon and set aside.
Place croutons in same baking dish.
Sprinkle with Cheddar and Monterey Jack cheeses.
In large bowl beat eggs.
Add milk, mustard, onion powder and pepper and pour over croutons and cheese.
Cook at 50% power for 8 minutes.
Sprinkle with bacon. Cook at 50% power for 12 minutes.
Let stand 5 to 10 minutes.

title: rainbow sherbet punch
directions: In punch bowl, add 1/2 bottle 7-Up, then frozen lemonade, frozen strawberries, then sherbet.
Add remaining 7-Up.
Mix.

title: orange mandarin jello salad
directions: Add 3 cups boiling water to jello and pudding mixes.
Cook until mixture starts to thicken.
Cool.
Add mandarin oranges and Cool Whip.
Chill until set.

title: gingerbread
directions: Sift together Flour, Sugar, Baking Powder, Ginger, Cinnamon, Nutmeg and Salt.
Add Butter to boiling water, when Butter is melted add Molasses.
Stir this into Flour mixture and beat just enough to make a smooth Batter.
Bake in a buttered 8 or 9-inch Square pan at 325 degrees for about 35 minutes.

title: rice krispies treats
directions: Melt margarine in large saucepan over low heat.
Add marshmallows and stir until completely melted.
Remove from heat.

title: sweet and sour marinade
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Stir until sugar dissolves.
Pour over desired vegetables (chopped).
Cover and chill 8 hours. Drain before serving.
Yields about 1 2/3 cups.

title: caramel corn
directions: Melt all ingredients in large saucepan over medium heat.
Boil for 5 minutes.
Take from heat and add 1/2 teaspoon soda. Stir. Pour over 16 cups popped popcorn quickly.
Bake in 200° oven on cookie sheets for 1 hour.
Stir every 15 minutes.

title: delicious cookies
directions: Blend margarine and oil.
Add brown and white sugars and cream with flavorings and egg.
Beat well.
Add flour, salt, baking soda and cream of tartar.
Mix well.
Stir in oats, Rice Krispies, coconut and chocolate chips.

title: crabmeat appetizer
directions: Combine cream cheese, crabmeat, onions, milk, horseradish and salt, mixing until well blended.
Stir in almonds; spoon into 9-inch pie plate.
Arrange 10 bread slices around outer edge of cream cheese mixture.
Place remaining bread on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake cream cheese mixture and bread at 375° for 15 minutes.
Top cream cheese mixture with parsley.
Serve with toasted bread slices.
Makes 6 servings.

title: hot chicken spread
directions: Mix cracker crumbs and almonds to make 2 cups.
Combine with rest of ingredients and put into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake uncovered about 45 minutes in 350° oven.
This is wonderful served hot or cold on crackers, bread or as a spread for raw veggies. This serves more than six.
I am always asked to bring this for baby or wedding showers or parties I attend.
I hope you enjoy it as much as I do.
This is very easy.
Cooking the chicken and cutting it up takes the most time.
Be sure to save the broth to use in the recipe.
Happy cooking!!!

title: pickled bologna
directions: Bring ingredients to a boil. Cut bologna in 2-inch pieces and prick skin. Pour sauce over bologna and refrigerate several days.

title: pork chops and scalloped potatoes
directions: Note:
For larger casserole, add more pork chops and potatoes.

title: oven baked chicken wings
directions: Combine all ingredients and marinate for 2 hours.
Bake for 1 hour or until nicely browned at 350°.

title: turkey hash
directions: In nonstick skillet heat 2 teaspoons of the oil.
Add onion. Saute over medium-low heat until onion begins to brown.
Stir in potatoes, turkey and parsley.
Season to taste.
Add broth or gravy.
Brush 9 to 10-inch round baking dish or cast-iron skillet with remaining oil and spoon in turkey mixture.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes until top is nicely browned in 350°
oven.
Serve with ketchup.

title: pussy foot (non-alcoholic drink)
directions: Blend or shake with crushed ice.
Makes 1 serving.

title: mom's white cake
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together.
Add next 5 ingredients. Beat for one minute, then add additional 1/4 cup of water and additional 1/4 cup milk.
Beat for one half a minute.
Add egg whites, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Continue to beat for 1 1/2 minutes.
Bake in 2 greased, waxed paper lined, floured 9-inch square cake pans or a 9 x 13-inch cake pan in moderate oven (350°) for 30 minutes.

title: kathy's kasserole
