directions: Cube bread and place in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch oblong dish. Brown sausage and drain well.
Place sausage on top of bread.
In a bowl, mix eggs, soup and milk and then pour on top.
Top with shredded cheese.
Bake about 30 minutes in moderate oven.
Garnish with fresh parsley.
Serves 8 to 10 people.

title: kraut salad
directions: Bring the vinegar and sugar to a boil to dissolve. Cool. Combine. Cover and refrigerate at least 24 hours. Will keep several weeks.

title: quick chicken chowder
directions: Cook celery and onion in butter until tender, but not brown. Stir in peas and potatoes, broth, milk, rosemary and dash of pepper.
Cook and stir until mixture boils.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer about 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add chicken and heat to boiling.
Serve hot and sprinkle crumbled, crisp-cooked bacon or paprika over the top.
Makes 4 servings.

title: sweet potato crisps
directions: Using vegetable peeler, cut potatoes into paper thin strips. In a 12-inch skillet over medium heat or in an electric skillet, heat 1-inch vegetable oil to 400° (see note).
Drop handful of potato strips into hot oil; fry about 2 minutes until crisp and golden.
Using slotted spoon, remove to paper towels to drain. Repeat with remaining potatoes.
Sprinkle lightly with salt to serve.
Makes 6 servings.
Per Serving:
316 calories, 2 grams protein, 19 grams fat and 36 grams carbohydrates.

title: apricot dressing
directions: Cut apricots in small pieces.
Add crumbs, butter, celery, almonds, salt and pepper; mix well.

title: rosy rhubarb mold
directions: Cook rhubarb in water until just tender.
Add jello and salt to hot mixture and stir until dissolved.
Chill, then fold in apples and nuts.
Chill and serve.

title: quick mackinac island fudge
directions: Bring first 6 ingredients to boil and boil for 6 minutes, stirring continuously.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla and powdered sugar and mix with electric mixer for 6 minutes.
Pour in buttered pan and place in freezer for 20 minutes.
Enjoy!

title: fruit cake
directions: Chop or cut the mixture together, leaving nuts in large pieces. Use tube pan (10 x 4-inch) with bottom and sides lined with greased paper.
Set water under the pan for baking.
Bake 2 hours in 250° to 275° oven.
Let cool in pan overnight.
(Line with greased brown paper bag to fit pan.)

title: brownie cake
directions: Melt and let stand
the shortening and cocoa.
Mix together the sugar, flour, eggs and vanilla.
Mix the shortening/cocoa with the flour, etc.
Add 2 cups pecans and bake 20 minutes at 400° in a 9 x 12-inch greased pan.
Cover with small marshmallows while hot then frost with cocoa icing.

title: blackberry pie
directions: Put first 4 ingredients in bowl.
Mix lightly.
Put in pie crust.
Cover with top crust.
Prick with fork.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes, then bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: coconut cake
directions: Mix cake mix, eggs, oil and water until creamy.
Bake at 350 for 30-35 minutes. Make 2 layers and cool.
Mix 1/2 of coconut and Cool Whip.
Frost cake with Cool Whip and coconut mixture. Sprinkle top with Coconut.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Put all this in bowl and stir real well.
Spray casserole dish with Pam and put all ingredients in casserole.
Sprinkle 2/3 cup crackers (crushed) on top and dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: oreo cake
directions: Mix together cookies (saving some to sprinkle on top of cake) and margarine.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Blend cheese and sugar; spread on cookies.
Beat chocolate pudding and 1 1/2 cups milk until thick.
Spread on top.
Then add 1 container of Cool Whip.
Mix vanilla pudding and 1 1/2 cups milk until thick.
Add on top.
Then add remaining container of Cool Whip.
Sprinkle remaining cookies on top of cake.
Refrigerate.

title: grandma keller's cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Roll a teaspoonful of dough in a ball and tip the top of dough in water, then in sugar.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes or until golden brown.
Can use colored sugar.

title: cherry salad
directions: Mix all of the ingredients and chill.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix the first 2 ingredients together and set aside.
Mix cake mix, melted oleo and the 3/4 cup milk.
Pour 1/2 the cake batter in a 9 x 12-inch cake pan that has been greased and floured.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Spread melted caramel mixture over top of hot cake.
Sprinkle chocolate chips on top of caramel.
Sprinkle pecans on top of chips.
Pour remaining batter over all and bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Let cool.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni.
Cook peas as directed and drain.
Mix macaroni, peas, cheese, gherkins, mayonnaise and onion.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Cover well and refrigerate at least 3 hours before serving.

title: veggie wedgies
directions: Pat out crescent rolls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 9 to 11 minutes until lightly browned.
Cool.
Mix cream cheese, dressing and mayonnaise.
Spread over rolls.
Spread vegetables over mixture (use any vegetables desired).
Chill well.
Cut into wedges and serve.
Nice alternative to sweet appetizer/snack.

title: roquefort grapes(makes 50 hors d'oeuvres)
directions: To toast nuts, preheat oven to 275°.
Spread nuts on baking sheet and bake until toasted.
Almonds should be a light golden brown color; pecans or walnuts should smell toasted, but not burned.
Chop toasted nuts rather coarsely.
Spread on a platter. Using electric mixer, combine Roquefort, cream cheese and cream and beat until smooth.
Drop clean, dry grapes into the cheese mixture and gently stir by hand to coat them.
Then roll the coated grapes in the toasted nuts and put on a tray lined with waxed paper.
Chill until ready to serve.

title: cheddar zucchini bake
directions: Cook zucchini until tender and drain.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper to taste.
Combine egg yolks, sour cream and flour. Beat egg whites until stiff and fold into sour cream mixture.
Place half the zucchini in an 11 x 7-inch baking dish.
Top with half the sour cream mixture and half the cheese.
Sprinkle crumbled bacon over cheese.
Layer remaining zucchini, sour cream mixture and cheese.
Melt butter and stir in crumbs.
Sprinkle over cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Boil sweet potatoes in jackets.
Remove skins and mash well. Add eggs, sugar, brown sugar, vanilla, milk and oleo.
Mix well and place in 2-quart casserole.

title: orange spice tea
directions: Mix well.
Store in air tight container.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Grease an 8-inch square glass dish.
Mix together flour, sugar and grated cheese.
Place drained pineapple chunks into casserole dish.
Pour flour mixture over top of pineapple. Add crushed crackers on top and pour melted butter over top of crackers.
Cook at 325° for 30 minutes or until crackers are lightly browned. Serves 4 to 6.

title: ladyfingers
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add water and vanilla.
Mix well. Blend in flour and nuts.
Chill 4 hours.
Shape in balls or fingers.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet about 20 minutes at 350°. Remove from pan and cool slightly.
Roll in powdered sugar.

title: corn casserole
directions: Cook green pepper and onion until tender; drain.
Mix both cans corn, eggs and muffin mix.
Add to pepper and onion.
Place in 2-quart greased casserole.
Spread cheese over top and bake 40 to 55 minutes in 350° oven.

title: sweet and sour pork
directions: Cut pork into bite-sized cubes.
Marinate pork in soy sauce, wine and ginger for 15 minutes.
Coat pork with cornstarch.
Fry until crisp.
Drain.
Cut onion, green pepper and carrot into sections.
Heat oil.
Add garlic, onion and green pepper; fry quickly.
Add seasoning and soup.
Bring to boil.
Thicken with cornstarch mixed with water and ketchup.
Add vinegar.
Add fried pork; mix well.
Serve hot on rice.

title: tasty cheese bread
directions: Tips:
Wheat germ that is toasted does not become rancid, so has better keeping qualities.
If you wish, the poppy seed can be stirred into the batter for an attractive, tasty loaf.
If you like, you can substitute Blue cheese for the Cheddar.
Top loaves with chopped walnuts.

title: lemon pie
directions: Mix lemonade and condensed milk. Add Cool Whip. Put in graham cracker crust and refrigerate.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: In a large skillet, over medium heat, saute onion, celery and broccoli in butter for 3 to 5 minutes.
Stir in cheese, soup and milk until smooth.

title: sheet cake & frosting
directions: In medium or large saucepan, bring to boil and stir till well blended: water, oleo & cocoa.
In a separate bowl, combine sugar, flour, eggs, soda, cinnamon, vanilla, milk.
Mix together well and add to boiled mixture.
Grease large cookie sheet and sides.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes only, then 375° for 20 minutes only. Spread with hot frosting while warm.

title: yum yum cookies
directions: Mix all
ingredients and let stand 2 1/2 hours. Use wet hands. Roll dough in little balls with powdered sugar.
Place on greased cookie sheet and bake at 325° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: broccoli rotini
directions: Cook rotini as directed.
Drain and set aside.
Melt butter in a wok or 5-quart pot.
Add onions, garlic and mushrooms; saute until browned.
Add broccoli flowerets and cook for 5 to 7 minutes.
Pour in the rotini and stir well.
Add salt, pepper and garlic salt to taste.
Add the half and half and simmer until it thickens, stirring occasionally.
Serves 4 to 6 people.

title: easy salad
directions: Prepare macaroni as directed.
Add pepper, carrots, cheese and onion.
Add salt.
Mix sugar, vinegar and oil.
Add to salad. Refrigerate.
Stir several times.
Better if made the day before.

title: corn casserole
directions: Beat eggs, oil and garlic salt.
Add Jiffy corn bread mix and beat again.
Stir in cream-style corn.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: grandma's potato salad
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Gently fold in potatoes and vegetables.
Chill several hours or overnight for maximum flavor.

title: carrot cake
directions: *Ahead of time, pour boiling water over raisins.
Let cool to plump them up.

title: poor man's soup
directions: Brown ground meat; drain fat.
Add rest of ingredients.
Cook on medium-low for approximately 2 hours, until veggies are tender.

title: blueberry coffee cake
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking powder, soda, cinnamon and salt.
Gently fold in blueberries in a small bowl. Whisk together the egg, milk and margarine.
Add to the flour mixture; stir carefully.
Spread into a greased 8 x 8-inch baking pan.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes and slice thin.
Make white sauce of oleo, flour and milk.
Put half the potatoes in greased 2-quart casserole. Cover with half the sauce, seasonings and onion.
Sprinkle with celery flakes and cheese.
Add remaining ingredients in layers. Sprinkle with celery flakes.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour. Uncover and continue to bake until top is browned.

title: chess cake
directions: Mix cake mix, butter and
1 egg together and press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cream powdered sugar, cream cheese, vanilla and 3 eggs together.
Pour over crust.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes. Cool completely.
Cut into small squares.

title: dirt dessert
directions: Cream together butter, cream cheese and confectioners sugar. Mix together the pudding and milk and add to cream mixture.
Layer cookie crumbs (reserve some for later use), pudding mix, and Cool Whip.
Top with a few (reserved) cookie crumbs.

title: caramel tapioca dessert
directions: Soak tapioca in 6 cups water overnight.
Add brown sugar. Bake at 350° until tapioca is clear and liquid thickens.
Remove from oven; cool and refrigerate for at least 2 hours before serving.

title: baked chicken and rice
directions: Melt margarine in a 2-quart dish in oven at 425°.
Add remaining ingredients except chicken and paprika.
Mix well.
Put uncooked chicken on top and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Turn chicken over sprinkling paprika on the other side. Continue baking for 30 more minutes.

title: pea salad
directions: Combine peas, celery, cheese and onion.
In separate bowl, blend salt, pepper, mayonnaise and lemon juice together until smooth.
Add to peas; mix well.

title: fruit compote
directions: Combine sugar and cornstarch in a saucepan; stir well.
Drain pineapple, reserving 3/4 cup juice.
Add reserved juice and next 3 items to cornstarch mixture, stirring until smooth.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thickened and bubbly. Combine fruit.
Pour hot glaze over fruit; gently stir to coat. Cover and refrigerate until chilled.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Cook sugar,
Karo,
peanuts and salt on High 6 minutes. Stir. Cook 9
more minutes on High.
Add margarine and vanilla.
Cook 1 minute.
Stir
in
soda.
Pour on buttered sheet. Cool.
Break in pieces.

title: fruity milk drink
directions: Blend in blender.
Pack into prechilled thermos.
Great for lunch box.

title: fruit salad
directions: Make pudding with pineapple juice, instant pudding and Tang. Slice bananas and add to pudding with fruit.
Chill both fruits before making.
This is good for diabetic diet.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Mix first seven ingredients in order given.
Put mixture into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: quick dessert
directions: Combine and stir through quickly.
Refrigerate 1 hour.

title: hamburger soup
directions: Brown meat with seasoning, onion and celery.
Cook noodles until done.
Drain meat.
Add noodles and water along with broth and tomatoes to the meat mixture.
Simmer.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Stir together the flour, cinnamon and nutmeg.
In large mixing bowl, beat shortening for 30 seconds. Add brown sugar; beat until light and fluffy.
Beat in eggs.
Add flour mixture alternately with milk, beating well after each addition.
Stir in oats, raisins and nuts.
Drop from a spoon onto ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for about 8 minutes, or until barely brown.

title: fruit dip
directions: Blend
well
in blender or mixer.
Recipe may be cut in half. Makes
approximately
cup.
Serve with strawberries, cut up melons, sliced apples, pineapple, bananas, etc.

title: basic herb butter
directions: Combine ingredients; mix until fluffy.
Store in refrigerator at least one hour to develop flavor.

title: popcorn cake
directions: Melt butter; add marshmallows when butter is warm.
Mix until all is melted.
Pour into a large pan and mix in nuts, popcorn and then M&M's.
Mix well and press down into angel food pan.
Let cool.
Turn out on cake plate.
Keep at room temperature.
It's ready to eat.

title: coconut macaroon cookies
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Gradually add sugar and salt. Add vanilla and fold into coconut and corn flakes.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake in 350° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: In a 9 x 12-inch casserole (round or flat), layer lettuce (1-inch deep) and remaining vegetables in order listed.
Spread mayonnaise over top.
Sprinkle freely with Parmesan cheese. Decorate as desired with cherry tomatoes.
Serves 8.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Cook chicken with onion, celery leaves, 1 teaspoon salt and 1/2 teaspoon pepper.
Strain stock.
Cut chicken into small cubes. Cook spaghetti per package directions.
Drain.
Wash, drain mushrooms, slice.
Saute 5 minutes in 1 tablespoon butter, combine with spaghetti.
Melt remaining 3 tablespoons butter.
Stir in flour smoothly.
Stir chicken stock, cook until thickened.
Remove from heat.
Stir in cream, add sherry a little at a time.
Start oven at 375°.
Grease 2 quart casserole.
Combine sauce and chicken with spaghetti, sprinkle grated cheese over all.
Bake 25 minutes or until top is lightly browned.
Makes 8 servings.

title: jet's chicken casserole
directions: Put chicken in a pan and cover with water; put in salt and boil until tender.
Remove chicken (reserve liquid in pan) and cut into bite-sized pieces.
Cook vegetables in 2 cups of the reserved chicken broth, boiling on low for 6 minutes.
Drain vegetables; mix with chicken, cheese soup, pepper and chives.
Pour into 2 1/2-quart casserole dish that has been sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serves 6.
Preparation time:
1 hour 15 minutes.

title: 3 hour refrigerator pickles
directions: Mix cold.
Slice cucumbers 1/4-inch thick.
Slice onion 1/8-inch thick.
Place both in a large nonmetallic bowl.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Pour over cucumbers and onions.
Stir well for 5 minutes.
Cover and refrigerate 3 hours before serving.

title: six week bran muffins
directions: Mix dry ingredients in very large bowl.
Add eggs, oil, buttermilk and molasses; mix and store in refrigerator overnight. Will keep six weeks.
Do not freeze dough.
Fill muffin tins 2/3 full.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake according to package directions.
Cool. Crumble 1/2 of 1 layer cake in bottom of punch bowl; add some pudding, cherries, pineapple, bananas and nuts.
Crumble other 1/2 of 1 layer and repeat.
Continue until punch bowl is full.
Top with Cool Whip and sprinkle with nuts.
Refrigerate.

title: assorted fruit with dip
directions: These fruits are just suggestions.
You may choose any fruit.

title: frozen punch
directions: Mix well.
Freeze to a slush.
May also freeze in small container and when partially thawed, put in a blender.

title: crock-pot apple butter
directions: Pour vinegar into bottom of crock-pot.
In large bowl, mix applesauce, sugar, candies and cloves.
Pour into pot.
Cover with a wet cloth.
Do not use lid.
Cook on high for 4 hours.
Stir occasionally.
Pour into hot jars and seal.
Makes 4 pints.

title: squash casserole
directions: Melt 1 stick of oleo and mix with the package of dressing mix until crumbly.
Cook squash and onion in small amount of salted water 5 minutes.
Drain liquid.
Add cream of chicken soup and 1 cup sour cream to squash.
Mix well.
Place half of dressing in bottom of 9 x 13 x 2-inch dish, then add squash mixture.
Cover top with remaining dressing mixture and bake at 300° for 30 minutes.

title: chili
directions: Cook chuck until almost done.
Drain.
Add tomato paste, onion, salt and pepper to taste.
Add 6 ounces of water and simmer 15 minutes.
Add chili powder.
Put beans in cooker and simmer.
Add meat mixture and simmer 15 minutes.
Serve with crackers and shredded cheese.

title: wilted greens salad
directions: Tear greens into bite sized pieces and place in mixing bowl, adding sprouts and water chestnuts.
Cut bacon into small pieces and cook over medium heat until crisp, do not drain.
Add onion, vinegar, ketchup and sugar to bacon and drippings, stirring to combine.
Cook and stir till mixture is heated through.
Remove pan from heat, stir greens into pan, stirring until spinach is slightly wilted.
Turn into salad bowl and serve warm.

title: orange chicken
directions: Season chicken parts with salt, pepper and garlic salt. Dip chicken in flour. Brown chicken in pan with butter. When browned, pour orange juice in pan to almost cover chicken. Simmer until orange juice thickens into sauce. Serve over rice.

title: broccoli rice bake
directions: Cook rice in water according to directions on box.
Saute onion in margarine.
Add broccoli and simmer until tender.
Mix soup and chunks of cheese.
Mix ingredients lightly.
Place in baking dish.
Top with croutons.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: taco salad
directions: Mix cream cheese and sour cream together and spread on round platter.
Pour taco sauce over cheese mixture evenly.
Shred lettuce and put on top of taco sauce.
Put diced tomatoes on top of lettuce.
Next, put diced onions on top of tomatoes.
Spread shredded cheese on top of onions.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown meat; drain fat.
Add garlic, onion, salt, pepper, tomato paste and water.
Simmer for 45 to 60 minutes.
Cook noodles as directed.
Mix eggs in cottage cheese.
Spread part of sauce in dish, then layer of noodles, sauce, cottage cheese and Mozzarella cheese, then repeat.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: tortilla cobbler
directions: Melt 1 stick oleo in Pyrex dish in microwave.
Place 1 tablespoon filling in center of tortilla, roll up and place in oleo in dish.
Roll all 10 tortillas.
Mix water, sugar and vanilla.
Heat this mixture until sugar has dissolved and pour over tortillas.
Cook in oven at 350° for 40 minutes or until brown and bubbly.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: party cheese ball
directions: Combine all ingredients except pecans and mix well.
Shape into a ball and roll in pecans. Prepare a few hours ahead so flavors can blend.
Great on any crackers.

title: grandma tiger's horseradish pickles
directions: Grating the fresh horseradish will give you an excuse to shed some tears.

title: shortbread cookies
directions: Cream together margarine and sugars; add egg yolk and blend well.
Add flour and pecans.
Mix well.
Form dough into small balls and press flat with floured fork on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° until lightly browned, about 8 minutes.

title: impossible pie
directions: Put everything into blender.
Mix well.
Pour into 9-inch well-greased pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until custard is set.

title: onion rice
directions: Mix and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Stir after 1/2 hour of baking.
You can sprinkle a little garlic powder on before cooking.

title: strawberry punch(timmy's favorite punch)
directions: Mix ingredients in gallon jug. Fill the rest of gallon jug with water.
Shake well.

title: 10-minute meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients and shape into a round or oval loaf. Place in microwave-safe dish; cover with wax paper and microwave on High for 10 minutes, turning dish after 5 minutes of cooking. Drain and cover with foil.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving. Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: all in one casserole
directions: Brown meat, onion, salt & pepper, and whatever seasonings desired. Layer beef, frozen vegetables, then tater tots in a greased casserole dish. Mix can of soup with milk and pour over top. Bake uncovered at 350° for 1 hour.

title: apple oatmeal bars
directions: Make a crumb mixture of the flour, salt, baking soda, brown sugar and oatmeal.
Cut the shortening into the crumb mixture. The mixture will be dry.
Spread half of the mixture on the bottom of a greased 9 x 13-inch Pyrex baking dish or greased metal pan. Arrange the apples over the mixture.
Dot with butter.
Sprinkle the cup of sugar over the apples.
Sprinkle cinnamon over all. Cover apples with remaining crumb mixture; pat mixture over apples.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.
Cool; cut into 3-inch or larger squares.
May be used as a dessert with a scoop of vanilla ice cream or whipped topping.

title: deviled crab
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine the celery, green pepper, scallions, parsley, crabmeat, 1 1/2 cups crushed crackers, salt, mustard, few drops of Tabasco sauce, cream and 1/2 cup melted butter.
Mix together gently but thoroughly.
Spoon mixture into buttered seafood shells (can purchase at Pier 1), sprinkling the remaining cracker crumbs equally between the portions.
Dribble the remaining butter on top.
Bake at 350° about 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve immediately.
Serves 6.

title: grilled fish steaks
directions: Marinate steaks in sauce-oleo mixture for 30 minutes to several hours in refrigerator.
Cover and bake in 350° oven for 10 minutes for each 1/2-inch thickness.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in water.
Add marshmallows and place over low heat, stirring until completely dissolved.
Add pineapple juice and let set until partially jelled.
Add pineapple, cottage cheese and whipped cream.
Stir as little as possible to mix and pour into mold.
Chill until firm.

You can add 1/2 cup chopped pecans to this salad if you like them (I think it really makes it better). If you don't want to put this in a mold, you can pour it into a 9x13x2 pan and cut into squares to serve.
This is another good company dish.
It can be done in advance and forgotten until serving time.

title: lemon pie
directions: Combine cornstarch, lemon juice, lemon rind and sugar.
Beat egg yolks and add to first mixture.
Gradually add boiling water. Heat to boil over direct heat for 4 minutes, gently stirring constantly.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Beat egg whites until stiff, not dry.
Gradually add powdered sugar.
Spread on top of lemon filling.
Bake at 425° for 4 to 5 minutes.
Cool away from draft.

title: overnight bread
directions: Combine yeast, 1 tablespoon sugar and 1 cup of warm water. Combine 1 cup sugar, eggs, shortening, 4 cups warm water and salt. Add yeast mixture and flour, alternating.
Mix and add enough flour to make dough easy to handle.
Turn dough onto lightly floured surface; knead in enough flour until smooth and elastic (takes a lot of flour).
Put dough in greased bowl.
Cover and allow to raise until double. Punch down and allow to raise again. Do this every hour for about three times.
Shape into loaves or rolls; place in greased pans.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake in the morning at 350° for about 30 to 40 minutes or until golden brown.

title: spanish coffee cake
directions: Mix well first 5 ingredients. Remove 1/2 cup of mixture into small bowl and add cinnamon and nuts; set aside. To rest of mixture add remaining ingredients. Mix well. Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle nut topping on batter. Stir around on top with fork. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Season chicken with salt and pepper and onion and garlic salt. Flour and fry until lightly browned.
Drain chicken.
Pour oil from skillet and saute onion and celery.
Add bouillon and Kitchen Bouquet.
Add water and rice.
Place chicken on top and cover tightly.
Place in oven for about 30 minutes at 400°.

title: fish batter
directions: Beat egg and milk together in one bowl.
Mix cornmeal, flour and Ranch mix in a separate bowl.
Dip fish in egg mixture and then in cornmeal mixture.
Fry in medium heat until done.

title: keri's banana nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream together shortening and sugar. Add, while using mixer, bananas, milk, eggs, flour, baking powder, salt and nutmeg.
Fold in chopped nuts.
Pour mixture into well-greased pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes if in loaf pan. Bake for 15 minutes for muffin tins.

title: cherry delight
directions: Mix cottage cheese and dry jello in bowl.
Fold in Cool Whip. Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: cranberry sauce
directions: Pick over and wash the berries carefully.
Place in saucepan with the boiling water.
Boil until all the berries have burst open, about 10 minutes.
Pour into sieve and mash through as much of the pulp as possible.
Add the sugar.
Return to heat and bring slowly to full rolling boil, stirring constantly so that all the sugar is dissolved.
Boil until the mixture falls in a sheet from the spoon, about 5 minutes.
Pour at once into heat resistant glass dish.
Chill until set.
Serve with meat, fish or poultry. Serves 6.

title: easy pie crust
directions: Mix together until crumbly. Add water.
Roll out onto floured board for 8-inch pie plate.

title: johnny cake
directions: Sift all ingredients.
Beat corn meal, egg and Crisco until smooth.
Add dry ingredients and milk.
Beat 2 minutes; add 1 to 2 cups corn and fold in.
Grease 8-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes, until center is done.

title: hungry jack casserole
directions: Brown beef.

Add next 4 ingredients and place in a 1 1/2-quart casserole. Cut biscuits in half and place on top of mixture, cut side down, around the edge of the casserole dish. Top with cheese. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: sticky buns
directions: Thaw bread slightly; break 1 loaf into small pieces.
Place in layer in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt margarine.
Add dry pudding, brown sugar, cinnamon, milk and nuts.
Bring to boil; stir constantly.
Cool slightly and pour mixture over rolls evenly.
Break other loaf into smaller pieces and place on top of other layer.
Let rise in warm spot until it reaches top of pan. Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 30 minutes.
Flip over on cookie sheet immediately.

title: crock-pot ham
directions: Cut up ham to fit into crock-pot.
Add water to cover ham; add orange juice and brown sugar and cook on high for 2 to 3 hours. Lower heat and cook until desired tenderness is reached.

title: homemade rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water; mix sugar, eggs and oil well. Add flour and salt; add warm milk.
Stir and mix well.
Add yeast mixture and blend until smooth.
Place in warm place. Let rise for 1 1/2 hours.

title: simply delicious coconut cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions.
While cake is still hot, use fork to make holes in top of cake.
Mix condensed milk and cream of coconut.
While cake is still warm, pour milk mixture on top.
Let cake cool completely.
Can even be stored in refrigerator overnight.
Before serving, spread Cool Whip on top and sprinkle coconut on top of Cool Whip.
Best coconut cake you've ever tasted.

title: sauerbraten and noodles or mashed potatoes
directions: Brown meat in oil.
Remove meat from skillet.
Add gravy mix and water.
Bring to a boil, stirring.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Add meat and pour into a 1 1/2-quart casserole. Cover and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Remove leaf and serve over noodles or mashed potatoes.

title: mock hollandaise dressing
directions: Mix and heat in top of double boiler.
Good over hot vegetables.

title: crab casserole
directions: Mix shrimp, soup, mayo and milk.
Add crabmeat; mix well.
Add noodles and 1/2 cup cheese.
Spread in baking dish.
Top with 1/2 cup cheese.
Cover and bake 25 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven; top with onion rings and bake 10 minutes more.

title: delicious chicken casserole
directions: Stew chicken until it falls off bone.
Remove from bone and set aside.
Use 2 cans of broth for simmering onion until tender.
Mix cream of chicken and cream of mushroom soups.
Add margarine and blend together until smooth.

title: roast corned beef and steamed cabbage
directions: Note:
Do not add salt to this meat recipe.

title: fruit punch for teenagers
directions: Boil 2 cups water and 2 cups of sugar for 10 minutes.
When cold add 3 cups cold tea, 1 cup lemon juice, 1 cup orange juice, 1 can crushed pineapple, juice and all, 1 small bottle maraschino cherries and mix well together.
When ready to serve, pour over ice cubes and pour in 2 large bottles ginger ale.

title: red cabbage with wine and apples
directions: Cut salt pork into tiny cubes.
Cook with onions and carrots for 10 minutes without browning.
Stir in cabbage; cut into 1/2-inch slices.
Cook 10 minutes.
Add and stir all remaining spices and ingredients.
Place in covered casserole.
Bake at 325° for 3 to 3 1/2 hours.

title: triway school hot rolls
directions: Put water and oil in mixer bowl, attach bread hook.
Mix about 5 pounds flour and other dry ingredients together in a small pan then add gradually to water with mixer speed set on low.
Keep adding flour until the dough is quite stiff then set speed on medium and let mix for a few minutes.
Divide dough into 3 batches and knead until it is not sticky.
Put into large oiled pan to rise until pan is full, then make into rolls.
Let rise again.
Makes 480 rolls.
Bake at 350°.

title: chocolate treats
directions: Melt chips and peanut butter in double boiler.
Stir well. Pour over corn flakes.
Drop on waxed paper.

title: aunt genny's baked beans
directions: Mix ingredients in pan.
Cook until thick over medium heat about 45 minutes.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Cook and drain spinach.
Cool.
Combine and blend with other ingredients.
Chill for one hour.

title: turkey casserole(family recipe)
directions: Saute celery, onion and pepper in butter; add turkey, cream, broth, seasonings and spaghetti.
Top with buttered crumbs.
Cook in slow oven until mixture bubbles and crumbs brown, about 30 minutes.
Serve with cranberry mold.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Mix all ingredients together except margarine.
Pour into a greased casserole dish.
Top with margarine.
Bake until brown at 350°.

title: pear liqueur
directions: Remove seeds and dice the pears.
Put in a large glass jar along with the spices, vodka, and sliced orange peel.
Cover the jar and place in a cool area for two weeks.
(Do not put in refrigerator).
After two weeks, strain the mixture and discard the diced pear, orange peel, clove and peppercorn pieces.
Put the strained mixture back in the glass jar.
Dissolve the sugar in the water and add that mixture to the strained mixture in the glass jar.

Cover the mixture and let this sit for two more weeks. After two weeks the mixture can be transferred into smaller bottles for gift giving or or in any other type of bottle that you wish to keep it in.
It is best to place the mixture in the refrigerator at this time, or it can be kept indefinitely in the freezer.
This is a mild, sweet liqueur that is especially good over vanilla ice cream.

title: lentil-barley stew
directions: Saute oleo, chopped celery and chopped onion.
Add water and lentils.
Cover and cook 20 minutes.
Add tomatoes, barley and seasonings listed and simmer for 45 minutes.
Add carrots (shredded) and cook for 5 minutes.

title: cucumber appetizer
directions: Do not peel cukes.
Score lengthwise with fork and slice them. Slice onions and separate into rings.
Combine vinegar, sugar and salt in small pan and stir over low heat until the sugar dissolves.
Bring mixture to boil.
Pour over cukes and onions. Mix well and chill.
These can be frozen.
When defrosted, use within 1 week.
Serves 4 to 6 people.

title: lemon drop cookies
directions: Cream together shortening, sugar, eggs and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Sift together dry ingredients; add alternately with lemon juice.
Drop by teaspoon 2-inches apart on greased cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with red or regular sugar.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes. Makes about 3 dozen.

title: edwena's last minute supper
directions: Cut smoked sausage into small pieces.
Place into a large skillet.
Peel potatoes and cut into quarters.
Place on top of sausage.
Put broccoli on top of potatoes and add about 2/3 cup of water.
Cover with lid and cook slowly for about 20 minutes, or until potatoes are tender and broccoli is well steamed.
"While this is cooking, bake up a pone of yellow cornbread."

title: waffle cookies
directions: Stir by hand in order.
Drop by spoonful on waffle iron. Makes 8 dozen.

title: apple crisp pie
directions: Butter a pie pan or baking dish.
Set aside.
Mix apples, cinnamon and 1 tablespoon of sugar.
Arrange apples in dish and combine sugar and flour.
Mix butter/margarine into flour, mix until crumbly.
Sprinkle crumbs over apples.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes, until apples are tender and crust is golden brown. Top with whipped cream.

title: honey roasted chicken
directions: Melt butter.
Add onion and garlic.
Saute
3 to 5 minutes. Add mustard, honey, salt, curry, preserves and currants.
Cool sauce.
Dip chicken into sauce and place in shallow roasting pan, skin side up.
Spoon remaining sauce over chicken.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour.

title: chocolate - caramel pretzels
directions: Cut caramel apple wraps into strips that will wrap around the pretzel rods.
Melt almond bark according to directions in a flat bottom dish (8x8 works well).
Roll pretzel in chocolate until completely covered.
Place on wax paper to cool. Sprinkle with colored sprinkles or drizzle with colored chocolate if desired. It helps to wrap all the pretzels in caramel before you melt the chocolate.

title: myra's popcorn balls
directions: Combine ingredients altogether in pan.
Stir constantly.
Boil until soft ball.
Add a pinch of soda when taken from fire.
Pour over approximately 4-quarts of popped popcorn.
Make into balls.

title: upside-down cake
directions: Melt 2 tablespoons butter in a 9-inch pan.
Add brown sugar; stir until melted.
Place pineapple and nuts over butter and brown sugar mixture.
Combine white sugar and egg, milk, vanilla, 2 tablespoons butter and shortening.
Add flour, baking powder and salt.
Pour over pineapple and brown sugar mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes; cool to lukewarm and turn out onto plate.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Put chicken, soups, onion and mixed vegetables in deep, large skillet.
Season to taste.
Add milk or water (approximately 1 cup).
Add noodles and cook until they are tender.
Serve with salad and bread.
A quick and easy recipe for when you are in a hurry.

title: yellow pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into Bundt cake pan.
Cook in 350° oven for 50 to 60 minutes.
Very tasty!

title: cheese toasties
directions: Microwave bacon and set aside.

title: classic baked pasta casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Prepare pasta as package directs.
In large bowl, combine pasta, sausage, pasta sauce and 2 cups cheese. Mix well.
Turn into greased 11 x 9-inch baking dish; cover. Bake 45 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Uncover; top with remaining 2 cups cheese and parsley.
Bake 10 minutes longer or until cheese melts.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: sadie's baked chicken breasts
directions: Take a piece of bacon, place a chicken breast on top, then a slice of dried beef, roll and stick with a toothpick.
Grease a loaf pan.
Place chicken breasts in pan.
Mix soup with sour cream.
Pour over chicken breasts and dot with butter or margarine.
Bake at 275° for 1 hour and 45 minutes, uncovered.

title: egg pie
directions: Mix ingredients in the order given.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes, or until firm.
Use unbaked pie shell.
You may double, even quadruple, this recipe.

title: low-fat oven corn chips
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Spray 2 large baking sheets.
Combine spices.
Stack tortillas and cut through center with sharp knife to make 6 equal wedges of each tortilla.
Arrange wedges without touching on baking sheets.
Spray lightly and sprinkle with seasonings.
Bake (400°) 8 to 10 minutes, or until lightly browned and crisp.
Cool and store in airtight plastic bags. Serve with salsa or low-fat dip.

title: broccoli-cheese casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Cook broccoli and rice according to package directions.
Set aside.
Saute diced onion in butter.
Add can of mushroom soup, Rotel, and Cheez Whiz over low heat.
Stir mixture thoroughly.
Remove from heat and combine rice, broccoli and cheeze mixture.
Pour into a casserole dish and bake for 30-45 minutes until heated through and has a golden brown crust.
